WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:00.515 --> 00:00:03.406
- [Narrator] The land of China was once shrouded in mystery

00:00:03.422 --> 00:00:05.360
to the rest of the ancient world.

00:00:05.376 --> 00:00:08.270
The Silk Road was a connection between the two realms

00:00:08.270 --> 00:00:11.625
that suggested China to be of immense wealth and power.

00:00:13.790 --> 00:00:17.510
Whilst these distant civilizations would see dramatic falls,

00:00:17.510 --> 00:00:21.198
China would continue to rise through countless dynasties

00:00:21.214 --> 00:00:23.237
and emperors for thousands of years

00:00:23.253 --> 00:00:26.245
forming the global superpower we know today

00:00:26.261 --> 00:00:28.880
from constructing the longest structure in the world

00:00:28.880 --> 00:00:30.260
to hosting the largest

00:00:30.260 --> 00:00:32.930
and deadliest wars in mankind's history.

00:00:32.930 --> 00:00:36.890
China is the longest continuous civilization on earth

00:00:36.890 --> 00:00:40.940
dating back 5,000 years, withstanding the ancient era,

00:00:40.940 --> 00:00:44.360
the middle Ages, and now the modern period.

00:00:44.360 --> 00:00:46.520
But can they continue on?

00:00:46.520 --> 00:00:48.860
To understand this fascinating land,

00:00:48.860 --> 00:00:50.993
we must start from the beginning.

00:00:52.640 --> 00:00:55.390
(dramatic music)

00:00:56.870 --> 00:00:59.570
The majority of China's earliest settlements began

00:00:59.570 --> 00:01:02.060
along the basin of the yellow River in the north

00:01:02.060 --> 00:01:04.100
and the Yangtze in the south.

00:01:04.100 --> 00:01:06.050
The people resided on floodplains

00:01:06.050 --> 00:01:08.480
and lived agricultural lifestyles,

00:01:08.480 --> 00:01:11.180
growing a plethora of millet and rice.

00:01:11.180 --> 00:01:13.160
The conditions were fair for farming,

00:01:13.160 --> 00:01:16.760
but a major issue plagued the newly blossoming communities

00:01:16.760 --> 00:01:19.760
flooding from the Yellow River constantly displaced

00:01:19.760 --> 00:01:22.460
or killed settlers, washing away their crops

00:01:22.460 --> 00:01:24.290
and lodgings in the process.

00:01:24.290 --> 00:01:26.900
The land was cruel and inhospitable,

00:01:26.900 --> 00:01:29.240
threatening their newfound way of life

00:01:29.240 --> 00:01:33.080
that was unto the legendary and likely mythological,

00:01:33.080 --> 00:01:35.030
Yu the Engineer was tasked

00:01:35.030 --> 00:01:37.310
with controlling the flow of the rivers.

00:01:37.310 --> 00:01:39.530
Yu knew firsthand that the waterways

00:01:39.530 --> 00:01:43.070
had not been the settler's biggest adversary for no reason.

00:01:43.070 --> 00:01:46.370
His father, Gwen had already spearheaded past efforts

00:01:46.370 --> 00:01:47.840
to control the rivers

00:01:47.840 --> 00:01:49.997
and a decade of his life had been spent on building

00:01:49.997 --> 00:01:52.130
his series of dikes and dams,

00:01:52.130 --> 00:01:54.590
which ultimately proved ineffective.

00:01:54.590 --> 00:01:56.090
No matter how large Gwen

00:01:56.090 --> 00:01:57.740
and his men built their walls,

00:01:57.740 --> 00:02:00.650
the river would prevail time and time again.

00:02:00.650 --> 00:02:02.840
Unphased by his father's failures,

00:02:02.840 --> 00:02:04.400
Yu was more than determined

00:02:04.400 --> 00:02:06.710
to carry out the monumental task.

00:02:06.710 --> 00:02:08.240
He recruited the help of one

00:02:08.240 --> 00:02:12.530
Hao Yi another semi mythical agricultural genius

00:02:12.530 --> 00:02:14.960
who is credited with supposedly introducing

00:02:14.960 --> 00:02:16.760
millet to humanity.

00:02:16.760 --> 00:02:18.950
The pair discussed schematics together

00:02:18.950 --> 00:02:22.370
and eventually built a canal based irrigation system,

00:02:22.370 --> 00:02:25.670
which removed most of the excess flood water into the sea

00:02:25.670 --> 00:02:29.570
while saving some to be reutilized for the growing of crops.

00:02:29.570 --> 00:02:33.500
Just like that, the system's debut had finally ended the era

00:02:33.500 --> 00:02:37.370
of flooding and Yu the Engineer was named China's ruler

00:02:37.370 --> 00:02:39.383
on account of his great success.

00:02:41.005 --> 00:02:44.005
(suspenseful music)

00:02:45.380 --> 00:02:47.720
Thus began the Xia Dynasty,

00:02:47.720 --> 00:02:50.510
the catalyst for China's dynastic system.

00:02:50.510 --> 00:02:54.110
The dynasty in its lands were very prosperous under Yu.

00:02:54.110 --> 00:02:56.870
They remained a mainly agricultural society,

00:02:56.870 --> 00:02:59.300
but are credited with creating many great Chinese

00:02:59.300 --> 00:03:02.750
inventions such as stone tools used for farming

00:03:02.750 --> 00:03:04.190
and the lunar calendar.

00:03:04.190 --> 00:03:08.180
Eventually you divided the territory into nine provinces

00:03:08.180 --> 00:03:10.670
and while each one was governed by their own Lord,

00:03:10.670 --> 00:03:13.310
they were required to stay loyal to use rain.

00:03:13.310 --> 00:03:15.560
Long after his years of stopping rivers

00:03:15.560 --> 00:03:17.960
and winning battles against neighboring tribes,

00:03:17.960 --> 00:03:20.360
old age and death closed in on you,

00:03:20.360 --> 00:03:23.090
which brought forth the question, what now?

00:03:23.090 --> 00:03:25.490
Yu decided that he did not want to pass that torch

00:03:25.490 --> 00:03:27.680
of leadership onto his son Qi.

00:03:27.680 --> 00:03:29.450
He instead wished for his Minister

00:03:29.450 --> 00:03:31.970
of Justice GaoYao to take over.

00:03:31.970 --> 00:03:35.240
Unfortunately, GaoYao died soon thereafter,

00:03:35.240 --> 00:03:37.190
and so a tribal leader named Yi

00:03:37.190 --> 00:03:39.110
was chosen to take on the role.

00:03:39.110 --> 00:03:42.230
The provincial Lords disagreed with this decision.

00:03:42.230 --> 00:03:44.630
They had grown so fond of Yu the great

00:03:44.630 --> 00:03:46.880
throughout his 45 years as Emperor,

00:03:46.880 --> 00:03:50.870
that they insisted upon his son Qi being his successor.

00:03:50.870 --> 00:03:52.850
Their wish was eventually granted.

00:03:52.850 --> 00:03:56.330
Qi was the first ruler of China to be granted power,

00:03:56.330 --> 00:03:58.610
not for his merit or capability,

00:03:58.610 --> 00:04:01.160
but because of his bloodline and connections.

00:04:01.160 --> 00:04:05.000
This hereditary system would last for thousands of years.

00:04:05.000 --> 00:04:07.610
It was in the 16th century BCE

00:04:07.610 --> 00:04:10.370
that the Xia Dynasty finally met its fate.

00:04:10.370 --> 00:04:13.940
The last ruler of Yu the Great's bloodline, Jie

00:04:13.940 --> 00:04:17.270
was said to be a cruel sadistic leader who led a handful

00:04:17.270 --> 00:04:21.530
of military operations solely for revenge and personal gain,

00:04:21.530 --> 00:04:25.040
and filled his free time with sex slaves, drunken orgies

00:04:25.040 --> 00:04:26.690
and senseless violence.

00:04:26.690 --> 00:04:29.510
Perhaps he was too blinded by his hedonism to sense

00:04:29.510 --> 00:04:32.090
what was brewing in the lands he now rule.

00:04:32.090 --> 00:04:35.450
There was a concept in ancient China known as the mandate

00:04:35.450 --> 00:04:38.420
of heaven, a seemingly Shakespearean principle

00:04:38.420 --> 00:04:41.450
that not only states that heaven gives noble men the ruling

00:04:41.450 --> 00:04:42.620
power of China,

00:04:42.620 --> 00:04:46.790
but that any wicked unjust leaders will be removed.

00:04:46.790 --> 00:04:49.340
Heaven had clearly taken issue with Jie.

00:04:49.340 --> 00:04:51.350
China had entered the Bronze Age

00:04:51.350 --> 00:04:55.250
and much to Jie's dismay, a new rebellious power emerged

00:04:55.250 --> 00:04:57.560
with brand new bronze weapons.

00:04:57.560 --> 00:05:00.230
The Xia were promptly overthrown by this group,

00:05:00.230 --> 00:05:03.984
which would be become known as the Shang Dynasty.

00:05:03.984 --> 00:05:06.984
(suspenseful music)

00:05:09.020 --> 00:05:12.110
Not only did they emerge victorious against the corrupt king

00:05:12.110 --> 00:05:13.460
Jie and his men,

00:05:13.460 --> 00:05:16.040
but the Shang Dynasty to this day have something

00:05:16.040 --> 00:05:18.920
that the Xia lack, a written history.

00:05:18.920 --> 00:05:21.800
Oracle bone inscriptions were an ancient form

00:05:21.800 --> 00:05:24.980
of Chinese writing, usually engraved on animal bones

00:05:24.980 --> 00:05:26.270
or turtle shells.

00:05:26.270 --> 00:05:29.870
There are over 3000 documented characters from the era

00:05:29.870 --> 00:05:33.230
of the Shang Dynasty, many of which are either still used

00:05:33.230 --> 00:05:36.020
or similar to modern Chinese characters.

00:05:36.020 --> 00:05:38.480
Considering the Shang Dynasty was in power

00:05:38.480 --> 00:05:40.970
about 3,600 years ago,

00:05:40.970 --> 00:05:43.790
we know an impressive amount about daily life

00:05:43.790 --> 00:05:47.030
and key traditions because of archeological finds

00:05:47.030 --> 00:05:49.010
such as the Oracle bones.

00:05:49.010 --> 00:05:51.170
The Shang Dynasty was quite mobile

00:05:51.170 --> 00:05:53.510
and oftentimes traveled to various islands

00:05:53.510 --> 00:05:55.400
and shores on their conquests.

00:05:55.400 --> 00:05:58.040
Upon each return, they would bring back seashells,

00:05:58.040 --> 00:06:00.860
which were used as currency within their society.

00:06:00.860 --> 00:06:03.650
They employed a futile system that brought great wealth

00:06:03.650 --> 00:06:06.140
to nobility and subjugated peasants

00:06:06.140 --> 00:06:08.510
and farmers to difficult lives.

00:06:08.510 --> 00:06:11.480
The poor possessed little agency, but the military

00:06:11.480 --> 00:06:14.150
and government were far too powerful at the time

00:06:14.150 --> 00:06:16.970
for any peasant resistance to overthrow them.

00:06:16.970 --> 00:06:19.730
The Shang leaders were a highly religious people

00:06:19.730 --> 00:06:23.510
with high priests having heaps of influence over the lands.

00:06:23.510 --> 00:06:25.910
These priests paid much attention to the death

00:06:25.910 --> 00:06:29.300
and dying process as well as subsequent burials

00:06:29.300 --> 00:06:32.690
and established a handful of rituals to preserve their power

00:06:32.690 --> 00:06:35.510
and safety both on earth and in heaven.

00:06:35.510 --> 00:06:39.560
Common practices in the dynasty included sacrificing humans

00:06:39.560 --> 00:06:41.270
for good weather and fortune,

00:06:41.270 --> 00:06:44.330
as well as burying slaves alive with their masters

00:06:44.330 --> 00:06:47.090
to ensure their servitude in the afterlife.

00:06:47.090 --> 00:06:50.930
The Shang Dynasty possessed a mighty military and workforce

00:06:50.930 --> 00:06:52.760
conquering region after region

00:06:52.760 --> 00:06:54.620
and building major walled cities

00:06:54.620 --> 00:06:56.270
across the land as they went.

00:06:56.270 --> 00:06:59.180
It was a restless time with constant battles

00:06:59.180 --> 00:07:02.210
with various tribes as well as internal struggles

00:07:02.210 --> 00:07:05.780
forcing the Shang to move their capital city five times.

00:07:05.780 --> 00:07:08.300
But their skill in molding bronze weapons

00:07:08.300 --> 00:07:12.140
and chariot wheels allowed them to squash opposing forces

00:07:12.140 --> 00:07:15.650
and remain in power for around 600 years.

00:07:15.650 --> 00:07:19.010
In a life that eerily resembled that of Xia ruler Jie,

00:07:19.010 --> 00:07:23.540
the last Shang Emperor DiXin was overcome by temptations

00:07:23.540 --> 00:07:26.090
and began living a life of pure debauchery.

00:07:26.090 --> 00:07:29.120
He hosted massive orgies and inflicted cruel,

00:07:29.120 --> 00:07:31.820
sadistic torture onto those who opposed him.

00:07:31.820 --> 00:07:35.210
A handful of DiXin's family members were jailed for trying

00:07:35.210 --> 00:07:37.340
to intervene in his life of partying,

00:07:37.340 --> 00:07:40.250
and it is said that he had his own uncle's heart ripped out

00:07:40.250 --> 00:07:42.260
of his chest as punishment.

00:07:42.260 --> 00:07:46.460
It was in 1046 BCE when the Zhou of the Wei Valley

00:07:46.460 --> 00:07:49.760
vassals of the Shang challenged the dynasty's reign

00:07:49.760 --> 00:07:51.050
at the Battle of Muye.

00:07:51.050 --> 00:07:54.230
The impoverished Chinese population was strongly in support

00:07:54.230 --> 00:07:56.960
of the Zhou and many slaves being forced to fight

00:07:56.960 --> 00:07:58.940
for the diminishing Shang Dynasty

00:07:58.940 --> 00:08:00.650
defected to fight for the Zhou.

00:08:00.650 --> 00:08:02.270
The members of the Shang army

00:08:02.270 --> 00:08:05.600
who remained loyal were eviscerated in a bloody battle

00:08:05.600 --> 00:08:09.650
that resulted in the deaths of around 50,000 Zhou soldiers

00:08:09.650 --> 00:08:12.200
and hundreds of thousands of the Shang army.

00:08:12.200 --> 00:08:15.920
After such a dismal effort, DiXin fled to his palace,

00:08:15.920 --> 00:08:18.050
surrounded himself with his treasures

00:08:18.050 --> 00:08:21.170
and set the building on fire, killing himself.

00:08:21.170 --> 00:08:23.030
With such a decisive victory,

00:08:23.030 --> 00:08:26.000
the Zhou believed they had inherited the mandate of heaven,

00:08:26.000 --> 00:08:28.220
which would now become a major principle

00:08:28.220 --> 00:08:29.843
of Chinese politics.

00:08:30.717 --> 00:08:33.717
(suspenseful music)

00:08:35.540 --> 00:08:39.020
The Zhou Dynasty was China's longest lasting dynasty

00:08:39.020 --> 00:08:43.300
spanning 789 years from 1046 BCE to 256 BCE.

00:08:45.410 --> 00:08:47.750
The events of those nearly eight centuries

00:08:47.750 --> 00:08:49.610
were some of the most important happenings,

00:08:49.610 --> 00:08:51.710
not only in Chinese history

00:08:51.710 --> 00:08:54.380
but in the development of the world as we know it.

00:08:54.380 --> 00:08:56.270
It was a period distinctly marked

00:08:56.270 --> 00:08:58.910
by both invention and change.

00:08:58.910 --> 00:09:02.780
Large scale irrigation systems transformed agriculture.

00:09:02.780 --> 00:09:04.850
A new network of canals was built

00:09:04.850 --> 00:09:07.850
to transport various goods across previously

00:09:07.850 --> 00:09:10.700
unfathomably long distances.

00:09:10.700 --> 00:09:13.670
Horseback riding became the standard for both travel

00:09:13.670 --> 00:09:15.410
and military use.

00:09:15.410 --> 00:09:17.870
News of silk production spread to Europe

00:09:17.870 --> 00:09:19.970
and the Chinese moved past bronze

00:09:19.970 --> 00:09:21.920
in favor of mastering iron.

00:09:21.920 --> 00:09:23.270
Perhaps the most significant

00:09:23.270 --> 00:09:26.720
of these newfound transitions was that of bronze to iron.

00:09:26.720 --> 00:09:29.030
Europe in the Middle East were hundreds of years

00:09:29.030 --> 00:09:30.110
behind the Zhou,

00:09:30.110 --> 00:09:32.930
who could now cast iron using heat resistant clay

00:09:32.930 --> 00:09:34.640
and furnaces and molds.

00:09:34.640 --> 00:09:37.730
They used the liquified metal to mass produce weapons

00:09:37.730 --> 00:09:41.000
and farming tools propelling both the military

00:09:41.000 --> 00:09:44.960
and general society forward at an unprecedented rate.

00:09:44.960 --> 00:09:47.210
With such a rapidly growing empire,

00:09:47.210 --> 00:09:50.690
however, instability is sure to rear its head.

00:09:50.690 --> 00:09:54.230
The Zhou Dynasty can be split up into two distinct periods,

00:09:54.230 --> 00:09:56.480
the first of which is the Western Zhou.

00:09:56.480 --> 00:09:59.570
During this time, the new found dynasty was operating

00:09:59.570 --> 00:10:03.110
under the futile system, a pyramid-shaped power structure

00:10:03.110 --> 00:10:06.170
where the power and land are concentrated in the royal

00:10:06.170 --> 00:10:10.190
family and are distributed to local lords as is seen fit.

00:10:10.190 --> 00:10:12.140
While this was functional for the Zhou,

00:10:12.140 --> 00:10:13.940
for about two centuries,

00:10:13.940 --> 00:10:16.670
their control instability began to diminish.

00:10:16.670 --> 00:10:19.700
As the futile lords grew increasingly powerful

00:10:19.700 --> 00:10:22.310
and self-serving, they began to revolt

00:10:22.310 --> 00:10:24.530
and raided the capital of Haojing

00:10:24.530 --> 00:10:27.140
and in a move that echoed their previous rulers,

00:10:27.140 --> 00:10:29.120
constant capital movements,

00:10:29.120 --> 00:10:32.450
the Zhou fled to their new capital city, Luoyang.

00:10:32.450 --> 00:10:35.030
In everything but name and technicality,

00:10:35.030 --> 00:10:38.270
the vassal states had essentially taken control of the land

00:10:38.270 --> 00:10:39.680
and its governance.

00:10:39.680 --> 00:10:41.630
This transition marked the beginning

00:10:41.630 --> 00:10:43.640
of the Eastern Zhou period,

00:10:43.640 --> 00:10:47.750
now recognized as having begun in 771 BCE.

00:10:47.750 --> 00:10:51.260
This era yielded perhaps the most significant Chinese

00:10:51.260 --> 00:10:54.260
philosophies of all time in three schools of thought,

00:10:54.260 --> 00:10:57.590
Confucianism, legalism and Taoism.

00:10:57.590 --> 00:11:01.910
Confucius or Master Kong was the most renowned ancient

00:11:01.910 --> 00:11:03.410
Chinese philosopher

00:11:03.410 --> 00:11:06.320
and his school of thought aimed to create a society

00:11:06.320 --> 00:11:08.570
driven by respect, justice,

00:11:08.570 --> 00:11:11.120
and a widespread desire for peace.

00:11:11.120 --> 00:11:14.540
He was born as Kong Qiu in the Zou state of Lu.

00:11:14.540 --> 00:11:18.350
His father Kong He was a commandment of the Lu's garrison,

00:11:18.350 --> 00:11:21.470
but died when Confucius was only three years old,

00:11:21.470 --> 00:11:24.530
leaving his mother to raise the boy alone in poverty.

00:11:24.530 --> 00:11:26.570
He committed his life to education

00:11:26.570 --> 00:11:30.230
and studied classic Chinese works at a school for commoners.

00:11:30.230 --> 00:11:33.740
Now educated in literature, history and music,

00:11:33.740 --> 00:11:36.560
he was married at 19 and raised a family.

00:11:36.560 --> 00:11:40.130
Confucius's mother passed away just a short four years later

00:11:40.130 --> 00:11:41.780
around the age of 40.

00:11:41.780 --> 00:11:44.060
Confucius is said to have mourned her death

00:11:44.060 --> 00:11:45.530
for three years.

00:11:45.530 --> 00:11:48.710
He worked in a variety of low ranking government jobs

00:11:48.710 --> 00:11:51.200
such as bookkeeping, intending to livestock

00:11:51.200 --> 00:11:54.200
just to afford a dignified burial for his mother.

00:11:54.200 --> 00:11:57.080
As he grew older, Confucius had built a considerable

00:11:57.080 --> 00:11:59.840
reputation amongst the local ruling class.

00:11:59.840 --> 00:12:03.170
The state of Lu was ruled by three ducal families

00:12:03.170 --> 00:12:07.100
who appointed Confucius as the minister of criminal matters.

00:12:07.100 --> 00:12:10.130
Confucius believed that there was a natural goodness

00:12:10.130 --> 00:12:13.190
to humanity, and so the core of his philosophy

00:12:13.190 --> 00:12:17.000
was to restore an ethically decrepit China's moral code

00:12:17.000 --> 00:12:18.860
through social relationships.

00:12:18.860 --> 00:12:22.190
After hearing of the wars, orgies, live burials

00:12:22.190 --> 00:12:25.340
and disembowelment practiced by past rulers,

00:12:25.340 --> 00:12:29.000
one can understand why he had grown increasingly discontent

00:12:29.000 --> 00:12:31.040
with the decay of Chinese society.

00:12:31.040 --> 00:12:34.190
He created a hierarchy of being to restore order

00:12:34.190 --> 00:12:36.890
and insisted upon each citizen understanding

00:12:36.890 --> 00:12:39.860
and adopting their respective role in this ladder.

00:12:39.860 --> 00:12:42.590
This system is known as The Five Bonds

00:12:42.590 --> 00:12:45.020
and describes the following relationships needed

00:12:45.020 --> 00:12:46.880
to achieve social harmony.

00:12:46.880 --> 00:12:50.780
Ruler to subject, husband to wife, father to son,

00:12:50.780 --> 00:12:52.640
elder brother to younger brother

00:12:52.640 --> 00:12:54.110
and friend to friend.

00:12:54.110 --> 00:12:57.830
Confucius stress, the importance of respecting one's elders

00:12:57.830 --> 00:13:01.040
and accepting their subjugation as a necessary step

00:13:01.040 --> 00:13:03.200
to maintaining a civil society.

00:13:03.200 --> 00:13:06.290
Family is at the basis of the five bonds

00:13:06.290 --> 00:13:09.830
and its effects are still seen in modern day China.

00:13:09.830 --> 00:13:12.560
The tradition of filial piety means

00:13:12.560 --> 00:13:14.360
that parents are indebted to their children

00:13:14.360 --> 00:13:18.050
in terms of offering care, safety and education,

00:13:18.050 --> 00:13:20.240
and children are indebted to their parents

00:13:20.240 --> 00:13:22.970
in terms of offering services, respect

00:13:22.970 --> 00:13:26.210
and maintaining the family's honor through their actions.

00:13:26.210 --> 00:13:29.060
A family is to uphold their morals as a unit

00:13:29.060 --> 00:13:32.060
and the benevolent family unit will subsequently expand

00:13:32.060 --> 00:13:34.220
to a greater Chinese society.

00:13:34.220 --> 00:13:38.840
As China to Confucius was in essence one massive family.

00:13:38.840 --> 00:13:40.970
His system called for the government to serve

00:13:40.970 --> 00:13:44.540
and take care of its people as parents would their children.

00:13:44.540 --> 00:13:46.970
While Confucius called for social harmony

00:13:46.970 --> 00:13:48.740
through widespread benevolence,

00:13:48.740 --> 00:13:51.440
another school of thought was developing in China

00:13:51.440 --> 00:13:54.950
that directly opposed his teachings, Legalism.

00:13:54.950 --> 00:13:57.380
Unlike Confucianism, legalism states

00:13:57.380 --> 00:14:00.860
that people are inherently bad and require law

00:14:00.860 --> 00:14:02.780
and punishment to be kept in order.

00:14:02.780 --> 00:14:05.463
It was developed from the teachings of Han Feizi,

00:14:05.463 --> 00:14:07.310
a Confucian reformer who believed

00:14:07.310 --> 00:14:10.460
that an ordered society is a strict society

00:14:10.460 --> 00:14:12.890
and a good citizen is one who allows themself

00:14:12.890 --> 00:14:14.180
to be controlled.

00:14:14.180 --> 00:14:16.850
It gained traction rivaling Confucianism

00:14:16.850 --> 00:14:18.470
throughout the Zhou Dynasty.

00:14:18.470 --> 00:14:21.830
The third major philosophy of the Zhou was Taoism,

00:14:21.830 --> 00:14:23.480
which stressed the need for humanity

00:14:23.480 --> 00:14:26.510
to reach a natural harmony with the universe.

00:14:26.510 --> 00:14:29.360
Humans are supposed to follow the universe's will

00:14:29.360 --> 00:14:32.960
and should avoid the tendency to go against its energy.

00:14:32.960 --> 00:14:37.040
The classic yin and yang symbol encapsulates the philosophy

00:14:37.040 --> 00:14:40.280
as one must accept the natural balance in forces

00:14:40.280 --> 00:14:42.710
of the universe to achieve harmony.

00:14:42.710 --> 00:14:44.780
Unlike Confucianism and legalism,

00:14:44.780 --> 00:14:47.840
which called for different moral actions and behaviors

00:14:47.840 --> 00:14:51.950
from the Chinese population, Taoism embraced inaction

00:14:51.950 --> 00:14:54.590
and a philosophy that can aptly be summarized

00:14:54.590 --> 00:14:56.750
as going with the flow.

00:14:56.750 --> 00:14:59.570
These three philosophies are all incredibly

00:14:59.570 --> 00:15:01.640
prevalent throughout Chinese history

00:15:01.640 --> 00:15:03.530
and the contemporary state

00:15:03.530 --> 00:15:05.690
and are the most important contribution

00:15:05.690 --> 00:15:07.490
of the Zhou Dynasty's reign.

00:15:07.490 --> 00:15:08.750
Because of the prominence

00:15:08.750 --> 00:15:11.450
of philosophical development in this time,

00:15:11.450 --> 00:15:14.030
the era and its products are recognized

00:15:14.030 --> 00:15:16.403
as the hundred years of thought.

00:15:17.967 --> 00:15:20.967
(suspenseful music)

00:15:22.520 --> 00:15:24.530
At the same time as these developments

00:15:24.530 --> 00:15:26.780
various states within the Zhou Dynasty

00:15:26.780 --> 00:15:29.300
were beginning to declare their independence.

00:15:29.300 --> 00:15:31.670
Former Dukes calling themselves kings

00:15:31.670 --> 00:15:33.770
and insisted they were politically on par

00:15:33.770 --> 00:15:35.090
with the Zhou King.

00:15:35.090 --> 00:15:38.270
This period is known as the Warring States,

00:15:38.270 --> 00:15:41.390
a time of unrest in which seven former vassal states

00:15:41.390 --> 00:15:44.180
fought for the ultimate reign of China's lands.

00:15:44.180 --> 00:15:48.950
They were the Qin, Han, Yan, Wei, Chu and Qi.

00:15:48.950 --> 00:15:51.170
It was at this time that famed general

00:15:51.170 --> 00:15:54.500
and strategist Sun Tzu wrote the "Art of War,"

00:15:54.500 --> 00:15:58.160
the earliest documented work on military science and war.

00:15:58.160 --> 00:16:01.130
Though the book covered a wide range of military tactics

00:16:01.130 --> 00:16:03.050
and wartime philosophies

00:16:03.050 --> 00:16:05.390
such as when to push your armies forward

00:16:05.390 --> 00:16:08.210
and how to develop strategic flexibility in the face

00:16:08.210 --> 00:16:10.640
of a widely unpredictable war,

00:16:10.640 --> 00:16:12.620
it is no wonder why the "Art of War"

00:16:12.620 --> 00:16:14.420
was birthed in this era.

00:16:14.420 --> 00:16:16.730
War had transformed in China.

00:16:16.730 --> 00:16:19.700
Battles became more sophisticated in the warring states

00:16:19.700 --> 00:16:22.100
period with generals using strategy

00:16:22.100 --> 00:16:24.410
and deceit to gain the upper hand.

00:16:24.410 --> 00:16:26.720
With increased troop numbers and conscriptions

00:16:26.720 --> 00:16:30.050
for males as young as 15 individual battles

00:16:30.050 --> 00:16:33.440
also often dragged on for much longer than a handful of days

00:16:33.440 --> 00:16:36.440
like the clashes of before with some stretching

00:16:36.440 --> 00:16:38.660
as long as months or years.

00:16:38.660 --> 00:16:40.940
The most powerful rising force of the country

00:16:40.940 --> 00:16:43.610
during this time was the Qin.

00:16:43.610 --> 00:16:45.500
They were led by Ying Zheng

00:16:45.500 --> 00:16:48.770
or Qin Shi Huang, which literally translates

00:16:48.770 --> 00:16:51.530
to first emperor of Qin.

00:16:51.530 --> 00:16:53.960
They resided in a dangerous region of China

00:16:53.960 --> 00:16:57.080
where a powerful military was in need for survival

00:16:57.080 --> 00:17:00.320
and thus adopted the use of various weapons technologies

00:17:00.320 --> 00:17:03.680
such as iron swords and crossbows.

00:17:03.680 --> 00:17:06.560
The first of the seven kingdoms to collapse at the hands

00:17:06.560 --> 00:17:08.450
of the Qin was Han.

00:17:08.450 --> 00:17:10.100
They were the weakest of the bunch

00:17:10.100 --> 00:17:12.230
and their territory rested right in the center

00:17:12.230 --> 00:17:14.600
of ancient China, leaving them vulnerable

00:17:14.600 --> 00:17:16.370
to attacks from all sides.

00:17:16.370 --> 00:17:18.560
Though the alliances and mutual interests

00:17:18.560 --> 00:17:20.900
of before protected them in the past,

00:17:20.900 --> 00:17:23.900
the warring states period brought forth an every man

00:17:23.900 --> 00:17:25.550
for himself attitude.

00:17:25.550 --> 00:17:28.790
Ying Zheng and his men swiftly conquered the territory

00:17:28.790 --> 00:17:32.120
and forced King An of Han surrender within a year.

00:17:32.120 --> 00:17:34.310
Though there were far more worthy opponents

00:17:34.310 --> 00:17:36.080
in the near future.

00:17:36.080 --> 00:17:39.140
Ying Zheng's next target was the state of Zhao.

00:17:39.140 --> 00:17:42.020
It was not the first time the two sides had battled.

00:17:42.020 --> 00:17:43.610
Just a couple decades ago,

00:17:43.610 --> 00:17:45.770
they had fought in the Battle of Changping,

00:17:45.770 --> 00:17:48.230
which stands as one of the deadliest battles

00:17:48.230 --> 00:17:49.580
in human history.

00:17:49.580 --> 00:17:53.030
Records estimate 450,000 Zhao deaths

00:17:53.030 --> 00:17:56.210
and 250,000 deaths on the Qin side.

00:17:56.210 --> 00:17:58.730
Because of this decisive Qin victory,

00:17:58.730 --> 00:18:00.470
the Zhao stayed with still weakened

00:18:00.470 --> 00:18:03.350
when Ying Zheng marched his men passed their borders

00:18:03.350 --> 00:18:05.780
to finish what had been started long ago.

00:18:05.780 --> 00:18:08.780
Despite their decaying state, the Zhao possessed something

00:18:08.780 --> 00:18:10.220
that the Qin did not.

00:18:10.220 --> 00:18:12.710
A general by the name of Li Mu.

00:18:12.710 --> 00:18:15.650
Li Mu had an impressive military reputation

00:18:15.650 --> 00:18:18.920
for his previous deceits of massive enemy armies

00:18:18.920 --> 00:18:21.770
and victories in numerous raids and battles.

00:18:21.770 --> 00:18:24.440
When it became clear that the Qin had their sight set

00:18:24.440 --> 00:18:26.300
on conquering the state of Zhao,

00:18:26.300 --> 00:18:29.360
his attention too shifted to the western borders

00:18:29.360 --> 00:18:32.300
to confront the newly ascended Ying Zheng.

00:18:32.300 --> 00:18:35.360
Any progress troops made were immediately trumped

00:18:35.360 --> 00:18:36.980
by Li Mu's tactics

00:18:36.980 --> 00:18:40.010
and it became quite clear to Ying Zheng that so long

00:18:40.010 --> 00:18:43.490
as Li Mu was alive, little progress would be made.

00:18:43.490 --> 00:18:46.310
Failing on the battlefield, he targeted the general

00:18:46.310 --> 00:18:48.530
through tricky political means.

00:18:48.530 --> 00:18:50.930
He bribed figures of the Zhao courts

00:18:50.930 --> 00:18:53.060
and sent spies to create disorder

00:18:53.060 --> 00:18:55.970
within their governmental systems.

00:18:55.970 --> 00:18:58.940
His goal was to create distrust between Youmiu,

00:18:58.940 --> 00:19:01.640
a king of Zhao and General Li Mu.

00:19:01.640 --> 00:19:03.140
He eventually succeeded

00:19:03.140 --> 00:19:05.480
and the king became convinced that Li Mu

00:19:05.480 --> 00:19:06.860
and his trusted associates

00:19:06.860 --> 00:19:09.050
were planning a violent rebellion.

00:19:09.050 --> 00:19:13.160
The general was relieved of his position and executed.

00:19:13.160 --> 00:19:14.750
Zhao was swiftly conquered

00:19:14.750 --> 00:19:16.100
after Li Mu's death.

00:19:16.100 --> 00:19:19.070
As his replacement Zhao Cong was no match

00:19:19.070 --> 00:19:21.050
for the blood thirsty Qin.

00:19:21.050 --> 00:19:25.640
The state's capital Handan was taken over in 228, BCE

00:19:25.640 --> 00:19:27.230
and Ying Zheng saw to it

00:19:27.230 --> 00:19:31.190
that naive King Youmiu was too executed.

00:19:31.190 --> 00:19:33.200
Though there were some self-proclaimed kings

00:19:33.200 --> 00:19:36.230
and kingdoms of Zhao following this major loss,

00:19:36.230 --> 00:19:39.260
the state was no longer a true threat to the Qin.

00:19:39.260 --> 00:19:42.410
Any rebellion or descendant of a king that rose to power

00:19:42.410 --> 00:19:45.650
was squashed over the course of the next handful of years

00:19:45.650 --> 00:19:49.130
until the region as a whole was completely annexed.

00:19:49.130 --> 00:19:52.310
After this success, Ying Zheng then directed his focus

00:19:52.310 --> 00:19:54.050
to the kingdom of Yan,

00:19:54.050 --> 00:19:57.440
well aware of the impending military force at his doorstep,

00:19:57.440 --> 00:20:01.010
the crown prince Dan aimed to defeat the Qin in another way

00:20:01.010 --> 00:20:03.980
by assassinating Ying Zheng himself,

00:20:03.980 --> 00:20:06.380
he picked an assassin named Jing Ke

00:20:06.380 --> 00:20:10.340
to kill Zheng in a suicide mission using a poison dagger

00:20:10.340 --> 00:20:12.710
of the sharpest possible quality.

00:20:12.710 --> 00:20:15.050
The plan was to approach the Qin court

00:20:15.050 --> 00:20:18.890
and pretend to be a traitorous nobleman, begging for mercy.

00:20:18.890 --> 00:20:21.020
He was to offer maps of Dukang,

00:20:21.020 --> 00:20:24.350
the fertile farmland region that Zheng wanted to claim first

00:20:24.350 --> 00:20:26.690
in his conquest as well as the head

00:20:26.690 --> 00:20:29.690
of defective Qin General Huan Yi's head.

00:20:29.690 --> 00:20:32.930
Before sticking the blade deep into Ying Zheng,

00:20:32.930 --> 00:20:35.900
the dagger would be hidden along the side of the maps

00:20:35.900 --> 00:20:39.350
so Jing Ke could strike as soon as he got close.

00:20:39.350 --> 00:20:41.930
Huan Yi, the owner of the aforementioned head

00:20:41.930 --> 00:20:43.820
required for this plan to work,

00:20:43.820 --> 00:20:46.190
had fallen out of the Qin's good graces

00:20:46.190 --> 00:20:48.650
and was seeking revenge for their dismissal,

00:20:48.650 --> 00:20:50.360
causing the Qin to put a bounty

00:20:50.360 --> 00:20:53.150
of 1000 gold pieces on his head.

00:20:53.150 --> 00:20:55.580
After Jing Ke explained the plan,

00:20:55.580 --> 00:20:58.040
the disgrace general agreed to commit suicide

00:20:58.040 --> 00:21:00.020
by cutting his own throat for the sake

00:21:00.020 --> 00:21:01.310
of collecting his head.

00:21:01.310 --> 00:21:03.980
So long as it would mean that Ying Zheng would die

00:21:03.980 --> 00:21:05.870
and the Qin would collapse,

00:21:05.870 --> 00:21:08.630
he cut his own throat without protest.

00:21:08.630 --> 00:21:11.060
With both the head and the maps now ready,

00:21:11.060 --> 00:21:14.990
Jing Ke and his supremely nervous associate Qin Wuyang

00:21:14.990 --> 00:21:17.373
traveled to present their gifts to Ying Zheng.

00:21:17.373 --> 00:21:20.600
Qin Wuyang was so anxious when they reached the palace

00:21:20.600 --> 00:21:23.180
that he entered a near paralyzed state

00:21:23.180 --> 00:21:25.100
and was almost unable to move.

00:21:25.100 --> 00:21:27.650
Jing Ke excused his skittish behavior

00:21:27.650 --> 00:21:29.180
as nothing more than awe

00:21:29.180 --> 00:21:33.110
and cultural shock as Qin Wuyang was, but a rural boy

00:21:33.110 --> 00:21:35.420
who had never truly seen the world.

00:21:35.420 --> 00:21:38.780
Despite Jing Ke's excuses Qin Wuyang was not allowed

00:21:38.780 --> 00:21:41.300
to move up any further and the assassin

00:21:41.300 --> 00:21:44.210
would now have to enter the court by his lonesome.

00:21:44.210 --> 00:21:47.480
Jing Ke calmly approached King Zheng with a map scroll

00:21:47.480 --> 00:21:50.840
and waited for it to be unrolled before grabbing the dagger

00:21:50.840 --> 00:21:52.460
and lunging towards him.

00:21:52.460 --> 00:21:55.010
King Zheng was startled by the sudden movement

00:21:55.010 --> 00:21:58.010
and was able to slip out of his grasp, turning away

00:21:58.010 --> 00:22:00.110
and running away from the attacker.

00:22:00.110 --> 00:22:03.830
Mayhem ensued in the palace with the king narrowly surviving

00:22:03.830 --> 00:22:07.010
by continuously running in circles behind a pillar.

00:22:07.010 --> 00:22:09.860
The armed guards were all but stationed outside

00:22:09.860 --> 00:22:12.200
and his ceremonial sword was too long

00:22:12.200 --> 00:22:13.640
to be pulled out quickly enough

00:22:13.640 --> 00:22:16.130
to defend himself against Jing Ke.

00:22:16.130 --> 00:22:19.100
So all he could do was hope that someone would intervene

00:22:19.100 --> 00:22:21.170
before the assassin closed in.

00:22:21.170 --> 00:22:24.830
Luckily for Ying Zheng, a royal physician stepped forward

00:22:24.830 --> 00:22:27.380
and hurled his medicine bag at Jing Ke,

00:22:27.380 --> 00:22:29.890
slowing him down just long enough for the King

00:22:29.890 --> 00:22:33.980
to unsheath his blade, he stabbed Jing Ke in the leg,

00:22:33.980 --> 00:22:35.420
prompting the injured assassin

00:22:35.420 --> 00:22:38.540
to throw his dagger in a last gasp attempt

00:22:38.540 --> 00:22:39.860
to kill his target,

00:22:39.860 --> 00:22:43.730
he missed and was stabbed eight more times by Ying Zheng.

00:22:43.730 --> 00:22:46.730
In his dying moments, the assassin taunted the king

00:22:46.730 --> 00:22:49.400
with obscene gestures until both he

00:22:49.400 --> 00:22:53.960
and the now fleeing Qin Wuyang were executed by the guards.

00:22:53.960 --> 00:22:56.120
The attempt had failed horribly

00:22:56.120 --> 00:23:00.710
and had only created an angrier, more obsessive Ying Zheng.

00:23:00.710 --> 00:23:04.370
He and his army invaded Yan in 226 BCE

00:23:04.370 --> 00:23:07.790
and quickly conquered the capital, Jicheng.

00:23:07.790 --> 00:23:10.580
In an effort to earn the king of Qin's forgiveness,

00:23:10.580 --> 00:23:14.750
a now desperate King Xi of Yan executed his own son,

00:23:14.750 --> 00:23:17.240
the Crown Prince Dan as an apology

00:23:17.240 --> 00:23:19.190
for the assassination attempt.

00:23:19.190 --> 00:23:21.680
He sent the head of his boy to Ying Zheng,

00:23:21.680 --> 00:23:24.320
which postponed the complete annexation of Yan

00:23:24.320 --> 00:23:26.150
for a small handful of years

00:23:26.150 --> 00:23:29.750
before the Qin returned to destroy them once and for all

00:23:29.750 --> 00:23:32.120
in 222 BCE.

00:23:32.120 --> 00:23:34.400
Ying Zheng began his attacks on the states

00:23:34.400 --> 00:23:37.100
of Wei and Chu at the same time.

00:23:37.100 --> 00:23:39.830
Fearing that one state may take advantage of the fact

00:23:39.830 --> 00:23:42.380
that the Qin were solely focused on the other

00:23:42.380 --> 00:23:44.810
and catch the Qin armies off guard.

00:23:44.810 --> 00:23:47.360
Two of Ying Zheng's most trusted generals,

00:23:47.360 --> 00:23:49.910
a father son duo by the names of Wang Jian

00:23:49.910 --> 00:23:53.720
and Wang Ben launched simultaneous attacks on the two states

00:23:53.720 --> 00:23:55.820
in 225 BCE.

00:23:55.820 --> 00:23:58.520
While Wang Jian began the Qin conquest

00:23:58.520 --> 00:24:02.600
of the incredibly large and powerful Chu his son Wang Ben

00:24:02.600 --> 00:24:05.030
led an army of 600,000 men

00:24:05.030 --> 00:24:08.300
to conquer 10 cities along the northern border of Wei,

00:24:08.300 --> 00:24:10.730
thereby guarding their flank.

00:24:10.730 --> 00:24:13.670
Wei crumbled fairly easily after Wang Ben

00:24:13.670 --> 00:24:16.460
cleverly redirected the waters of the Yellow River

00:24:16.460 --> 00:24:18.946
to flood the capital of Daliang.

00:24:18.946 --> 00:24:22.850
100,000 people, many of which were civilians were killed

00:24:22.850 --> 00:24:25.070
in the flooding, the king surrendered,

00:24:25.070 --> 00:24:28.130
allowing for all the Qin manpower to be focused

00:24:28.130 --> 00:24:29.750
on the powerful Chu.

00:24:29.750 --> 00:24:32.990
Their initial attacks on the Chu had not been particularly

00:24:32.990 --> 00:24:36.980
successful with the Qin army being pushed back and repelled.

00:24:36.980 --> 00:24:39.710
Wang Jian was brought out of retirement two years

00:24:39.710 --> 00:24:41.210
after the initial seizures

00:24:41.210 --> 00:24:44.180
with an army three times larger than before

00:24:44.180 --> 00:24:47.570
and the capital city was taken, the king was captured

00:24:47.570 --> 00:24:50.480
and the state was annexed leaving only one state

00:24:50.480 --> 00:24:51.620
to be captured, Qi.

00:24:51.620 --> 00:24:56.620
In 221 BCE, Ying Zheng's men faced very little pushback

00:24:57.350 --> 00:25:00.500
and conquered the kingdom within the same year.

00:25:00.500 --> 00:25:02.900
When the Qin arrived at the capital city,

00:25:02.900 --> 00:25:06.590
the king of Qi simply surrendered the land without a fight.

00:25:06.590 --> 00:25:09.260
The warring states had all been conquered

00:25:09.260 --> 00:25:11.810
and thus began the Qin Dynasty

00:25:11.810 --> 00:25:14.993
ruled under the iron fist of Ying Zheng.

00:25:16.758 --> 00:25:20.270
(suspenseful music)

00:25:20.270 --> 00:25:21.797
Though they displayed great promise

00:25:21.797 --> 00:25:25.130
and power in the warring states period leading Ying Zheng

00:25:25.130 --> 00:25:27.200
to proclaim that his dynasty would rule

00:25:27.200 --> 00:25:29.630
for 10,000 generations.

00:25:29.630 --> 00:25:33.380
The Qin's dynastic cycle was relatively short lift,

00:25:33.380 --> 00:25:37.847
lasting approximately 15 years from 221 BCE to 206 BCE.

00:25:40.760 --> 00:25:43.970
Despite this, their effects proved to be very important

00:25:43.970 --> 00:25:46.670
and durable across the following centuries.

00:25:46.670 --> 00:25:50.090
The name China comes from Qin.

00:25:50.090 --> 00:25:52.250
In contrast with a feudalist Zhou

00:25:52.250 --> 00:25:54.440
whose decentralization ultimately led

00:25:54.440 --> 00:25:56.150
to the dynasty's downfall.

00:25:56.150 --> 00:25:58.580
The Qin enacted an intense centralization

00:25:58.580 --> 00:26:01.070
and subjugation of the state citizens.

00:26:01.070 --> 00:26:04.700
Ying Zheng's main efforts included registering each citizen

00:26:04.700 --> 00:26:07.340
with a government directing the flow of taxes

00:26:07.340 --> 00:26:09.650
to the state instead of futile lords

00:26:09.650 --> 00:26:12.230
and dividing the land into provinces.

00:26:12.230 --> 00:26:14.570
Each one governed by an appointed official

00:26:14.570 --> 00:26:16.730
acting as an appendage of his ruling.

00:26:16.730 --> 00:26:19.430
He also aimed to standardize currencies,

00:26:19.430 --> 00:26:22.070
writing systems and weights.

00:26:22.070 --> 00:26:24.380
While these changes were primarily for the sake

00:26:24.380 --> 00:26:26.780
of making the population more manageable

00:26:26.780 --> 00:26:29.660
and controllable, they contributed to the creation

00:26:29.660 --> 00:26:32.330
of a culturally homogenous Chinese identity

00:26:32.330 --> 00:26:36.230
that was previously unseen throughout the country's history.

00:26:36.230 --> 00:26:39.050
China had become a united empire

00:26:39.050 --> 00:26:42.500
and Ying Zheng, its first true emperor.

00:26:42.500 --> 00:26:44.900
The Qin were notorious for their cruelty

00:26:44.900 --> 00:26:46.580
and harsh punishments.

00:26:46.580 --> 00:26:49.880
As legalists, they believed people were born evil

00:26:49.880 --> 00:26:52.730
and that the only way to sustain a civilized society

00:26:52.730 --> 00:26:55.760
was to utilize ghastly criminal punishments

00:26:55.760 --> 00:26:58.880
and deter potentially disobedient citizens

00:26:58.880 --> 00:27:00.470
solely through fear.

00:27:00.470 --> 00:27:03.230
Ying Zheng needed everyone in China to understand

00:27:03.230 --> 00:27:06.530
that he and he alone ruled the land.

00:27:06.530 --> 00:27:09.050
Governmental workers and military personnel

00:27:09.050 --> 00:27:11.630
were also subjected to collective punishments

00:27:11.630 --> 00:27:14.870
to holding entire labor groups accountable for their work.

00:27:14.870 --> 00:27:18.230
If one man neglected his duties, it would come at the cost

00:27:18.230 --> 00:27:20.543
of the entire collective's wellbeing.

00:27:21.986 --> 00:27:24.736
(dramatic music)

00:27:25.700 --> 00:27:27.800
The life of a peasant under the Qin

00:27:27.800 --> 00:27:31.730
and an ancient China in general was very taxing.

00:27:31.730 --> 00:27:34.520
Peasants worked long, straining hours typically

00:27:34.520 --> 00:27:38.000
in one of two fields, farming or silk weaving.

00:27:38.000 --> 00:27:40.280
Entertainment was used to relieve the stress

00:27:40.280 --> 00:27:42.020
of long working days.

00:27:42.020 --> 00:27:44.270
Theater and dance were very popular

00:27:44.270 --> 00:27:47.900
and formerly military training games such as Cuju,

00:27:47.900 --> 00:27:51.583
a game similar to Hacky sack were adopted to pass the time.

00:27:51.583 --> 00:27:54.470
The Qin State was a patriarchal society

00:27:54.470 --> 00:27:57.080
and life could be very difficult for women.

00:27:57.080 --> 00:28:00.080
They primarily stayed home to tend to the children and look

00:28:00.080 --> 00:28:02.570
after the household and had little to no say

00:28:02.570 --> 00:28:05.960
in marital issues, land acquisition or sales

00:28:05.960 --> 00:28:08.090
or daily local proceedings.

00:28:08.090 --> 00:28:11.930
Peasants did not particularly like the emperor detesting him

00:28:11.930 --> 00:28:15.611
for his cruel punishments and adoption of legalism.

00:28:15.611 --> 00:28:18.361
(pleasant music)

00:28:19.730 --> 00:28:21.770
It was not just his own population

00:28:21.770 --> 00:28:23.780
that Ying Zheng had to fear.

00:28:23.780 --> 00:28:27.110
Nomadic tribes, particularly the Xiongnu

00:28:27.110 --> 00:28:28.970
who are believed to be the predecessors

00:28:28.970 --> 00:28:31.610
to the Huns continuously terrorized

00:28:31.610 --> 00:28:33.620
the northern Qin borders.

00:28:33.620 --> 00:28:37.010
Armed horsemen would launch fierce intrusions on China's

00:28:37.010 --> 00:28:39.680
outskirts highlighting the Qin's need

00:28:39.680 --> 00:28:41.510
for strengthened borders.

00:28:41.510 --> 00:28:44.210
This led to the most significant construction effort

00:28:44.210 --> 00:28:47.990
of the Qin Dynasty, a Great Wall.

00:28:47.990 --> 00:28:51.200
This wasn't the same Great Wall of China we know today

00:28:51.200 --> 00:28:54.140
though parts of the incredible architectural feat

00:28:54.140 --> 00:28:56.060
are still visible today.

00:28:56.060 --> 00:28:58.640
Sections of the Great Wall had already been built

00:28:58.640 --> 00:29:00.713
tracing back to the fifth century BCE.

00:29:01.610 --> 00:29:03.770
Though Qin Shi Huang was the first to think

00:29:03.770 --> 00:29:06.200
of uniting all of the existing pieces

00:29:06.200 --> 00:29:08.570
to form one Great Wall.

00:29:08.570 --> 00:29:10.160
Peasants who were deemed lazy

00:29:10.160 --> 00:29:11.900
or unproductive in their farming

00:29:11.900 --> 00:29:15.350
or market jobs were oftentimes sent to work on the wall.

00:29:15.350 --> 00:29:18.110
Transporting materials was very difficult,

00:29:18.110 --> 00:29:19.730
so the wall was mainly built out

00:29:19.730 --> 00:29:22.100
of whatever resources were readily available

00:29:22.100 --> 00:29:24.050
in each particular area.

00:29:24.050 --> 00:29:26.150
In mountainous regions, the wall was made

00:29:26.150 --> 00:29:28.670
of mountain stones while rammed earth

00:29:28.670 --> 00:29:30.800
was used in the plains.

00:29:30.800 --> 00:29:32.780
Though the Qin did not view the wall

00:29:32.780 --> 00:29:34.430
as a permanent solution,

00:29:34.430 --> 00:29:37.370
the project would be continued over many successive

00:29:37.370 --> 00:29:40.943
centuries to form the Great Wall we know today.

00:29:42.110 --> 00:29:44.300
Though he had conquered the warring states

00:29:44.300 --> 00:29:46.070
at just the age of 38,

00:29:46.070 --> 00:29:49.010
survived three assassination attempts throughout the course

00:29:49.010 --> 00:29:52.130
of his rule and now fortified the state of Qin.

00:29:52.130 --> 00:29:53.180
There was one enemy,

00:29:53.180 --> 00:29:57.174
Ying Zheng could not defeat, death itself.

00:29:57.174 --> 00:29:59.591
(calm music)

00:30:03.440 --> 00:30:06.560
When Ying Zheng reached middle age, he became obsessed

00:30:06.560 --> 00:30:09.770
with his own mortality and sought out various elixirs

00:30:09.770 --> 00:30:11.870
and potions to extend his life.

00:30:11.870 --> 00:30:14.690
He sent alchemists and explorers on quests

00:30:14.690 --> 00:30:17.240
around the Pacific to find the legendary island

00:30:17.240 --> 00:30:19.850
of Penglai whose mountain supposedly held

00:30:19.850 --> 00:30:21.920
the elixir of immortality.

00:30:21.920 --> 00:30:23.660
Ying Zheng was so desperate

00:30:23.660 --> 00:30:26.630
that he could not understand he was being conned

00:30:26.630 --> 00:30:30.590
primarily by Xu Fu, the leader of these expeditions.

00:30:30.590 --> 00:30:35.090
On the first voyage, Xu Fu was sent with 3000 virgin boys

00:30:35.090 --> 00:30:37.340
and girls and 60 boats,

00:30:37.340 --> 00:30:39.980
but of course returned empty handed

00:30:39.980 --> 00:30:42.050
as the island was mythological.

00:30:42.050 --> 00:30:45.260
Possibly fearing the consequences of a failed mission,

00:30:45.260 --> 00:30:48.140
Xu Fu in the explorers that returned from the voyage claimed

00:30:48.140 --> 00:30:51.980
that their passage was obstructed by a giant sea creature.

00:30:51.980 --> 00:30:55.190
Xu Fu requested a troop of archers for their next effort

00:30:55.190 --> 00:30:59.030
to defeat the creature and move forward with their conquest.

00:30:59.030 --> 00:31:00.980
Ying Zheng obliged and once again

00:31:00.980 --> 00:31:03.260
provided everything he requested.

00:31:03.260 --> 00:31:07.070
Though Xu Fu and his crews never returned from the trip,

00:31:07.070 --> 00:31:09.980
what exactly happened is still unknown today,

00:31:09.980 --> 00:31:12.320
though the most popular theory is that Xu Fu

00:31:12.320 --> 00:31:15.230
simply sailed to Japan and colonized it.

00:31:15.230 --> 00:31:17.960
Growing increasingly paranoid and desperate,

00:31:17.960 --> 00:31:20.240
Ying Zheng began ingesting potions

00:31:20.240 --> 00:31:22.400
his own alchemists had created.

00:31:22.400 --> 00:31:26.030
It is at this time that a series of now famed book burnings

00:31:26.030 --> 00:31:27.980
and live burials took place

00:31:27.980 --> 00:31:30.980
as Ying Zheng had grown utterly mad.

00:31:30.980 --> 00:31:32.870
Wanting to erase all history

00:31:32.870 --> 00:31:36.350
and ideologies he saw as diminishing to his reign

00:31:36.350 --> 00:31:41.350
and the Qin Dynasty Ying Zheng had 460 Confucian scholars

00:31:41.540 --> 00:31:44.570
buried alive and destroyed many of their texts

00:31:44.570 --> 00:31:46.250
and Mass book burnings,

00:31:46.250 --> 00:31:48.620
which were the first documented book burnings

00:31:48.620 --> 00:31:50.000
in human history.

00:31:50.000 --> 00:31:53.630
Soon thereafter, in an ironic twist, Ying Zheng's quest

00:31:53.630 --> 00:31:57.470
for eternal life led to his death at the age of 49.

00:31:57.470 --> 00:31:59.330
The concoctions he was supplied with

00:31:59.330 --> 00:32:02.330
by his alchemist contained high levels of mercury,

00:32:02.330 --> 00:32:04.850
which killed the emperor by poisoning.

00:32:04.850 --> 00:32:06.350
Before the emperor's death,

00:32:06.350 --> 00:32:07.850
he had commanded the construction

00:32:07.850 --> 00:32:10.520
of a grand mausoleum to house his body.

00:32:10.520 --> 00:32:14.570
An underground Acropolis flooded with artifacts, monuments,

00:32:14.570 --> 00:32:17.780
and thousands of clay warriors to follow Ying Zheng

00:32:17.780 --> 00:32:20.870
into the afterlife was accidentally uncovered

00:32:20.870 --> 00:32:24.770
by a group of farmers in 1974 AD.

00:32:24.770 --> 00:32:29.240
The scale and detail of each soldier shocked archeologists.

00:32:29.240 --> 00:32:32.870
No two warriors had the same facial features

00:32:32.870 --> 00:32:35.630
and just like a real army, they were divided

00:32:35.630 --> 00:32:38.360
by military rank in battle formation.

00:32:38.360 --> 00:32:40.730
Each one was equipped with a real weapon

00:32:40.730 --> 00:32:42.680
that had never been used in battle.

00:32:42.680 --> 00:32:45.530
There are clear signs of mass production simply

00:32:45.530 --> 00:32:49.700
to arm the Terracotta warriors with new undamaged weapons.

00:32:49.700 --> 00:32:51.620
Ying Zheng had clearly decided

00:32:51.620 --> 00:32:53.630
that if he could not conquer death,

00:32:53.630 --> 00:32:55.730
he would conquer the afterlife.

00:32:55.730 --> 00:32:57.380
There is still plenty of mystery

00:32:57.380 --> 00:32:59.630
regarding the Terracotta warriors.

00:32:59.630 --> 00:33:02.870
We don't know who exactly built the grand mausoleum

00:33:02.870 --> 00:33:06.500
or why there is no documented history of its construction.

00:33:06.500 --> 00:33:11.120
It is estimated that it took over 700,000 workers to build.

00:33:11.120 --> 00:33:14.630
Because of this enigma and the grand scale of the findings,

00:33:14.630 --> 00:33:17.540
Ying Zheng's Terracotta army is referred to

00:33:17.540 --> 00:33:20.090
as the eighth wonder of the world.

00:33:20.090 --> 00:33:22.880
Following the emperor's passing his associate,

00:33:22.880 --> 00:33:25.580
Li Si kept his death a secret with the hopes

00:33:25.580 --> 00:33:28.760
of snatching power away from Ying Zheng's eldest son

00:33:28.760 --> 00:33:30.890
and successor, Fusu.

00:33:30.890 --> 00:33:34.100
Li Si sought to present him from gaining any more political

00:33:34.100 --> 00:33:35.840
might than he already had.

00:33:35.840 --> 00:33:39.740
As Fusu had ties with a general that rivaled Li Si in court,

00:33:39.740 --> 00:33:41.960
the pair would surely remove him from power

00:33:41.960 --> 00:33:43.430
if they were in control.

00:33:43.430 --> 00:33:46.250
Li Si brought the king's corpse back to the capitol

00:33:46.250 --> 00:33:48.770
and a merchant caravan of rotting fish

00:33:48.770 --> 00:33:50.300
to mask the scent of death.

00:33:50.300 --> 00:33:53.210
He then created a fake document supposedly written

00:33:53.210 --> 00:33:55.820
by Ying Zheng commanding both Fusu

00:33:55.820 --> 00:33:58.370
and the general to commit suicide.

00:33:58.370 --> 00:34:01.250
The plan worked and with both of their targets dead.

00:34:01.250 --> 00:34:03.890
Another son of the emperor took power.

00:34:03.890 --> 00:34:06.980
That son was Qin Er Shi who quickly proved

00:34:06.980 --> 00:34:10.700
to be far less capable than his widely feared father.

00:34:10.700 --> 00:34:13.670
He was incredibly self-indulgent and childish.

00:34:13.670 --> 00:34:17.107
Killing however Li Si would not take power,

00:34:17.107 --> 00:34:20.030
Qin Er Shi would suspect him and others of corruption

00:34:20.030 --> 00:34:20.990
and treason.

00:34:20.990 --> 00:34:23.870
Li Si was sentenced to execution by death

00:34:23.870 --> 00:34:25.460
of a thousand cuts.

00:34:25.460 --> 00:34:28.850
This method of execution involved the condemned person

00:34:28.850 --> 00:34:30.800
being subjected to a series of cuts

00:34:30.800 --> 00:34:33.620
or slices to various parts of their body.

00:34:33.620 --> 00:34:36.440
The intent was not to cause immediate death

00:34:36.440 --> 00:34:38.990
but to prolong the suffering of the condemned.

00:34:38.990 --> 00:34:41.990
Additionally, to top it off, his entire family

00:34:41.990 --> 00:34:44.960
to the third degree was executed.

00:34:44.960 --> 00:34:47.630
Quickly capitalizing on the weakened state

00:34:47.630 --> 00:34:49.520
mass revolts began.

00:34:49.520 --> 00:34:52.460
Liu Bang, a peasant under the Qin Dynasty

00:34:52.460 --> 00:34:54.620
spearheaded a major uprising

00:34:54.620 --> 00:34:56.360
and gained control of the land

00:34:56.360 --> 00:34:59.570
after a fierce clash known as the Battle of Gaixia

00:34:59.570 --> 00:35:02.720
in which over 100,000 men were either killed

00:35:02.720 --> 00:35:04.010
or taken prisoner.

00:35:04.010 --> 00:35:08.352
Thus began the incredibly successful Han Dynasty.

00:35:08.352 --> 00:35:11.352
(suspenseful music)

00:35:14.720 --> 00:35:17.870
With his victory, Liu Bang sees the title of emperor,

00:35:17.870 --> 00:35:21.050
changed his name to Gaozu and established the capital

00:35:21.050 --> 00:35:23.270
of the new state of Han in Changan.

00:35:23.270 --> 00:35:26.570
It is one of the only parts of the destroyed Qin state

00:35:26.570 --> 00:35:30.890
with a surviving palace making for a fairly easy decision.

00:35:30.890 --> 00:35:33.920
Changan is where the Han's namesake comes from

00:35:33.920 --> 00:35:35.375
and the period in which it served

00:35:35.375 --> 00:35:38.630
as the state capital is known as the Western Han,

00:35:38.630 --> 00:35:42.410
lasting from 206 BCE to nine AD.

00:35:42.410 --> 00:35:45.770
Today over 90% of Chinese people identify

00:35:45.770 --> 00:35:50.330
as ethnically Han making up nearly 20% of the world.

00:35:50.330 --> 00:35:52.790
The Han were the world's most populous state

00:35:52.790 --> 00:35:55.400
and were contemporaries of the Roman empire.

00:35:55.400 --> 00:35:59.090
After gaining power, Gaozu cemented Chinese policies

00:35:59.090 --> 00:36:01.490
that would last for thousands of years.

00:36:01.490 --> 00:36:03.350
Coming from peasantry himself,

00:36:03.350 --> 00:36:05.810
he quickly saw to replace many of the rulings

00:36:05.810 --> 00:36:08.600
and precedency saw to be unfair to the commoner.

00:36:08.600 --> 00:36:11.420
Taxes were heavily cut, especially in regions

00:36:11.420 --> 00:36:14.090
who were particularly affected by the wars.

00:36:14.090 --> 00:36:16.250
Many slaves were freed as well.

00:36:16.250 --> 00:36:18.080
Confucianism was brought back

00:36:18.080 --> 00:36:20.840
as the main philosophical school of thought

00:36:20.840 --> 00:36:24.050
and was taught in the state's new Imperial Academy.

00:36:24.050 --> 00:36:28.160
Family loyalty and virtue were once again the main pillars

00:36:28.160 --> 00:36:32.207
of Chinese society, not fear or punishment.

00:36:32.207 --> 00:36:35.360
Gaozu also established the system of civil service

00:36:35.360 --> 00:36:38.330
to prevent lazy and unqualified men from serving

00:36:38.330 --> 00:36:40.700
in important political positions.

00:36:40.700 --> 00:36:42.980
The ruling class was based on merit

00:36:42.980 --> 00:36:46.460
and education rather than familial connections.

00:36:46.460 --> 00:36:49.070
This governmental system would last all the way

00:36:49.070 --> 00:36:54.070
until 1912 AD, nearly 2000 years later.

00:36:54.440 --> 00:36:57.650
Although Gaozu and his Han state had secured power,

00:36:57.650 --> 00:36:59.750
the empire was far from safe.

00:36:59.750 --> 00:37:01.400
The same nomadic Xiongnu

00:37:01.400 --> 00:37:04.070
who threatened the Qin were still a dangerous threat

00:37:04.070 --> 00:37:06.110
and the loyalty of many Han generals

00:37:06.110 --> 00:37:08.210
was questionable at best.

00:37:08.210 --> 00:37:11.210
Following a series of humiliating defeats at the hands

00:37:11.210 --> 00:37:14.120
of the Xiongnu, Gaozu made peace with the tribes

00:37:14.120 --> 00:37:15.590
and agreed to pay tribute.

00:37:15.590 --> 00:37:19.190
Wine and women were gifted to the Xiongnu on an annual basis

00:37:19.190 --> 00:37:20.660
to preserve the peace.

00:37:20.660 --> 00:37:25.550
Gaozu died in 195 BCE, which started a power struggle

00:37:25.550 --> 00:37:26.900
to claim the throne.

00:37:26.900 --> 00:37:30.890
Though Hui, the second son of Gaozu became the next emperor,

00:37:30.890 --> 00:37:33.560
the true ruler of Han was Hui's mother.

00:37:33.560 --> 00:37:36.950
Gaozu's empress consort Empress Lu.

00:37:36.950 --> 00:37:40.250
She had murdered several of his sons to ensure her power

00:37:40.250 --> 00:37:41.960
following Gaozu's death.

00:37:41.960 --> 00:37:43.460
Though her most famous killing

00:37:43.460 --> 00:37:46.823
was that of Gaozu's favorite mistress, Lady Qi.

00:37:47.720 --> 00:37:50.510
Lady Qi also had children with Gaozu

00:37:50.510 --> 00:37:53.630
and Lu did not desire any competition.

00:37:53.630 --> 00:37:56.840
Summa Chin, a historian from the Han Dynasty wrote

00:37:56.840 --> 00:38:00.740
that Empress Lu cut off Lady Qi's hands and feet,

00:38:00.740 --> 00:38:03.500
plucked out her eyes, burned her ears,

00:38:03.500 --> 00:38:06.050
gave her a potion to drink, which made her mute

00:38:06.050 --> 00:38:10.610
and had her thrown into the privy calling her human swine.

00:38:10.610 --> 00:38:12.680
Emperor Hui was so disgusted

00:38:12.680 --> 00:38:15.920
and demoralized by his mother's murderous actions

00:38:15.920 --> 00:38:19.310
that he essentially handed over the ruling power to her.

00:38:19.310 --> 00:38:21.080
He lived a short life of drinking

00:38:21.080 --> 00:38:26.030
and sex until his death in 188 BCE at the age of 22.

00:38:26.030 --> 00:38:27.470
A handful of rulers gained

00:38:27.470 --> 00:38:29.840
and lost power over the following decades,

00:38:29.840 --> 00:38:31.940
maintaining a relatively solid sense

00:38:31.940 --> 00:38:34.940
of peace and prosperity given the ongoing conflict

00:38:34.940 --> 00:38:35.930
with the Xiongnu.

00:38:35.930 --> 00:38:40.490
In 141 BCE, Emperor Wu became the leader of Han

00:38:40.490 --> 00:38:45.490
and would rule for 57 years up until 87 BCE.

00:38:45.590 --> 00:38:47.720
It was also at this time that relations

00:38:47.720 --> 00:38:50.300
with the Xiongnu had reached a boiling point

00:38:50.300 --> 00:38:54.350
and full fledged war began in 133 BCE.

00:38:54.350 --> 00:38:56.870
A handful of Han men were sent West during the war

00:38:56.870 --> 00:38:59.453
to seek out potential allies of the Xiongnu.

00:38:59.453 --> 00:39:02.480
Silk trade in China was being hindered by the tribes

00:39:02.480 --> 00:39:04.940
and the Hans sought alliances with Western peoples

00:39:04.940 --> 00:39:06.230
to fight the Xiongnu.

00:39:06.230 --> 00:39:09.230
What they brought back was knowledge about civilizations,

00:39:09.230 --> 00:39:12.140
trade and the economies of the western world,

00:39:12.140 --> 00:39:14.060
India and the Middle East.

00:39:14.060 --> 00:39:17.060
A trade route called the Silk Road was established,

00:39:17.060 --> 00:39:19.000
which connected all the way from China

00:39:19.000 --> 00:39:20.900
to the Mediterranean Sea.

00:39:20.900 --> 00:39:23.480
The names Silk Road came from the Greek word

00:39:23.480 --> 00:39:28.480
for China, Seres, which translates to the land of silk.

00:39:29.150 --> 00:39:31.370
China would come to rely on the Silk Road

00:39:31.370 --> 00:39:34.700
for trade For more than 1500 years.

00:39:34.700 --> 00:39:38.510
The Silk Road allowed for unprecedented cultural exchange,

00:39:38.510 --> 00:39:41.390
which led to the introduction of Buddhism in China,

00:39:41.390 --> 00:39:44.270
though whether or not Emperor Wu was aware of the religion

00:39:44.270 --> 00:39:47.060
during his time is unknown today.

00:39:47.060 --> 00:39:50.540
The Han territory grew considerably at this time of war

00:39:50.540 --> 00:39:54.530
as they won many major battles against the Xiongnu tribes.

00:39:54.530 --> 00:39:56.840
The dynasty expanded south into regions

00:39:56.840 --> 00:39:59.720
of modern day Vietnam and Myanmar.

00:39:59.720 --> 00:40:01.070
Despite their victories,

00:40:01.070 --> 00:40:03.860
the Han treasury was depleted from all the resources

00:40:03.860 --> 00:40:05.300
poured into the conflict.

00:40:05.300 --> 00:40:07.670
Hundreds of thousands of soldiers died

00:40:07.670 --> 00:40:10.280
while peasants were heavily taxed to fund the war,

00:40:10.280 --> 00:40:14.397
bringing forth a period of rebellion and instability.

00:40:14.397 --> 00:40:16.814
(calm music)

00:40:20.480 --> 00:40:24.110
In the year nine AD, a rising politician by the name

00:40:24.110 --> 00:40:27.560
of Wang Mang capitalized on the shaky state of Han

00:40:27.560 --> 00:40:31.190
and established the very short-lived Xin Dynasty.

00:40:31.190 --> 00:40:33.950
All of the empire's land was seized by Wang Mang

00:40:33.950 --> 00:40:35.990
and redistributed to the peasantry,

00:40:35.990 --> 00:40:38.060
which earned him the historical nickname

00:40:38.060 --> 00:40:40.640
of China's socialist Emperor.

00:40:40.640 --> 00:40:43.160
Policies such as this were not received well

00:40:43.160 --> 00:40:44.900
by the wealthier citizens.

00:40:44.900 --> 00:40:47.000
The empire was left in shambles

00:40:47.000 --> 00:40:49.400
after a series of natural disasters

00:40:49.400 --> 00:40:52.370
and a famine creating yet another period

00:40:52.370 --> 00:40:54.380
of instability and rebellion.

00:40:54.380 --> 00:40:57.260
Just like in the case of the preceding Western Han,

00:40:57.260 --> 00:40:59.240
the Xin Dynasty also failed

00:40:59.240 --> 00:41:02.300
to extinguish the Xiongnu threat at the northern borders

00:41:02.300 --> 00:41:06.380
of China leading to the treasury being depleted once again.

00:41:06.380 --> 00:41:08.660
The people of Xin had had enough.

00:41:08.660 --> 00:41:10.610
There were two major rebellion groups

00:41:10.610 --> 00:41:12.710
that gained prominence at this time.

00:41:12.710 --> 00:41:15.530
The Red Eyebrows and the Lulin.

00:41:15.530 --> 00:41:19.010
The name Red Eyebrows came to be as the rebels painted

00:41:19.010 --> 00:41:21.620
their eyebrows red to distinguish themselves

00:41:21.620 --> 00:41:24.920
from those who supported the government and ruling class.

00:41:24.920 --> 00:41:27.140
The imperial armies were defeated time

00:41:27.140 --> 00:41:29.960
and time again by the various rebel parties

00:41:29.960 --> 00:41:33.830
and Wang Mang was killed in battle in 23 AD.

00:41:33.830 --> 00:41:36.650
Though the Red Eyebrows continuously defied odds

00:41:36.650 --> 00:41:38.210
and showed great promise,

00:41:38.210 --> 00:41:40.910
they collapsed after falling out of the public's favor

00:41:40.910 --> 00:41:42.770
because of their disorganization

00:41:42.770 --> 00:41:45.800
and lack of direction in restoring peace to China,

00:41:45.800 --> 00:41:48.110
they were viewed as a mob like presence

00:41:48.110 --> 00:41:51.020
due to their brutal treatment of local populations

00:41:51.020 --> 00:41:53.513
and desecration of Han graves.

00:41:54.350 --> 00:41:56.300
The Red Eyebrows were trapped in a state

00:41:56.300 --> 00:41:58.880
of constant disarray and frequent deaths

00:41:58.880 --> 00:42:01.640
towards the tail end of their fighting years.

00:42:01.640 --> 00:42:03.140
The Red Eyebrows surrendered

00:42:03.140 --> 00:42:07.310
to Liu Xiu, one of 11 self-proclaimed emperors at the time

00:42:07.310 --> 00:42:10.400
who had been involved with a contemporary Lulin rebellion

00:42:10.400 --> 00:42:11.870
against Wang Mang.

00:42:11.870 --> 00:42:16.160
Liu Xiu or Emperor Guangwu was a very benevolent

00:42:16.160 --> 00:42:17.780
and pardoned the Red Eyebrows

00:42:17.780 --> 00:42:21.110
before beginning his conquest of the entire empire.

00:42:21.110 --> 00:42:23.750
Over the course of a decade, he squashed all

00:42:23.750 --> 00:42:25.820
of the other self-proclaimed emperors

00:42:25.820 --> 00:42:28.658
until he alone claimed the throne.

00:42:28.658 --> 00:42:31.075
(calm music)

00:42:34.970 --> 00:42:38.270
The city of Changan had been destroyed in the rebellions.

00:42:38.270 --> 00:42:42.290
So Guangwu established the new Han capital in Luoyang.

00:42:42.290 --> 00:42:44.870
This period is known as the Eastern Han,

00:42:44.870 --> 00:42:48.410
the latter half of the long withstanding Han Dynasty.

00:42:48.410 --> 00:42:50.840
Under Guangwu taxes were lowered

00:42:50.840 --> 00:42:52.940
and the emperor saw to it that the quality

00:42:52.940 --> 00:42:55.130
of life improved for the peasantry.

00:42:55.130 --> 00:42:58.430
Over 100 academic institutes were established

00:42:58.430 --> 00:43:01.400
using government funds to ensure a well-educated

00:43:01.400 --> 00:43:03.380
future ruling class.

00:43:03.380 --> 00:43:06.200
Guangwu continued to promote Confucianism

00:43:06.200 --> 00:43:09.350
and set up a system in which local governors would nominate

00:43:09.350 --> 00:43:12.890
young men who properly embodied Confucian virtues

00:43:12.890 --> 00:43:14.570
for governmental roles.

00:43:14.570 --> 00:43:16.100
With an excellent basis set

00:43:16.100 --> 00:43:18.350
under the dynasty's first emperor,

00:43:18.350 --> 00:43:21.920
the Eastern Han entered a new golden age over the first

00:43:21.920 --> 00:43:23.510
and second centuries.

00:43:23.510 --> 00:43:25.100
The economy was thriving.

00:43:25.100 --> 00:43:28.700
Educational policies were as thorough as they'd ever been,

00:43:28.700 --> 00:43:31.940
and the military was incredibly powerful.

00:43:31.940 --> 00:43:34.400
CrossBows allowed the Han to kill their enemies

00:43:34.400 --> 00:43:37.460
from a safe distance and durable iron axes

00:43:37.460 --> 00:43:38.900
and swords greatly improved

00:43:38.900 --> 00:43:41.210
their close range combat abilities.

00:43:41.210 --> 00:43:44.300
Resistance in Vietnam and Korea were destroyed,

00:43:44.300 --> 00:43:47.360
and the Xiongnu tribes within the Han borders were defeated

00:43:47.360 --> 00:43:50.270
when they once again turned against the empire.

00:43:50.270 --> 00:43:53.150
The role of the emperor became much less respected

00:43:53.150 --> 00:43:55.670
at this time as the civil servant class

00:43:55.670 --> 00:43:59.180
became the most dominant members of Chinese hierarchies.

00:43:59.180 --> 00:44:01.460
Paper was also invented at this time,

00:44:01.460 --> 00:44:04.400
allowing for their ideas to be shared much easier

00:44:04.400 --> 00:44:05.840
than in days past.

00:44:05.840 --> 00:44:07.370
Emperors were put in place

00:44:07.370 --> 00:44:10.460
and removed as the civil servants saw fit,

00:44:10.460 --> 00:44:12.200
but were usually more concerned

00:44:12.200 --> 00:44:15.380
with their lavish lifestyles than their duties at the helm

00:44:15.380 --> 00:44:17.090
of the empire anyway.

00:44:17.090 --> 00:44:20.750
This absence of centralized leadership led to worse policies

00:44:20.750 --> 00:44:24.590
that erase taxes and allowed for another famine in China,

00:44:24.590 --> 00:44:27.110
and so another powerful resistance group

00:44:27.110 --> 00:44:28.550
rose from the ashes,

00:44:28.550 --> 00:44:32.600
the Yellow Turban Rebellion led by Taoist Zhang Jue

00:44:32.600 --> 00:44:34.640
who claimed that the Han Dynasty was already

00:44:34.640 --> 00:44:35.960
on its last legs.

00:44:35.960 --> 00:44:39.320
The rebels began attacking government offices in pillaging

00:44:39.320 --> 00:44:41.270
villages in 184.

00:44:41.270 --> 00:44:43.610
Though they ultimately failed to bring down the Han,

00:44:43.610 --> 00:44:46.370
the empire was indeed on its way out.

00:44:46.370 --> 00:44:48.350
In order to defeat the Yellow Turbans,

00:44:48.350 --> 00:44:51.320
the bureaucracies forced hand gave significant amounts

00:44:51.320 --> 00:44:53.780
of power back to the nobility who split up

00:44:53.780 --> 00:44:55.730
as individual warlords each

00:44:55.730 --> 00:44:58.658
with their own controlled regions.

00:44:58.658 --> 00:45:01.075
(calm music)

00:45:04.700 --> 00:45:06.800
Another period of warring states began

00:45:06.800 --> 00:45:09.500
until the last emperor of Han was dethroned

00:45:09.500 --> 00:45:12.080
and only three major kingdoms remained.

00:45:12.080 --> 00:45:14.600
Wei, Wu and Shu Han.

00:45:14.600 --> 00:45:18.080
Shu Han the least populated state was the first to go.

00:45:18.080 --> 00:45:20.720
They surrendered the way after exhausting their powers

00:45:20.720 --> 00:45:21.650
fighting Wu.

00:45:21.650 --> 00:45:23.240
Despite their now massive chunk

00:45:23.240 --> 00:45:25.700
of territory the Wei went next.

00:45:25.700 --> 00:45:27.290
They were taken over out of nowhere

00:45:27.290 --> 00:45:30.980
by a powerful clan called Jin, who then defeated Wu

00:45:30.980 --> 00:45:33.950
the last of the three kingdoms in 280.

00:45:33.950 --> 00:45:37.790
This meant that China was reunited and a new dynasty began.

00:45:37.790 --> 00:45:41.390
Emperor Wu of Jin was the first to rule the Jin Dynasty

00:45:41.390 --> 00:45:45.200
and built a legacy of indulgence, waste and sexual prowess.

00:45:45.200 --> 00:45:47.870
He quickly became far more focused on feasting

00:45:47.870 --> 00:45:50.630
and having sex in his harems than fulfilling

00:45:50.630 --> 00:45:52.550
any of his political duties.

00:45:52.550 --> 00:45:55.820
In 281, 5,000 women were brought from the palace

00:45:55.820 --> 00:45:59.780
of conquered Wu Emperor's son Zhao to his own in Luoyang.

00:45:59.780 --> 00:46:01.100
With all the beautiful women,

00:46:01.100 --> 00:46:04.190
now at his disposal, Emperor Wu was overwhelmed

00:46:04.190 --> 00:46:06.500
with a choice and had difficulty deciding

00:46:06.500 --> 00:46:08.240
whom he should have sex with.

00:46:08.240 --> 00:46:10.820
His famous solution to this problem was to ride

00:46:10.820 --> 00:46:12.950
around in a goat drawn cart.

00:46:12.950 --> 00:46:15.080
Wherever the goat stopped, Wu would get out

00:46:15.080 --> 00:46:17.420
and have sex with whichever woman was there.

00:46:17.420 --> 00:46:20.030
Some of the women began leaving bamboo leaves

00:46:20.030 --> 00:46:21.920
and salt outside their bedrooms,

00:46:21.920 --> 00:46:25.370
hoping to lure the goats into stopping at their rooms.

00:46:25.370 --> 00:46:29.420
Wu was utterly sex crazed using this goat drawn method

00:46:29.420 --> 00:46:32.060
nearly every day for eight years.

00:46:32.060 --> 00:46:34.970
He went so far as to criminalize new marriages

00:46:34.970 --> 00:46:37.550
until he was finished picking his concubines

00:46:37.550 --> 00:46:40.820
to ensure he could sleep with any woman he desired.

00:46:40.820 --> 00:46:42.950
When Emperor Wu died in 290,

00:46:42.950 --> 00:46:45.320
the Jin Dynasty got caught up in a civil war

00:46:45.320 --> 00:46:48.860
known as the War of the Eight Princes after his death.

00:46:48.860 --> 00:46:51.110
Numerous factions wanted to gain power,

00:46:51.110 --> 00:46:52.520
now that there was an opening

00:46:52.520 --> 00:46:54.590
and started bringing in nomadic tribes

00:46:54.590 --> 00:46:56.630
such as the Xiongnu to assist them.

00:46:56.630 --> 00:46:58.610
This backfired with the nomadic people

00:46:58.610 --> 00:47:01.640
turning on the Jin Dynasty and claiming the north region

00:47:01.640 --> 00:47:02.660
of the empire.

00:47:02.660 --> 00:47:06.140
The Jin accordingly moved their capital south to Jiankang.

00:47:06.140 --> 00:47:09.530
What ensued was countless changes in ruling families in both

00:47:09.530 --> 00:47:13.130
the barbarian run north as well as the Jin south.

00:47:13.130 --> 00:47:15.500
Both regions were incredibly unstable

00:47:15.500 --> 00:47:18.980
until the Sui Dynasty was erected in 581

00:47:18.980 --> 00:47:22.901
and unified the Empire once again in 589.

00:47:22.901 --> 00:47:25.484
(gentle music)

00:47:29.210 --> 00:47:31.820
While the Sui Dynasty was very short-lived,

00:47:31.820 --> 00:47:34.010
they acted as a very important turning point

00:47:34.010 --> 00:47:35.240
in Chinese history.

00:47:35.240 --> 00:47:38.330
They reinstated the rule of China's ethnic Han

00:47:38.330 --> 00:47:41.330
and began efforts to culturally assimilate the barbarians

00:47:41.330 --> 00:47:42.980
that had migrated into China.

00:47:42.980 --> 00:47:45.800
Confucianism and Buddhism were heavily fostered

00:47:45.800 --> 00:47:46.633
at this time.

00:47:46.633 --> 00:47:49.280
As the Emperor Wen of Sui had been raised

00:47:49.280 --> 00:47:51.170
and taught by a Buddhist nun.

00:47:51.170 --> 00:47:54.320
It was a difficult time to be in power, north of the Sui,

00:47:54.320 --> 00:47:57.470
in the central steps, the Turks were rising to power

00:47:57.470 --> 00:47:59.420
and becoming a formidable force,

00:47:59.420 --> 00:48:02.180
which made expansion difficult for the dynasty.

00:48:02.180 --> 00:48:05.120
While the empire was relatively stable for a short period

00:48:05.120 --> 00:48:08.060
of time, it began to deteriorate very fast

00:48:08.060 --> 00:48:10.580
because of the evil Emperor Yang Guang's

00:48:10.580 --> 00:48:12.770
constant misuse of resources.

00:48:12.770 --> 00:48:16.310
Yang Guang was obsessed with construction projects and war.

00:48:16.310 --> 00:48:19.370
Many peasants worked to death rebuilding the Great Wall,

00:48:19.370 --> 00:48:21.110
and he sent millions of soldiers

00:48:21.110 --> 00:48:24.080
to die in his attempted conquest of Goguryeo,

00:48:24.080 --> 00:48:25.880
which is modern day Korea.

00:48:25.880 --> 00:48:28.940
The last attack on Goguryeo had been an utterly pathetic

00:48:28.940 --> 00:48:31.940
failure, resulting in a 90% casualty rate

00:48:31.940 --> 00:48:34.790
for the Sui troops and a relatively tiny one

00:48:34.790 --> 00:48:35.930
for the Goguryeo.

00:48:35.930 --> 00:48:37.880
This all spurred more rebellions

00:48:37.880 --> 00:48:39.560
as the peasantry was fed up.

00:48:39.560 --> 00:48:42.770
A father and son duo became the two most important figures

00:48:42.770 --> 00:48:45.260
in China during this time of resistance.

00:48:45.260 --> 00:48:48.470
The Father Li Yuan had been born in 566

00:48:48.470 --> 00:48:50.660
in the Three Kingdoms period.

00:48:50.660 --> 00:48:52.940
Li Yuan had many familial connections

00:48:52.940 --> 00:48:56.090
to the throne with many family members close to the emperor,

00:48:56.090 --> 00:48:59.180
though that did not exactly make things easier for him.

00:48:59.180 --> 00:49:02.840
Emperor Yang Guang was evil, tyrannical and brutal

00:49:02.840 --> 00:49:04.970
and offered little help to Li Yuan.

00:49:04.970 --> 00:49:08.420
His son, Li Shimin was a very bold military leader

00:49:08.420 --> 00:49:10.340
who successfully fought against the Turks

00:49:10.340 --> 00:49:11.960
on multiple occasions.

00:49:11.960 --> 00:49:13.640
He famously tricked his opponents

00:49:13.640 --> 00:49:15.680
by bringing in excessive amount of flags

00:49:15.680 --> 00:49:18.320
and drums to the battlefield to make them retreat,

00:49:18.320 --> 00:49:20.900
thinking that the Sui army was much larger

00:49:20.900 --> 00:49:22.370
than it actually was.

00:49:22.370 --> 00:49:25.520
Though both Li Yuan and Li Shimin were initially loyal

00:49:25.520 --> 00:49:28.010
to the Sui Dynasty throughout this time of war,

00:49:28.010 --> 00:49:30.560
it became increasingly clear to both of them

00:49:30.560 --> 00:49:32.630
that the empire was in decline.

00:49:32.630 --> 00:49:34.880
Li Yuan was very sacred and timid

00:49:34.880 --> 00:49:36.740
and did not wish to turn on their leaders

00:49:36.740 --> 00:49:38.630
considering the number of family members

00:49:38.630 --> 00:49:40.070
that were close to the throne.

00:49:40.070 --> 00:49:43.970
If Yang Guang caught wind of rebellion, Li Yuan's family,

00:49:43.970 --> 00:49:48.020
including his daughter, Pingyang, would surely be executed.

00:49:48.020 --> 00:49:50.720
Li Shimin, however convinced him to join a band

00:49:50.720 --> 00:49:54.620
of rebels since death was already on his doorstep anyways.

00:49:54.620 --> 00:49:57.650
Yang Guang had begun killing his own generals

00:49:57.650 --> 00:49:59.270
who were not doing a good enough job

00:49:59.270 --> 00:50:00.650
of defeating the rebels,

00:50:00.650 --> 00:50:03.680
and Li Yuan was up next on the chopping block.

00:50:03.680 --> 00:50:07.160
With a little left to lose, it was now or never,

00:50:07.160 --> 00:50:09.800
or else it would be Li Yuan's head.

00:50:09.800 --> 00:50:12.530
He spread rumors that the emperor was planning another

00:50:12.530 --> 00:50:16.700
invasion of Goguryeo that would require even more soldiers.

00:50:16.700 --> 00:50:19.820
Still fiercely angry about the last invasions,

00:50:19.820 --> 00:50:21.710
the peasants hit a breaking point.

00:50:21.710 --> 00:50:23.300
They did not want to die fighting

00:50:23.300 --> 00:50:25.730
for a clearly inferior army in a war

00:50:25.730 --> 00:50:27.500
that would not benefit them.

00:50:27.500 --> 00:50:30.680
This allowed Li Yuan and Li Shimin to garner more support

00:50:30.680 --> 00:50:33.350
for their rebellion and recruit soldiers.

00:50:33.350 --> 00:50:36.380
After Li Yuan ensured the safety of his family members

00:50:36.380 --> 00:50:39.320
through replaying secret messages, encouraging them

00:50:39.320 --> 00:50:40.760
to get away from the capitol,

00:50:40.760 --> 00:50:44.090
the campaign to take the capitol of Changan began.

00:50:44.090 --> 00:50:46.700
There were many doubts about the future of the rebels

00:50:46.700 --> 00:50:49.010
as there were many other rebel groups as well

00:50:49.010 --> 00:50:51.800
as the Turks in the north vying for power.

00:50:51.800 --> 00:50:54.920
Li Yuan was very weak-minded and afraid.

00:50:54.920 --> 00:50:58.490
Though Li Shimin was successful once again in encouraging

00:50:58.490 --> 00:51:02.210
him to saddle up and fight the Turks and other rebel groups.

00:51:02.210 --> 00:51:04.700
The Army grew significantly in size

00:51:04.700 --> 00:51:06.800
and the Li family was reunited.

00:51:06.800 --> 00:51:09.710
Surprisingly, Pingyang had formed a rebellion group

00:51:09.710 --> 00:51:13.010
of her own, which was 70,000 strong.

00:51:13.010 --> 00:51:15.260
The Capitol was taken in a major attack

00:51:15.260 --> 00:51:18.920
with all their forces and Li Yuan snatched power away

00:51:18.920 --> 00:51:21.590
from Emperor Yang Guang's grandson.

00:51:21.590 --> 00:51:24.800
The emperor himself was many miles away at this time

00:51:24.800 --> 00:51:26.090
in Eastern China,

00:51:26.090 --> 00:51:29.210
but could not escape his long overdue fate.

00:51:29.210 --> 00:51:31.550
His own officials murdered him,

00:51:31.550 --> 00:51:34.760
and the Sui Dynasty was without a doubt, over.

00:51:34.760 --> 00:51:38.780
While the Sui rule was indeed very brief ending in 618,

00:51:38.780 --> 00:51:42.500
father and son Li Yuan and Li Shimin had set the stage

00:51:42.500 --> 00:51:45.353
for a new golden age of Chinese history.

00:51:47.310 --> 00:51:49.893
(gentle music)

00:51:53.929 --> 00:51:56.540
The Tang Dynasty is viewed as one of the best eras

00:51:56.540 --> 00:51:57.980
of Chinese history.

00:51:57.980 --> 00:51:59.480
The empire was stable.

00:51:59.480 --> 00:52:02.750
The population grew from 50 to 80 million people

00:52:02.750 --> 00:52:03.980
and many scientific

00:52:03.980 --> 00:52:07.010
and cultural advancements ballooned during this time.

00:52:07.010 --> 00:52:10.490
The rain is viewed so favorably that all these years later,

00:52:10.490 --> 00:52:12.080
ethnic Chinese people refer

00:52:12.080 --> 00:52:14.840
to the neighborhoods in Western metropolitan areas,

00:52:14.840 --> 00:52:18.920
commonly known as Chinatown, as Tang Ren Jie,

00:52:18.920 --> 00:52:21.800
which translates to the Tang people street.

00:52:21.800 --> 00:52:25.190
However, such good fortune did not come easy early on.

00:52:25.190 --> 00:52:27.920
While Li Yuan and his family had defeated the Sui,

00:52:27.920 --> 00:52:29.900
there still remained a great many threats

00:52:29.900 --> 00:52:31.220
to his future reign.

00:52:31.220 --> 00:52:34.190
Two dynasties were established to the east of the Tang

00:52:34.190 --> 00:52:36.800
and the Turks were still the major threat in the north.

00:52:36.800 --> 00:52:40.280
Capitalizing on all the chaos of war that comes with rising

00:52:40.280 --> 00:52:41.750
and falling dynasties,

00:52:41.750 --> 00:52:45.140
the Turks had been slowly creeping into mainland China.

00:52:45.140 --> 00:52:49.130
Li Yuan declared himself the Tang Dynasty's first emperor

00:52:49.130 --> 00:52:52.460
and Li Shimin was given the role of Prime Minister,

00:52:52.460 --> 00:52:55.340
the eldest of Li Yuan sons, Li Jiancheng,

00:52:55.340 --> 00:52:56.600
who had helped in the rebellion

00:52:56.600 --> 00:52:59.420
as a key general was named Crown Prince

00:52:59.420 --> 00:53:00.770
and the heir apparent,

00:53:00.770 --> 00:53:03.440
even though he did not have the same glorious military

00:53:03.440 --> 00:53:05.660
reputation that Li Shimin did.

00:53:05.660 --> 00:53:08.210
This made Li Jiancheng feel uneasy

00:53:08.210 --> 00:53:11.030
and overshadowed in his role as Crown Prince.

00:53:11.030 --> 00:53:14.870
An intense rivalry began between the two brothers,

00:53:14.870 --> 00:53:18.020
Li Jiancheng, and another brother Li Yuanji

00:53:18.020 --> 00:53:19.820
began preparing a private army

00:53:19.820 --> 00:53:23.000
to stage a coup and assassinate Li Shimin.

00:53:23.000 --> 00:53:25.130
Yuanji supported Li Jiancheng

00:53:25.130 --> 00:53:26.690
as he wanted to be crown prince.

00:53:26.690 --> 00:53:29.120
Once Li Jiancheng became emperor,

00:53:29.120 --> 00:53:32.720
unfortunately for the pair, word got out fairly quickly.

00:53:32.720 --> 00:53:35.270
Li Shimin received word from his soldiers

00:53:35.270 --> 00:53:37.820
and Li Jiancheng's plan was foil.

00:53:37.820 --> 00:53:40.100
He was put under house arrest by his father.

00:53:40.100 --> 00:53:43.430
Prompting an associate of Li Jiancheng to formally rebel.

00:53:43.430 --> 00:53:45.227
Li Shimin was commanded to go out

00:53:45.227 --> 00:53:47.090
and kill the rebel leader

00:53:47.090 --> 00:53:49.520
and was promised the title of Crown Prince

00:53:49.520 --> 00:53:51.560
upon his return to Changan.

00:53:51.560 --> 00:53:54.020
It didn't take much of an effort on Li Shimin's part

00:53:54.020 --> 00:53:56.270
to kill Li Jiancheng's associate.

00:53:56.270 --> 00:53:58.640
His own band of rebels killed him at the site

00:53:58.640 --> 00:54:00.050
of the Imperial army.

00:54:00.050 --> 00:54:03.290
Meanwhile, the weak willed Li Yuan was caving in

00:54:03.290 --> 00:54:05.690
and easing up on his son back in the capitol.

00:54:05.690 --> 00:54:09.230
Li Jiancheng was very close with his father's concubines

00:54:09.230 --> 00:54:10.670
who would often do his bidding

00:54:10.670 --> 00:54:12.710
and try to rehabilitate his image.

00:54:12.710 --> 00:54:14.480
At Li Jiancheng's request,

00:54:14.480 --> 00:54:16.730
the women successfully convinced the emperor

00:54:16.730 --> 00:54:19.940
to go easy on his son, likely stressing the importance

00:54:19.940 --> 00:54:22.250
of family in such trying times.

00:54:22.250 --> 00:54:24.860
When Li Shimin returned, he was shocked to learn

00:54:24.860 --> 00:54:27.170
that Li Jiancheng would be keeping his title

00:54:27.170 --> 00:54:29.870
of Crown Prince, but there was little time

00:54:29.870 --> 00:54:32.870
to process his father's ridiculous leniency

00:54:32.870 --> 00:54:35.120
and the forgiveness of his young brother.

00:54:35.120 --> 00:54:38.240
The Turks had moved just outside of Changan.

00:54:38.240 --> 00:54:41.150
Li Shimin had taken charge and organized a treaty

00:54:41.150 --> 00:54:44.300
involving regular payments to the imposing forces

00:54:44.300 --> 00:54:47.780
just two years prior in 622 AD.

00:54:47.780 --> 00:54:49.460
Though the threat was becoming more

00:54:49.460 --> 00:54:52.120
and more dangerous as they pushed closer to the capitol,

00:54:52.120 --> 00:54:55.580
Li Shimin approached the Khagan, the leader of the Turks

00:54:55.580 --> 00:54:56.900
outside of the city

00:54:56.900 --> 00:54:59.420
and declared that if they had become dissatisfied

00:54:59.420 --> 00:55:01.040
with their previous agreement,

00:55:01.040 --> 00:55:03.710
then he and the Khagan should dual to the death.

00:55:03.710 --> 00:55:06.650
The Khagan was uncertain of what tricks Li Shimin

00:55:06.650 --> 00:55:10.190
had up his sleeve and withdrew his back to their camp.

00:55:10.190 --> 00:55:13.730
Li Shimin and his army remained incredibly close by

00:55:13.730 --> 00:55:16.430
and after a night of rainfall sent a message

00:55:16.430 --> 00:55:19.520
detailing the Tang Army's advantageous position,

00:55:19.520 --> 00:55:22.040
as well as his analysis of how the Turks bows

00:55:22.040 --> 00:55:24.167
would likely be deteriorated by now.

00:55:24.167 --> 00:55:26.000
The people of the Eurasian steps

00:55:26.000 --> 00:55:29.510
used composite bows made of wood and animal horns,

00:55:29.510 --> 00:55:32.510
which did not fare well during rainy seasons.

00:55:32.510 --> 00:55:34.640
Outsmarted by the witty Li Shimin,

00:55:34.640 --> 00:55:36.230
the Khagan agreed once again

00:55:36.230 --> 00:55:38.330
to the Tang's proposed peace treaty

00:55:38.330 --> 00:55:42.080
and retreated without a drop of bloodshed on either side.

00:55:42.080 --> 00:55:45.110
Upon Li Shimin's return, it was all the more clear

00:55:45.110 --> 00:55:48.230
that he would be the next great leader of the Tang Dynasty.

00:55:48.230 --> 00:55:51.020
This made Li Jiancheng all the more desperate

00:55:51.020 --> 00:55:53.750
to kill his brother and secure power.

00:55:53.750 --> 00:55:56.210
Li Jiancheng hosted a banquet in his residence

00:55:56.210 --> 00:55:59.270
for his brothers Li Shimin and Li Yuanji.

00:55:59.270 --> 00:56:01.610
He had poisoned Li Shimin's wine.

00:56:01.610 --> 00:56:04.280
Li Shimin was in such a horrible state that he needed

00:56:04.280 --> 00:56:07.100
to be carried home and barely survived the ordeal

00:56:07.100 --> 00:56:09.200
after vomiting blood all night.

00:56:09.200 --> 00:56:12.740
Li Yuan couldn't bear to witness the rivalry of his sons

00:56:12.740 --> 00:56:14.090
and informed Li Shimin

00:56:14.090 --> 00:56:16.850
that he would be dividing the empire into two halves

00:56:16.850 --> 00:56:18.830
to avoid further conflict.

00:56:18.830 --> 00:56:21.860
Li Shimin was promised the rule of the Eastern half,

00:56:21.860 --> 00:56:24.380
which he protested, but it was no use.

00:56:24.380 --> 00:56:27.050
His stubborn father had already made up his mind

00:56:27.050 --> 00:56:29.510
that a vision failed to quell the rivalry.

00:56:29.510 --> 00:56:32.060
In the West Li Jiancheng and Li Yuanji

00:56:32.060 --> 00:56:34.570
continued plotting the murder of Li Shimin.

00:56:34.570 --> 00:56:37.610
In the East, Li Shimin was continuously encouraged

00:56:37.610 --> 00:56:40.880
by his cabinet to strike first and kill his brothers.

00:56:40.880 --> 00:56:43.460
Though despite everything, he was still hesitant

00:56:43.460 --> 00:56:45.500
to plot an attack on his own family.

00:56:45.500 --> 00:56:49.160
When the Turks attacked once again in the summer of 626,

00:56:49.160 --> 00:56:52.250
the two conniving brothers saw the disorder as a chance

00:56:52.250 --> 00:56:54.680
to kill Li Shimin once and for all.

00:56:54.680 --> 00:56:58.190
Backed by Li Jiancheng, Li Yuanji approached his father

00:56:58.190 --> 00:57:01.190
and asked to command the army against the invading Turks.

00:57:01.190 --> 00:57:03.200
Though the emperor was a bit hesitant

00:57:03.200 --> 00:57:06.440
as he initially intended on sending the decorated Li Shimin

00:57:06.440 --> 00:57:08.420
to resist them, he agreed.

00:57:08.420 --> 00:57:12.050
Much to Li Jiancheng's delight, Li Yuanji was able to turn

00:57:12.050 --> 00:57:14.750
many of Li Shimin's associates against him

00:57:14.750 --> 00:57:16.520
while organizing his army.

00:57:16.520 --> 00:57:18.680
Those who had one sided with Li Shimin

00:57:18.680 --> 00:57:21.620
and encouraged him to attack his brothers had given up

00:57:21.620 --> 00:57:24.110
on trying to convince him and were now looking

00:57:24.110 --> 00:57:26.240
after their own lives instead.

00:57:26.240 --> 00:57:28.610
Because of this victory, the eldest brother

00:57:28.610 --> 00:57:31.310
promised Li Yuanji the title of Crown Prince

00:57:31.310 --> 00:57:32.810
once he became emperor,

00:57:32.810 --> 00:57:35.930
which would be any day now should their plan work.

00:57:35.930 --> 00:57:38.600
The pair decided that after they killed Li Shimin,

00:57:38.600 --> 00:57:41.420
they would finally gain power by forcing their father

00:57:41.420 --> 00:57:43.460
to give up the throne.

00:57:43.460 --> 00:57:45.800
Shortly after, however, Li Jiancheng

00:57:45.800 --> 00:57:48.410
and Li Yuanji were summoned to their father's court.

00:57:48.410 --> 00:57:51.230
Li Shimin had submitted a message to his father claiming

00:57:51.230 --> 00:57:54.620
that both Li Jiancheng and Li Yuanji had been sleeping

00:57:54.620 --> 00:57:57.260
with many of the emperor's concubines.

00:57:57.260 --> 00:57:59.540
When the two brothers conferred on what to do,

00:57:59.540 --> 00:58:03.260
Li Yuanji argued that they should fake illnesses and not go,

00:58:03.260 --> 00:58:05.120
but Li Jiancheng pulled rank

00:58:05.120 --> 00:58:07.190
and decided that they should both go to try

00:58:07.190 --> 00:58:10.340
and smooth out the situation to the best of their abilities.

00:58:10.340 --> 00:58:12.380
What ensued is what is now known

00:58:12.380 --> 00:58:14.660
as the Shen Wu Gate incident.

00:58:14.660 --> 00:58:16.730
Upon their arrival at the Shen Wu Gate,

00:58:16.730 --> 00:58:19.910
which served as an entrance to the Palace City in Changan,

00:58:19.910 --> 00:58:22.160
they began to feel like something was wrong.

00:58:22.160 --> 00:58:24.890
They realized they were walking into a coup d'état

00:58:24.890 --> 00:58:26.810
and immediately tried to retreat,

00:58:26.810 --> 00:58:28.960
but by then it was far too late.

00:58:28.960 --> 00:58:31.850
Li Shimin bound through the gates on horseback

00:58:31.850 --> 00:58:34.640
and called them over, which prompted Li Yuanji

00:58:34.640 --> 00:58:37.400
to draw his bow, but he was far too slow

00:58:37.400 --> 00:58:39.140
compared to the quick Li Shimin.

00:58:39.140 --> 00:58:41.450
Li Shimin quickly drew his own weapon

00:58:41.450 --> 00:58:44.450
and fired an arrow straight into Li Jiancheng,

00:58:44.450 --> 00:58:48.080
killing him instantly, a chase ensued with Li Yuanji

00:58:48.080 --> 00:58:49.370
trying to escape the scene

00:58:49.370 --> 00:58:51.710
before Li Shimin could kill him too.

00:58:51.710 --> 00:58:55.340
In the chaos, however, Li Shimin's horse became overwhelmed

00:58:55.340 --> 00:58:57.830
throwing the middle brother off its back.

00:58:57.830 --> 00:59:00.050
Li Yuanji pounced on this opportunity

00:59:00.050 --> 00:59:02.840
and tried to strangle the fallen Li Shimin to death

00:59:02.840 --> 00:59:04.340
with his own bow string.

00:59:04.340 --> 00:59:07.700
Just in the nick of time, Yuchi Jingde, an associate

00:59:07.700 --> 00:59:10.810
of Li Shimin arrived and shouted at Li Yuanji.

00:59:10.810 --> 00:59:13.100
Li Yuanji tried to flee on foot

00:59:13.100 --> 00:59:15.980
but was promptly killed by Yuchi's arrows.

00:59:15.980 --> 00:59:18.800
Overwhelmed by the situation Li Yuan agreed

00:59:18.800 --> 00:59:20.210
that power would be handed over

00:59:20.210 --> 00:59:22.670
to the surviving son, Li Shimin

00:59:22.670 --> 00:59:25.670
and that the opposing forces should submit to his rule.

00:59:25.670 --> 00:59:28.117
The male heirs of both Li Jiancheng

00:59:28.117 --> 00:59:30.770
and Li Yuanji were promptly executed To prevent

00:59:30.770 --> 00:59:32.840
further destabilization.

00:59:32.840 --> 00:59:35.570
The two power hungry brothers had started a battle

00:59:35.570 --> 00:59:37.280
that they could not finish

00:59:37.280 --> 00:59:40.820
and it ultimately came at the cost of their family's lives.

00:59:40.820 --> 00:59:43.730
Li Yuan retired to a more ceremonious role

00:59:43.730 --> 00:59:46.190
while Li Shimin was declared emperor.

00:59:46.190 --> 00:59:48.890
Though there was little time to celebrate his new role,

00:59:48.890 --> 00:59:50.990
the Turks had not stopped their advances

00:59:50.990 --> 00:59:54.380
to allow the House of Li to play out their family dramas.

00:59:54.380 --> 00:59:56.206
They had already reached the edges of Changan.

00:59:56.206 --> 01:00:01.206
Li Shimin opted for a nonviolent confrontation once again

01:00:01.310 --> 01:00:03.980
as he thought that Khagan's selfish and cruel treatment

01:00:03.980 --> 01:00:06.140
of his inferiors would eventually break apart

01:00:06.140 --> 01:00:09.380
the Turkic Khaganate and provide an easier opportunity

01:00:09.380 --> 01:00:11.510
to attack sometime in the future.

01:00:11.510 --> 01:00:13.760
The Tang Dynasty was too vulnerable

01:00:13.760 --> 01:00:15.710
to face them head on right now,

01:00:15.710 --> 01:00:18.920
so Li Shimin simply renegotiated their peace treaty

01:00:18.920 --> 01:00:21.260
and agreed to pay tribute for the time being.

01:00:21.260 --> 01:00:24.380
In the meantime, the new emperor focused on building a basis

01:00:24.380 --> 01:00:26.900
of trust and free speech within his cabinet.

01:00:26.900 --> 01:00:29.930
He picked members based on their talent and intellect

01:00:29.930 --> 01:00:32.510
and even allowed those who had served as advisors

01:00:32.510 --> 01:00:34.130
to his treacherous brothers

01:00:34.130 --> 01:00:35.990
to join his ranks if he thought it was

01:00:35.990 --> 01:00:37.790
what was best for the empire.

01:00:37.790 --> 01:00:41.210
Li Shimin encouraged his officials to speak honestly

01:00:41.210 --> 01:00:42.800
and critique his rule,

01:00:42.800 --> 01:00:45.560
and so together they worked on improving the domestic

01:00:45.560 --> 01:00:48.740
conditions of the Empire before launching any attack

01:00:48.740 --> 01:00:49.700
on the Turks.

01:00:49.700 --> 01:00:53.510
China entered a very prosperous age with Li Shimin,

01:00:53.510 --> 01:00:56.420
now known as Emperor Taizong of Tang

01:00:56.420 --> 01:00:58.163
at the helm of the empire.

01:00:59.630 --> 01:01:02.780
He is recognized today as the absolute greatest

01:01:02.780 --> 01:01:04.580
of the hundreds of emperors who came

01:01:04.580 --> 01:01:06.770
and went throughout Chinese history

01:01:06.770 --> 01:01:09.650
and an argument could be made that China was the wealthiest

01:01:09.650 --> 01:01:11.870
and most powerful state in the world

01:01:11.870 --> 01:01:13.940
during this second golden age,

01:01:13.940 --> 01:01:16.790
but why exactly was that the case?

01:01:16.790 --> 01:01:19.760
Relations between the Turks and the Tang remained stable

01:01:19.760 --> 01:01:22.430
as Emperor Taizong worked on the living conditions

01:01:22.430 --> 01:01:23.600
of his subjects,

01:01:23.600 --> 01:01:26.780
but an opportunity to capitalize on the inner turmoil

01:01:26.780 --> 01:01:28.430
of the Khaganate rose quicker

01:01:28.430 --> 01:01:30.260
than the emperor thought it would.

01:01:30.260 --> 01:01:33.590
Political discord was caused by the Khagan's poor treatment

01:01:33.590 --> 01:01:36.050
of the tribes that fell under his command,

01:01:36.050 --> 01:01:38.270
and a handful of them broke away from him,

01:01:38.270 --> 01:01:41.000
which made the ruler furiously persecute them

01:01:41.000 --> 01:01:42.380
with all his might.

01:01:42.380 --> 01:01:44.990
War broke out between the various tribes

01:01:44.990 --> 01:01:47.750
and in 628, a lesser Khagan by the name

01:01:47.750 --> 01:01:51.290
of Ashina Shibobi requested Emperor Taizong's help

01:01:51.290 --> 01:01:53.270
in defeating the selfish ruler.

01:01:53.270 --> 01:01:55.670
He obliged and they successfully defeated

01:01:55.670 --> 01:01:58.940
the Eastern Khaganate leader by the year 630.

01:01:58.940 --> 01:02:00.800
The members of the Turkic tribes

01:02:00.800 --> 01:02:03.890
that fought against the Khagan nominated Emperor Taizong

01:02:03.890 --> 01:02:06.920
to rule over them marking him the first emperor

01:02:06.920 --> 01:02:09.650
to hold the title of both Chinese Emperor

01:02:09.650 --> 01:02:11.660
and the Khan of Heaven.

01:02:11.660 --> 01:02:14.990
Even after Taizong's death in the year 649,

01:02:14.990 --> 01:02:18.530
the Tang Dynasty steadily expanded while becoming more

01:02:18.530 --> 01:02:20.630
and more cosmopolitan in the cities

01:02:20.630 --> 01:02:24.050
such as Changan, the Capitol was the world's most

01:02:24.050 --> 01:02:25.850
populated city at the time.

01:02:25.850 --> 01:02:30.140
With approximately 2 million inhabitants, Buddhism, Taoism,

01:02:30.140 --> 01:02:33.470
and Confucianism all flourished under Tang rule.

01:02:33.470 --> 01:02:36.620
With monasteries and temples popping up all around

01:02:36.620 --> 01:02:39.950
the major cities, many famous paintings, poetry

01:02:39.950 --> 01:02:43.310
and pottery were created as art became more of a steeple

01:02:43.310 --> 01:02:44.630
of Chinese culture.

01:02:44.630 --> 01:02:48.170
Military efforts were made back into Korea and Vietnam

01:02:48.170 --> 01:02:51.530
and the Empire took control of many Western lands as well,

01:02:51.530 --> 01:02:53.270
which connected them more strongly

01:02:53.270 --> 01:02:56.270
to other major civilizations in the Mediterranean

01:02:56.270 --> 01:02:57.620
and the Middle East.

01:02:57.620 --> 01:02:58.850
They quickly swelled

01:02:58.850 --> 01:03:01.970
and became the most powerful state in Southeast Asia

01:03:01.970 --> 01:03:02.803
as a whole.

01:03:02.803 --> 01:03:05.240
Precisely because of the emphasis on improving

01:03:05.240 --> 01:03:07.520
the domestic state as opposed to spending

01:03:07.520 --> 01:03:09.920
all of the empire's resources.

01:03:09.920 --> 01:03:13.340
When an empire is stable within it is far easier

01:03:13.340 --> 01:03:14.900
to expand outward.

01:03:14.900 --> 01:03:17.990
The Golden Age reached its peak early into the later

01:03:17.990 --> 01:03:21.980
Emperor Xuanzong reign, which began in 712,

01:03:21.980 --> 01:03:23.960
though the latter half of his time in power

01:03:23.960 --> 01:03:25.520
saw the decline of the Tang.

01:03:25.520 --> 01:03:29.300
In 736, historian, musician and politician,

01:03:29.300 --> 01:03:32.510
Li Linfu was named the Tang chief minister

01:03:32.510 --> 01:03:34.310
and began increasing his power

01:03:34.310 --> 01:03:36.500
as Emperor Xuanzong became less

01:03:36.500 --> 01:03:39.500
and less interested in fulfilling his role as Emperor.

01:03:39.500 --> 01:03:43.130
Li Linfu had many of his court enemies executed

01:03:43.130 --> 01:03:45.530
and began introducing a series of policies

01:03:45.530 --> 01:03:47.840
that were very damaging to the empire.

01:03:47.840 --> 01:03:50.660
One major policy that would come back to bite the Tang

01:03:50.660 --> 01:03:54.020
was that the military governors must not be Chinese.

01:03:54.020 --> 01:03:56.360
The de facto ruler Li Linfu believed

01:03:56.360 --> 01:03:58.820
that there would be less trivial politics involved

01:03:58.820 --> 01:04:00.650
in the governmental process

01:04:00.650 --> 01:04:03.530
and that none of his rivals would be able to take power.

01:04:03.530 --> 01:04:06.290
One of the generals selected was a Turk by the name

01:04:06.290 --> 01:04:08.840
of An Lushan who commanded an army

01:04:08.840 --> 01:04:12.500
with over 150,000 soldiers in the Northeast.

01:04:12.500 --> 01:04:15.337
He was viewed very favorably by both the emperor

01:04:15.337 --> 01:04:18.950
and Li Linfu and rose the rinks very quickly,

01:04:18.950 --> 01:04:20.630
even being named a prince.

01:04:20.630 --> 01:04:24.280
However, after Li Linfu's death in 753,

01:04:24.280 --> 01:04:27.560
An Lushan was steadily being edged out of his position

01:04:27.560 --> 01:04:29.660
by political rivals in China,

01:04:29.660 --> 01:04:32.240
recognizing that he had very little to lose,

01:04:32.240 --> 01:04:34.610
he launched a rebellion against the dynasty

01:04:34.610 --> 01:04:37.430
to try and claim power over the empire.

01:04:37.430 --> 01:04:40.970
What followed was known as the An Lushan Rebellion,

01:04:40.970 --> 01:04:44.030
one of the deadliest wars in human history.

01:04:44.030 --> 01:04:48.740
In 755, An Lushan attacked the eastern capital of Luoyang

01:04:48.740 --> 01:04:50.990
and declared himself to be the emperor

01:04:50.990 --> 01:04:54.080
of the new Yan Dynasty after his victory,

01:04:54.080 --> 01:04:55.820
he then set his sights on the capture

01:04:55.820 --> 01:04:59.210
of the Tang Dynasty's western capital of Changan.

01:04:59.210 --> 01:05:02.950
Despite their initial successes and rapidly growing army,

01:05:02.950 --> 01:05:05.240
An Lushan's next major battle,

01:05:05.240 --> 01:05:09.260
the siege of Yongqiu was a definitive victory for the Tang.

01:05:09.260 --> 01:05:12.530
The Yongqiu was very militarily important

01:05:12.530 --> 01:05:14.180
and was a big stepping stone

01:05:14.180 --> 01:05:17.240
for An Lushan's push further south into China.

01:05:17.240 --> 01:05:20.480
The Tang recognized this and 2000 men were sent

01:05:20.480 --> 01:05:25.280
to besiege it and killed 20,000 Yan troops in the process.

01:05:25.280 --> 01:05:27.680
The Yan men were now unable to advance

01:05:27.680 --> 01:05:30.260
because of the Tang troops' defensive positions

01:05:30.260 --> 01:05:32.000
along the Tang Pass,

01:05:32.000 --> 01:05:34.550
but the tides turned due to inner turmoil

01:05:34.550 --> 01:05:35.990
with the Tang Dynasty

01:05:35.990 --> 01:05:39.170
as well as completely inept military judgment.

01:05:39.170 --> 01:05:40.640
Orders were made for the Tang

01:05:40.640 --> 01:05:43.940
to attack An Lushan's Yan army on open ground

01:05:43.940 --> 01:05:47.000
and they suffered a very bitter defeat.

01:05:47.000 --> 01:05:50.240
The path to the capital of Changan was now clear

01:05:50.240 --> 01:05:51.110
for the Yan.

01:05:51.110 --> 01:05:53.240
Catching wind of the impending threat,

01:05:53.240 --> 01:05:56.150
Emperor Xuanzong decided to flee the capital,

01:05:56.150 --> 01:05:59.510
an attempt to regroup in the province of Sichuan.

01:05:59.510 --> 01:06:02.390
However, this was not realized so easily.

01:06:02.390 --> 01:06:04.910
The emperor had brought much of his household court

01:06:04.910 --> 01:06:06.590
and bodyguards with him

01:06:06.590 --> 01:06:10.010
and chaos ensued his hunger induced anger and madness

01:06:10.010 --> 01:06:13.340
along the difficult terrains of China's mountainous regions

01:06:13.340 --> 01:06:16.910
resulted in the executions of members of the convoy.

01:06:16.910 --> 01:06:20.120
Fearing a mutiny, the emperor was required to go along

01:06:20.120 --> 01:06:22.130
with the demands of his soldiers

01:06:22.130 --> 01:06:25.790
even when they desired the deaths of his family members.

01:06:25.790 --> 01:06:28.730
While the emperor was forced to watch the strangulations

01:06:28.730 --> 01:06:31.700
of his relatives in desolate mountain ranges,

01:06:31.700 --> 01:06:34.490
a different kind of chaos was occurring in the capital

01:06:34.490 --> 01:06:38.150
of Changan, thousands fled at the side of the rebels

01:06:38.150 --> 01:06:39.980
who slashed their way through the city

01:06:39.980 --> 01:06:42.170
and looted like there was no tomorrow.

01:06:42.170 --> 01:06:45.980
Hundreds of thousands were killed in the bloody siege.

01:06:45.980 --> 01:06:49.850
In August, Emperor Xuanzong had finally reached Sichuan,

01:06:49.850 --> 01:06:52.670
where he abdicated and gave his son the throne.

01:06:52.670 --> 01:06:56.150
The new emperor recruited mercenaries to oppose An Lushan

01:06:56.150 --> 01:06:57.860
and they successfully prevented him

01:06:57.860 --> 01:06:59.870
from expanding further south.

01:06:59.870 --> 01:07:03.080
However, the internal turmoil of the self-proclaimed

01:07:03.080 --> 01:07:06.440
Yan Dynasty helped the Tang more than anything else.

01:07:06.440 --> 01:07:09.380
Fearing his constant state of violent paranoia,

01:07:09.380 --> 01:07:13.190
An Lushan was murdered by his own son, An Qingxu

01:07:13.190 --> 01:07:16.340
on January 29th, 757.

01:07:16.340 --> 01:07:19.610
The ruler had grown increasingly cruel to his subjects

01:07:19.610 --> 01:07:21.770
and flogged them whenever he pleased,

01:07:21.770 --> 01:07:24.230
which caused his subordinates to turn on him,

01:07:24.230 --> 01:07:26.480
especially when the obese tyrant's health

01:07:26.480 --> 01:07:28.160
took a turn for the worse.

01:07:28.160 --> 01:07:30.440
It is said that a horse was once crushed

01:07:30.440 --> 01:07:33.410
under the unfathomable weight of An Lushan.

01:07:33.410 --> 01:07:37.070
With his death, An Qingxu took over as leader of the Yan

01:07:37.070 --> 01:07:40.760
and launched a lengthy siege on the city of Suiyang

01:07:40.760 --> 01:07:43.460
resulting in one of the most disturbing battles

01:07:43.460 --> 01:07:44.930
in Chinese history,

01:07:44.930 --> 01:07:47.090
it could be said that both sides lost.

01:07:47.090 --> 01:07:51.050
On the Tang side, mass cannibalism ensued as the inhabitants

01:07:51.050 --> 01:07:54.650
of the besieged city resorted to eating the elderly women

01:07:54.650 --> 01:07:57.740
and children after running out of provisions.

01:07:57.740 --> 01:08:01.490
There remained only 400 Tang defenders of the city,

01:08:01.490 --> 01:08:04.700
less than 1% of its initial population,

01:08:04.700 --> 01:08:07.400
while the Yan did indeed eventually capture the city

01:08:07.400 --> 01:08:09.950
after approximately eight months of battle,

01:08:09.950 --> 01:08:13.010
they had suffered over a hundred thousand casualties

01:08:13.010 --> 01:08:16.430
and wasted plenty of time and resources.

01:08:16.430 --> 01:08:19.430
The Tang were able to reclaim the capitals of Changan

01:08:19.430 --> 01:08:21.680
and Luoyang because of this disarray

01:08:21.680 --> 01:08:24.650
and the Yan Dynasty began to burst at the seams

01:08:24.650 --> 01:08:26.570
because of political turmoil.

01:08:26.570 --> 01:08:29.450
The rebellion was put down in 763

01:08:29.450 --> 01:08:31.670
and the Tang emerged victorious.

01:08:31.670 --> 01:08:34.490
However, the Imperial government was far weaker

01:08:34.490 --> 01:08:36.890
than they had been before this mess had begun

01:08:36.890 --> 01:08:40.640
and the golden age of the Tang was undeniably over.

01:08:40.640 --> 01:08:44.450
20% of the empire's population had died as a result

01:08:44.450 --> 01:08:46.310
of the An Lushan rebellion

01:08:46.310 --> 01:08:49.100
and the Tang never fully recovered from its effects.

01:08:49.100 --> 01:08:51.050
Over the course of the ninth century,

01:08:51.050 --> 01:08:53.660
the struggling dynasty lost much of its northern

01:08:53.660 --> 01:08:55.820
and western territory to Turks

01:08:55.820 --> 01:08:57.860
and the Tibetan empire who took advantage

01:08:57.860 --> 01:08:59.450
of their vulnerable state,

01:08:59.450 --> 01:09:02.390
the Tang were ruled by a line of poor emperors

01:09:02.390 --> 01:09:03.590
during this time.

01:09:03.590 --> 01:09:06.830
Massive groups of bandits became increasingly common,

01:09:06.830 --> 01:09:09.770
ransacking cities and smuggling illicit goods

01:09:09.770 --> 01:09:12.710
across the empire until full scale rebellions

01:09:12.710 --> 01:09:14.390
reared their heads once again.

01:09:14.390 --> 01:09:17.840
In 875, a disgruntled former salt smuggler

01:09:17.840 --> 01:09:20.900
named Huang Chao started a peasant rebellion

01:09:20.900 --> 01:09:24.020
with tens of thousands of soldiers and citizens.

01:09:24.020 --> 01:09:26.870
His forces steadily pushed into the south of China,

01:09:26.870 --> 01:09:29.810
massacring thousands of people along the way,

01:09:29.810 --> 01:09:32.630
particularly merchants who they saw as sympathetic

01:09:32.630 --> 01:09:33.860
to the Tang reign.

01:09:33.860 --> 01:09:37.370
By 881, the capital of Changan had been captured

01:09:37.370 --> 01:09:41.870
and Huang Chao declared himself emperor of the Daqi Dynasty.

01:09:41.870 --> 01:09:43.940
Angry with the selfish and inept rich

01:09:43.940 --> 01:09:45.650
and ruling class of China,

01:09:45.650 --> 01:09:47.300
many of his reforms were focused

01:09:47.300 --> 01:09:48.980
on confiscating their wealth,

01:09:48.980 --> 01:09:51.140
but it did not take long for Huang Chao

01:09:51.140 --> 01:09:53.900
to prove that he was no better at running an empire.

01:09:53.900 --> 01:09:56.660
Unfortunately, for the self-proclaimed empire,

01:09:56.660 --> 01:09:58.820
he was unable to arrange of food supply

01:09:58.820 --> 01:10:00.230
to the concord capital.

01:10:00.230 --> 01:10:02.600
The Tang Dynasty struck back with a series

01:10:02.600 --> 01:10:05.750
of counter attacks under the command of General Zhu Wen.

01:10:05.750 --> 01:10:08.540
Zhu Wen had been a general in none other than Huang Chao's

01:10:08.540 --> 01:10:12.650
rebellion, but defected to the Tang Dynasty in 882.

01:10:12.650 --> 01:10:14.930
With the help of Zhu Wen's strong leadership,

01:10:14.930 --> 01:10:17.300
the government utilized alliances with a group

01:10:17.300 --> 01:10:19.730
of Turkish tribes to drive Huang Chao

01:10:19.730 --> 01:10:23.090
and his de facto dynasty out of the capital.

01:10:23.090 --> 01:10:25.640
Huang Chao was killed in 884

01:10:25.640 --> 01:10:28.400
and his legacy today is one of controversy.

01:10:28.400 --> 01:10:30.440
Some, see him as a violent traitor

01:10:30.440 --> 01:10:34.100
who committed many atrocities during his military campaign,

01:10:34.100 --> 01:10:37.670
though others see him as a hero of the peasant rebellion

01:10:37.670 --> 01:10:40.460
who was committed to ridding China of corruption

01:10:40.460 --> 01:10:41.570
and wealth hoarding.

01:10:41.570 --> 01:10:44.480
Whatever the true nature of Huang Chao may have been,

01:10:44.480 --> 01:10:48.230
the damage he inflicted on the already weakened Tang Empire

01:10:48.230 --> 01:10:50.000
was certainly irreparable.

01:10:50.000 --> 01:10:52.790
The central government had lost much of its power

01:10:52.790 --> 01:10:55.133
and no longer had a solidified army.

01:10:56.692 --> 01:10:59.275
(gentle music)

01:11:01.280 --> 01:11:04.130
As a side note, while the ninth century was indeed

01:11:04.130 --> 01:11:07.610
disastrous for the Tang Dynasty, an important invention

01:11:07.610 --> 01:11:11.240
that would sheep modern history was created in 850 AD

01:11:11.240 --> 01:11:14.120
within the empire's borders, gunpowder.

01:11:14.120 --> 01:11:16.670
An unknown monk, an alchemist was trying to invent

01:11:16.670 --> 01:11:18.620
a substance that would heal ailments

01:11:18.620 --> 01:11:20.540
and prolong one's lifespan.

01:11:20.540 --> 01:11:23.690
In doing so, he mixed the following proportions,

01:11:23.690 --> 01:11:28.690
75% saltpetre, 15% charcoal and 10% sulfur.

01:11:29.270 --> 01:11:31.490
The result was plenty of scorched skin

01:11:31.490 --> 01:11:33.470
within the group of monks who were present

01:11:33.470 --> 01:11:36.350
and the house they resided in was burnt to the ground.

01:11:36.350 --> 01:11:39.620
Gunpowder was considered one of the four great inventions

01:11:39.620 --> 01:11:43.910
of China alongside paper making, printing and the compass.

01:11:43.910 --> 01:11:46.640
Although the invention would be utilized more efficiently

01:11:46.640 --> 01:11:49.220
in coming years, particularly with the rise

01:11:49.220 --> 01:11:51.920
of the Song Dynasty in the 10th century,

01:11:51.920 --> 01:11:55.100
history shows that it was Chinese monks under the Tang

01:11:55.100 --> 01:11:56.780
who discovered the substance,

01:11:56.780 --> 01:12:00.863
no matter what other dynasties or western empires may claim.

01:12:02.401 --> 01:12:05.151
(dramatic music)

01:12:07.310 --> 01:12:10.220
Without a widespread military application though,

01:12:10.220 --> 01:12:12.800
the newfound substance did not make a difference

01:12:12.800 --> 01:12:14.780
in the fate of the declining Tang.

01:12:14.780 --> 01:12:18.650
An era known as the Five Dynasties and Ten Kingdoms period

01:12:18.650 --> 01:12:22.160
was on its way and would be marked by various warlords

01:12:22.160 --> 01:12:26.120
and regimes staking claims for power across China.

01:12:26.120 --> 01:12:28.730
The period is notoriously difficult to follow

01:12:28.730 --> 01:12:31.850
because of how messy and unstable the region was.

01:12:31.850 --> 01:12:35.960
With constant assassinations, new and shattered alliances

01:12:35.960 --> 01:12:38.000
and factions breaking apart,

01:12:38.000 --> 01:12:41.360
the situation was constantly changing just like it had

01:12:41.360 --> 01:12:43.610
during the warring states period.

01:12:43.610 --> 01:12:47.210
This name Five Dynasties and Ten Kingdoms period came to be

01:12:47.210 --> 01:12:50.840
as five regimes successfully ruled over the northern region

01:12:50.840 --> 01:12:51.740
of China.

01:12:51.740 --> 01:12:54.530
While 10 independent states were established

01:12:54.530 --> 01:12:56.690
in southern and western China.

01:12:56.690 --> 01:12:58.910
Though these states were relatively stable

01:12:58.910 --> 01:13:01.670
during their existence, they were not as significant

01:13:01.670 --> 01:13:03.920
as the five major dynasties.

01:13:03.920 --> 01:13:06.200
The first of these five dynasty rulers

01:13:06.200 --> 01:13:08.180
was the warlord Zhu Wen

01:13:08.180 --> 01:13:10.460
though he had helped the Huang Chao Rebellion

01:13:10.460 --> 01:13:12.200
and then the Tang government,

01:13:12.200 --> 01:13:14.960
Zhu Wen was now looking to help himself.

01:13:14.960 --> 01:13:18.410
In 904, he executed the emperor of Tang

01:13:18.410 --> 01:13:21.260
and made the dead ruler's 13-year-old boy serve

01:13:21.260 --> 01:13:22.700
as a puppet emperor.

01:13:22.700 --> 01:13:26.300
Only three years later in 907, he usurped the throne

01:13:26.300 --> 01:13:29.090
and named himself emperor of the Liang,

01:13:29.090 --> 01:13:32.360
the first of the five dynasties that ruled in this era.

01:13:32.360 --> 01:13:35.810
However many other warlords did not accept his rule

01:13:35.810 --> 01:13:38.060
and established their own countries.

01:13:38.060 --> 01:13:41.780
One of these men was Li Keyong, a rival of Zhu Wen.

01:13:41.780 --> 01:13:44.630
Prior to the establishment of the Liang Dynasty,

01:13:44.630 --> 01:13:47.480
Zhu Wen had attempted to assassinate Li Keyong,

01:13:47.480 --> 01:13:49.820
so he understandably had no interest

01:13:49.820 --> 01:13:51.190
in serving the new emperor.

01:13:51.190 --> 01:13:54.800
Li Keyong established the minor kingdom of Jin,

01:13:54.800 --> 01:13:58.280
which would play a large role in future power struggles,

01:13:58.280 --> 01:14:01.460
but rivals such as Li Keyong were not the only ones

01:14:01.460 --> 01:14:02.750
who hated the Emperor.

01:14:02.750 --> 01:14:05.720
Zhu Wen often summoned his son's wives to the palace

01:14:05.720 --> 01:14:07.100
to have sex with them.

01:14:07.100 --> 01:14:09.470
He was a notorious sexual predator

01:14:09.470 --> 01:14:12.050
who repeatedly assaulted his officer's wives

01:14:12.050 --> 01:14:14.300
as well as his own daughters-in-law.

01:14:14.300 --> 01:14:16.640
As a result of his horrendous conduct,

01:14:16.640 --> 01:14:19.970
as well as familial turmoil over which son would succeed,

01:14:19.970 --> 01:14:23.360
the crazed ruler, Zhu Wen was murdered in his palace

01:14:23.360 --> 01:14:25.547
by his third son, Zhu Yogui.

01:14:25.547 --> 01:14:28.760
Zhu Yogui would last just one year in power

01:14:28.760 --> 01:14:31.580
being murdered soon thereafter by his younger brother,

01:14:31.580 --> 01:14:34.340
Zhu Youzhen in a coup for the throne.

01:14:34.340 --> 01:14:36.800
He would rule from 913 onward

01:14:36.800 --> 01:14:39.170
with his reign lasting about a decade.

01:14:39.170 --> 01:14:41.810
It was during that time that a boiling point was reached

01:14:41.810 --> 01:14:44.330
between the Liang and the kingdoms of Jin.

01:14:44.330 --> 01:14:47.660
After many clashes with Emperor Zhu Youzhen's troops

01:14:47.660 --> 01:14:49.370
over contested regions,

01:14:49.370 --> 01:14:52.040
the Jin kingdom had become quite powerful

01:14:52.040 --> 01:14:55.700
and contested the Liang Dynasty in 923.

01:14:55.700 --> 01:14:59.570
They established what is known as the Later Tang Dynasty.

01:14:59.570 --> 01:15:01.190
They kept the name as Tang

01:15:01.190 --> 01:15:03.920
because they desired a restored empire.

01:15:03.920 --> 01:15:06.620
Li Cunxu, who was Li Keyong's son

01:15:06.620 --> 01:15:09.290
became the first emperor of the Later Tang.

01:15:09.290 --> 01:15:11.240
While they showed flashes of brilliance

01:15:11.240 --> 01:15:13.850
and potential promise in unifying China,

01:15:13.850 --> 01:15:16.970
they failed to control the regions they initially conquered

01:15:16.970 --> 01:15:19.100
due to more declarations of independence

01:15:19.100 --> 01:15:20.480
within their territory.

01:15:20.480 --> 01:15:22.220
The state was thrown into chaos

01:15:22.220 --> 01:15:25.157
due to Li Cunxu's poor leadership, as the emperor

01:15:25.157 --> 01:15:28.157
and his consort Empress Liu hoarded wealth

01:15:28.157 --> 01:15:31.550
and did not reward his soldiers for their efforts in battle.

01:15:31.550 --> 01:15:36.080
In the spring of 926, he was finally murdered in a mutiny.

01:15:36.080 --> 01:15:38.690
The next dynasty was formed by a veteran general

01:15:38.690 --> 01:15:41.750
named Shi Jingtang, his claiming of the throne

01:15:41.750 --> 01:15:44.120
marked the third of the five dynasties

01:15:44.120 --> 01:15:47.330
and was labeled the Later Jin or Shi Jin.

01:15:47.330 --> 01:15:50.720
During this time, Shi Jingtang's army was not powerful

01:15:50.720 --> 01:15:54.140
enough to control the incredibly dynamic wartime landscape

01:15:54.140 --> 01:15:57.380
of China, and in 936 he asked for the help

01:15:57.380 --> 01:15:59.330
of the Khitan in the north.

01:15:59.330 --> 01:16:02.210
The Khitan were a nomadic people who dominated

01:16:02.210 --> 01:16:05.840
much of Northeast Asia, including modern day Mongolia,

01:16:05.840 --> 01:16:09.140
as well as chunks of China and Russia's far east.

01:16:09.140 --> 01:16:12.290
A term of the agreement was that the 16 prefectures

01:16:12.290 --> 01:16:14.870
of Yayun, a region along the Great Wall,

01:16:14.870 --> 01:16:16.790
which contained the strategic positions

01:16:16.790 --> 01:16:19.340
of modern day Beijing and Tianjin.

01:16:19.340 --> 01:16:22.550
The Khitan Emperor Yelu Delang was also given

01:16:22.550 --> 01:16:25.160
superiority over Shi Jingtang.

01:16:25.160 --> 01:16:27.170
This was the cause of a conflict.

01:16:27.170 --> 01:16:29.300
As the Later Jin eventually decided

01:16:29.300 --> 01:16:31.340
that they did not wanna live under the rule

01:16:31.340 --> 01:16:32.840
of the Khitan emperor,

01:16:32.840 --> 01:16:36.140
they tried to distance themselves from Yelu Delang's reign,

01:16:36.140 --> 01:16:39.860
which enraged the ruler who had so recently greatly helped

01:16:39.860 --> 01:16:42.260
in the establishment of their dynasty.

01:16:42.260 --> 01:16:45.710
A war broke out and Khitan conquered the Later Jin.

01:16:45.710 --> 01:16:49.460
They sacked the Shang Prefecture, modern day Anyang

01:16:49.460 --> 01:16:52.010
and massacred most of the population.

01:16:52.010 --> 01:16:54.860
The Khitan state was renamed the Liao Dynasty

01:16:54.860 --> 01:16:59.090
and Yelu Delang declared himself emperor of all of China.

01:16:59.090 --> 01:17:02.120
However, this era did not last very long.

01:17:02.120 --> 01:17:04.790
The ruler was universally hated by the Chinese

01:17:04.790 --> 01:17:06.650
and after constant pushback,

01:17:06.650 --> 01:17:09.830
he died while journeying in an attempt to return north.

01:17:09.830 --> 01:17:13.220
Shortly after this, rebel Liu Zheyan ceased power

01:17:13.220 --> 01:17:16.700
and named himself emperor of the Later Han Dynasty.

01:17:16.700 --> 01:17:19.490
Though he died after just one year in power.

01:17:19.490 --> 01:17:22.250
He was succeeded by his son Liu Chengyou,

01:17:22.250 --> 01:17:25.250
who took the throne at just 17 years of age.

01:17:25.250 --> 01:17:27.470
Though a minister by the name of Guo Wei

01:17:27.470 --> 01:17:29.480
usurped the inept young leader

01:17:29.480 --> 01:17:31.850
after just three years as emperor.

01:17:31.850 --> 01:17:34.370
This made the Later Han the shortest dynasty

01:17:34.370 --> 01:17:37.580
from this period, lasting just about five years.

01:17:37.580 --> 01:17:41.330
In 951, Guo Wei declared himself the new emperor

01:17:41.330 --> 01:17:44.813
of the last of the five dynasties, the Later Zhou.

01:17:46.550 --> 01:17:48.727
The state served as a vassal state to the Khitan

01:17:48.727 --> 01:17:52.070
in the north and lasted until 1960

01:17:52.070 --> 01:17:54.800
when a new force emerged to unified China.

01:17:54.800 --> 01:17:56.866
The Song Dynasty.

01:17:56.866 --> 01:17:59.283
(calm music)

01:18:02.450 --> 01:18:04.190
The Song Dynasty was formed

01:18:04.190 --> 01:18:07.340
after Zhao Kuangyin, a military inspector,

01:18:07.340 --> 01:18:10.370
general of the Later Zhao Dynasty gained control

01:18:10.370 --> 01:18:12.260
of the empire after a coup.

01:18:12.260 --> 01:18:14.900
He was able to conquer the remaining regions of China,

01:18:14.900 --> 01:18:16.820
not yet under his control

01:18:16.820 --> 01:18:19.370
and ended the unstable Five Dynasties

01:18:19.370 --> 01:18:23.210
and Ten Kingdoms Period with the unification of the empire.

01:18:23.210 --> 01:18:25.340
The Song Dynasty's history is divided

01:18:25.340 --> 01:18:27.200
into two major periods.

01:18:27.200 --> 01:18:31.880
The Northern Song lasting from 960 to 1127 AD

01:18:31.880 --> 01:18:36.770
and the Southern Song lasting from 1127 to 1279.

01:18:36.770 --> 01:18:40.220
Zhao Kuangyin, now known as Emperor Taizu of Song,

01:18:40.220 --> 01:18:43.490
spearheaded a project to map the entire empire

01:18:43.490 --> 01:18:46.850
and put an increased focus on scholarly pursuits.

01:18:46.850 --> 01:18:49.160
The civil service exams were revamped

01:18:49.160 --> 01:18:51.890
and Confucianism made a major return.

01:18:51.890 --> 01:18:55.040
This revived push of Confucianism is often referred

01:18:55.040 --> 01:18:59.600
to as Neo-Confucianism, in the context of the Song Dynasty.

01:18:59.600 --> 01:19:02.090
Though the Song had reunified China,

01:19:02.090 --> 01:19:03.950
they were quite weak, militarily

01:19:03.950 --> 01:19:06.263
compared to the preceding Tang Dynasty.

01:19:07.520 --> 01:19:08.990
After Taizu's death,

01:19:08.990 --> 01:19:11.240
his successors had continuously been threatened

01:19:11.240 --> 01:19:14.330
by the Khitan Liao Kingdom in the north

01:19:14.330 --> 01:19:16.670
that had been established during the Five Dynasties

01:19:16.670 --> 01:19:18.260
and Ten Kingdoms Period.

01:19:18.260 --> 01:19:20.960
Over time, the bureaucracies quality worsened

01:19:20.960 --> 01:19:22.910
and worsened until the Jurchen

01:19:22.910 --> 01:19:25.460
a northern ethnic group from the Khitan lands

01:19:25.460 --> 01:19:28.700
who had overthrown the Liao finally took advantage.

01:19:28.700 --> 01:19:32.690
In 1126, the Jurchen, now taking the Chinese name

01:19:32.690 --> 01:19:37.220
of the Jin Dynasty, conquered the capital city of Kaifeng.

01:19:37.220 --> 01:19:40.670
It was truly a shame for the Northern Song Dynasty

01:19:40.670 --> 01:19:44.060
as the capital city had become a beautiful cosmopolitan

01:19:44.060 --> 01:19:45.890
center before the invasion,

01:19:45.890 --> 01:19:47.780
the last Northern Song emperor

01:19:47.780 --> 01:19:50.600
had been an avid art collector and enthusiast,

01:19:50.600 --> 01:19:54.680
and so as a result, the city was full of gorgeous temples,

01:19:54.680 --> 01:19:57.080
palaces, and pagodas,

01:19:57.080 --> 01:19:59.870
which are tower like architectural structures

01:19:59.870 --> 01:20:03.440
typically associated with Buddhism in Southeast Asia.

01:20:03.440 --> 01:20:06.200
The city was easy picking however, for the Jin,

01:20:06.200 --> 01:20:09.470
the Song were very weak by the mid 12th century

01:20:09.470 --> 01:20:12.110
and the invading forces burned the metropolis

01:20:12.110 --> 01:20:13.463
upon their arrival.

01:20:15.380 --> 01:20:17.870
The North had been taken over by the Jin,

01:20:17.870 --> 01:20:19.670
but were unable to seize control

01:20:19.670 --> 01:20:22.490
of the Song Dynasty's southern territories.

01:20:22.490 --> 01:20:26.390
The Southern Song Dynasty began in 1127

01:20:26.390 --> 01:20:29.060
with Lin'an or modern day Hangzhou,

01:20:29.060 --> 01:20:30.830
serving as the capital city.

01:20:30.830 --> 01:20:33.500
Despite their defeat in the north at the hands of the Jin,

01:20:33.500 --> 01:20:36.530
the Southern Song era was very prosperous.

01:20:36.530 --> 01:20:39.500
Rice production boomed as farmers were granted the rights

01:20:39.500 --> 01:20:41.720
to their land, which grew the economy

01:20:41.720 --> 01:20:44.420
as peasants could now sell and trade their surpluses

01:20:44.420 --> 01:20:46.250
to acquire other goods.

01:20:46.250 --> 01:20:49.400
The population exploded and many great inventions

01:20:49.400 --> 01:20:50.600
came about.

01:20:50.600 --> 01:20:53.030
The printing press allowed for the mass production

01:20:53.030 --> 01:20:55.850
of paper money, making the Song the first government

01:20:55.850 --> 01:20:58.040
in the whole world to achieve this feat.

01:20:58.040 --> 01:21:01.580
The magnetic compass was also created at this time,

01:21:01.580 --> 01:21:03.440
which modernized navigation.

01:21:03.440 --> 01:21:05.450
Once again, the Song Dynasty

01:21:05.450 --> 01:21:08.720
were also able to utilize gunpowder for weaponry

01:21:08.720 --> 01:21:12.260
and began launching bombs from catapults in warfare.

01:21:12.260 --> 01:21:13.940
This allowed the Southern Song troops

01:21:13.940 --> 01:21:15.470
to defeat the Jin dynasties

01:21:15.470 --> 01:21:18.590
and naval forces even when they were wildly outnumbered

01:21:18.590 --> 01:21:20.810
by a massive number of ships.

01:21:20.810 --> 01:21:22.910
They were unfortunately still unable

01:21:22.910 --> 01:21:25.340
to take back the northern regions of China.

01:21:25.340 --> 01:21:28.700
As the opposing forces were growing stronger and stronger

01:21:28.700 --> 01:21:31.100
and were able to replicate their inventions

01:21:31.100 --> 01:21:34.220
simply by kidnapping tradesmen from Southern Song

01:21:34.220 --> 01:21:37.610
and forcing them to recreate their weaponry and tools.

01:21:37.610 --> 01:21:39.920
Considering their outmatched military,

01:21:39.920 --> 01:21:43.340
the Southern Song scholars rejected foreign influences

01:21:43.340 --> 01:21:46.940
and desired the preservation of traditional Chinese culture,

01:21:46.940 --> 01:21:49.160
fearing that they could be wiped off the map

01:21:49.160 --> 01:21:50.330
during the wartime.

01:21:50.330 --> 01:21:53.450
This fear is why Confucianism made a comeback

01:21:53.450 --> 01:21:55.760
during the dynasty as it was believed

01:21:55.760 --> 01:21:58.850
that the core principles were crucial to China's development

01:21:58.850 --> 01:21:59.810
and future.

01:21:59.810 --> 01:22:02.600
An increased focus was placed on healthy communities

01:22:02.600 --> 01:22:06.560
and families, which made for very well-developed cities.

01:22:06.560 --> 01:22:08.360
An excellent age of paintings

01:22:08.360 --> 01:22:10.490
and other art blossomed at this time

01:22:10.490 --> 01:22:13.550
with many works focusing on the beauty of village scenes

01:22:13.550 --> 01:22:15.110
and familial peace.

01:22:15.110 --> 01:22:16.550
No philosophy or art,

01:22:16.550 --> 01:22:19.070
however could save the Song from their fate

01:22:19.070 --> 01:22:23.240
at the hands of one of the most famous men in human history,

01:22:23.240 --> 01:22:24.323
Genghis Khan.

01:22:26.521 --> 01:22:29.271
(dramatic music)

01:22:30.830 --> 01:22:34.940
Genghis, originally named Temüjin, had been born in Mongolia

01:22:34.940 --> 01:22:39.470
in 1162 AD as a member of the Borjigin tribe

01:22:39.470 --> 01:22:41.660
and was a descendant of a former leader.

01:22:41.660 --> 01:22:45.200
It is said that Genghis was born grasping a blood clot

01:22:45.200 --> 01:22:48.110
in his fist, a sign in Mongol folklore

01:22:48.110 --> 01:22:50.120
that he was destined to lead.

01:22:50.120 --> 01:22:53.900
Life in Genghis' region was not easy by any means

01:22:53.900 --> 01:22:56.090
with constant warring between tribes

01:22:56.090 --> 01:22:58.460
and difficult environments earning at the title

01:22:58.460 --> 01:23:01.400
of the barbarian wilderness in China.

01:23:01.400 --> 01:23:04.400
Genghis spent his early years learning to hunt, travel

01:23:04.400 --> 01:23:08.120
and ride horses and was said to be very disinterested

01:23:08.120 --> 01:23:09.500
in speaking with others.

01:23:09.500 --> 01:23:12.800
At the age of nine, his parents arranged Genghis' marriage

01:23:12.800 --> 01:23:15.980
with a girl named Borte from a neighboring tribe

01:23:15.980 --> 01:23:17.960
who was 10 years old at the time.

01:23:17.960 --> 01:23:20.240
Such was commonplace with the Mongols,

01:23:20.240 --> 01:23:24.080
with camps often containing junior wives, concubines

01:23:24.080 --> 01:23:25.100
and children.

01:23:25.100 --> 01:23:29.000
Women had a little to no agency in these decisions.

01:23:29.000 --> 01:23:31.460
Genghis was to be transferred to Borte's camp

01:23:31.460 --> 01:23:33.410
after the marriage was set in stone

01:23:33.410 --> 01:23:35.390
so the pair could grow up together.

01:23:35.390 --> 01:23:38.330
On the journey, however, Rival Tatars poisoned

01:23:38.330 --> 01:23:41.120
and killed Genghis' father by offering food

01:23:41.120 --> 01:23:42.800
and drink for their travels,

01:23:42.800 --> 01:23:45.410
leaving the young boy's family fatherless.

01:23:45.410 --> 01:23:47.390
Genghis returned home after this

01:23:47.390 --> 01:23:49.670
as his family were abandoned by their tribe

01:23:49.670 --> 01:23:52.820
and had been left in a vulnerable outcast position.

01:23:52.820 --> 01:23:54.950
Without a patriarchal figure,

01:23:54.950 --> 01:23:58.280
tensions rose between Genghis and one of his stepbrothers,

01:23:58.280 --> 01:24:02.060
Behter as both boys claimed to be their father's heir.

01:24:02.060 --> 01:24:03.890
Behter was the older of the two,

01:24:03.890 --> 01:24:07.193
though Genghis was the child of their father's chief wife.

01:24:08.210 --> 01:24:11.591
Their rivalry came to a head when Genghis was 13

01:24:11.591 --> 01:24:13.160
and Behter tried to take a fish

01:24:13.160 --> 01:24:15.020
that Genghis had caught for himself.

01:24:15.020 --> 01:24:17.840
Genghis drew his bow and killed Behter

01:24:17.840 --> 01:24:19.820
marking the first kill of a man

01:24:19.820 --> 01:24:21.320
who would eventually have the deaths

01:24:21.320 --> 01:24:25.010
of roughly 40 million people attributed to him.

01:24:25.010 --> 01:24:27.367
By the time the hardened Genghis was 15,

01:24:27.367 --> 01:24:30.230
he had become incredibly skilled in hunting

01:24:30.230 --> 01:24:31.700
and horsemanship.

01:24:31.700 --> 01:24:34.160
He became the leader of his remaining brothers,

01:24:34.160 --> 01:24:35.420
which prompted the clan

01:24:35.420 --> 01:24:38.240
that had initially expelled his family to take him

01:24:38.240 --> 01:24:40.640
as prisoner as they feared he would organize

01:24:40.640 --> 01:24:42.110
an attack against them.

01:24:42.110 --> 01:24:43.490
He escaped during a feast

01:24:43.490 --> 01:24:45.560
and hid in the tent of a guard who had failed

01:24:45.560 --> 01:24:48.380
to raise the alarm as he made a run for it.

01:24:48.380 --> 01:24:50.840
He took shelter in the tent for three days,

01:24:50.840 --> 01:24:52.040
threatening to tell the clan

01:24:52.040 --> 01:24:53.930
that the guard had helped him escape.

01:24:53.930 --> 01:24:55.820
In a very clever move,

01:24:55.820 --> 01:24:59.090
he then used this cart to acquire a horse from the guard

01:24:59.090 --> 01:25:01.070
and gallop away into the night.

01:25:01.070 --> 01:25:04.340
At 16, Genghis returned to the encampment of Borte

01:25:04.340 --> 01:25:06.080
to finally marry the girl

01:25:06.080 --> 01:25:08.270
after their last arrangement had been foiled

01:25:08.270 --> 01:25:10.430
by his father's untimely death.

01:25:10.430 --> 01:25:13.460
Borte's father was over the moon at his return

01:25:13.460 --> 01:25:16.820
and gifted Genghis a sable cloak to welcome him back.

01:25:16.820 --> 01:25:19.640
Genghis then re-gifted the cloak to Toghrul,

01:25:19.640 --> 01:25:23.060
the leader of a neighboring tribe to gain his alliance.

01:25:23.060 --> 01:25:25.490
Wanting to regain the loyalty of the tribesmen

01:25:25.490 --> 01:25:27.230
who had abandoned his family

01:25:27.230 --> 01:25:30.350
Genghis first aimed to build a strong following

01:25:30.350 --> 01:25:31.550
and that he did.

01:25:31.550 --> 01:25:34.940
Other clans began making alliances with Genghis

01:25:34.940 --> 01:25:36.830
and before long he had amassed

01:25:36.830 --> 01:25:39.740
a relatively strong military force.

01:25:39.740 --> 01:25:41.780
Around this time, Genghis and his wife

01:25:41.780 --> 01:25:44.930
had their first child, a daughter named Qojin.

01:25:44.930 --> 01:25:47.780
Soon after, however, things took a turn for the worse

01:25:47.780 --> 01:25:51.470
for Genghis, a group of 300 Merkit horsemen,

01:25:51.470 --> 01:25:55.220
the Merkit being one of the five major tribal confederation

01:25:55.220 --> 01:25:57.950
of the land raided Genghis encampment

01:25:57.950 --> 01:25:59.900
and kidnapped his wife, Borte.

01:25:59.900 --> 01:26:03.110
Genghis swore to destroy the Merkit invaders

01:26:03.110 --> 01:26:05.780
and in preparation was able to put together an army

01:26:05.780 --> 01:26:08.840
of thousands of warriors using his alliances.

01:26:08.840 --> 01:26:12.500
They struck back hard and a merciless attack on the Merkits

01:26:12.500 --> 01:26:15.080
and comprehensively destroyed the invaders

01:26:15.080 --> 01:26:17.900
in a whirlwind of killing and pillaging.

01:26:17.900 --> 01:26:20.780
Genghis discovered his wife, who was now pregnant

01:26:20.780 --> 01:26:23.750
after being repeatedly abused by a Merkit

01:26:23.750 --> 01:26:25.730
and returned her home to camp.

01:26:25.730 --> 01:26:28.250
She gave birth to their son Jochi,

01:26:28.250 --> 01:26:30.440
who would be followed for the rest of his life

01:26:30.440 --> 01:26:34.029
with questions about his true biological father.

01:26:34.029 --> 01:26:36.260
Genghis and Borte would have three more sons

01:26:36.260 --> 01:26:39.500
and four more daughters in the course of the next decade.

01:26:39.500 --> 01:26:41.810
It was during this time that Genghis became

01:26:41.810 --> 01:26:44.210
exceedingly close with his childhood friend

01:26:44.210 --> 01:26:47.930
and blood brother Jamukha and United their clans.

01:26:47.930 --> 01:26:51.170
The two men spent an enormous amount of their time together,

01:26:51.170 --> 01:26:54.830
be it during camping, riding or other everyday activity.

01:26:54.830 --> 01:26:58.340
Supposedly they even slept under the same blanket.

01:26:58.340 --> 01:27:00.440
Eventually, however tensions arose

01:27:00.440 --> 01:27:02.300
and the two liters left one another.

01:27:02.300 --> 01:27:05.330
It is not entirely clear why this occurred.

01:27:05.330 --> 01:27:08.420
Though certain texts indicate that a jealous Borte

01:27:08.420 --> 01:27:10.550
played a hand by spreading rumors

01:27:10.550 --> 01:27:12.740
and misinformation about Jamukha.

01:27:12.740 --> 01:27:15.800
Unfortunately, for Jamukha, many of his soldiers

01:27:15.800 --> 01:27:17.690
and leaders joined Genghis.

01:27:17.690 --> 01:27:20.630
Before long, Genghis was developing the largest

01:27:20.630 --> 01:27:22.880
and most powerful Mongol clan.

01:27:22.880 --> 01:27:24.830
He was acclaimed by his followers

01:27:24.830 --> 01:27:26.840
as the Khan of the Mongols.

01:27:26.840 --> 01:27:29.600
He proved to be a vicious military leader

01:27:29.600 --> 01:27:31.100
and expanded his territory

01:27:31.100 --> 01:27:32.807
through murderous raids in which him

01:27:32.807 --> 01:27:35.630
and his men would pillage and burn settlements

01:27:35.630 --> 01:27:37.310
before taking their women.

01:27:37.310 --> 01:27:40.880
This served as a form of psychological warfare as well

01:27:40.880 --> 01:27:43.310
with many men simply surrendering their camps

01:27:43.310 --> 01:27:45.440
without a fight to avoid the destruction

01:27:45.440 --> 01:27:48.860
that was becoming all too common in the surrounding areas.

01:27:48.860 --> 01:27:52.100
While they were overwhelmingly successful in these campaigns

01:27:52.100 --> 01:27:53.930
and were gaining much of the ground

01:27:53.930 --> 01:27:56.780
and men of Mongolia, tensions were rising

01:27:56.780 --> 01:28:01.396
with Jamukha's very much alive and very much resentful army.

01:28:01.396 --> 01:28:04.610
Genghis' former blood brother was quickly becoming

01:28:04.610 --> 01:28:06.260
his sworn enemy.

01:28:06.260 --> 01:28:11.060
Open conflict broke out in 1187 with the two sides clashing

01:28:11.060 --> 01:28:13.520
at the Battle of Dalan Baljut.

01:28:13.520 --> 01:28:16.310
Jamukha had assembled 30,000 soldiers

01:28:16.310 --> 01:28:18.860
and flanked Genghis' men from the north.

01:28:18.860 --> 01:28:21.260
While they were evenly matched in size

01:28:21.260 --> 01:28:25.490
it was a decisive bloody victory for Jamukha and his men

01:28:25.490 --> 01:28:28.430
and the disgruntled leader was shockingly cruel

01:28:28.430 --> 01:28:30.230
in the aftermath.

01:28:30.230 --> 01:28:33.170
He boiled 70 captured young men alive

01:28:33.170 --> 01:28:36.140
and humiliated the deceased bodies of the rival leaders

01:28:36.140 --> 01:28:38.210
that were now siding with Genghis.

01:28:38.210 --> 01:28:41.450
This cruelty, however, did not serve Jamukha well

01:28:41.450 --> 01:28:43.730
as many followers defected to Genghis,

01:28:43.730 --> 01:28:46.730
after witnessing his true vicious nature,

01:28:46.730 --> 01:28:50.720
approximately 10,000 of his men joined his rival side

01:28:50.720 --> 01:28:53.900
that day, which forced the now outnumbered Jamukha

01:28:53.900 --> 01:28:55.580
to move his men back.

01:28:55.580 --> 01:28:58.880
The victory however was still undoubtedly his.

01:28:58.880 --> 01:29:01.130
Humiliated with such a brutal defeat,

01:29:01.130 --> 01:29:03.890
Genghis Khan put an increased focus on the discipline

01:29:03.890 --> 01:29:05.690
and training of his military

01:29:05.690 --> 01:29:09.800
and forged an unimaginably powerful killing machine

01:29:09.800 --> 01:29:11.540
even stronger than before.

01:29:11.540 --> 01:29:13.250
The Jin Dynasty struggling

01:29:13.250 --> 01:29:15.863
with constant attacks from a common enemy

01:29:15.863 --> 01:29:18.020
the Tatars of the steps recruited the help

01:29:18.020 --> 01:29:21.590
of the newfound Mongol force, which worked incredibly well.

01:29:21.590 --> 01:29:24.530
Genghis' army crushed the enemy Tatars

01:29:24.530 --> 01:29:25.790
and returned to their homeland

01:29:25.790 --> 01:29:28.040
of Mongolia after their victory.

01:29:28.040 --> 01:29:31.040
However, upon their return, Jamukha forces looked

01:29:31.040 --> 01:29:34.790
to seize the opportunity and attack the unsuspecting army.

01:29:34.790 --> 01:29:37.970
The campaign was a complete failure for Jamukha

01:29:37.970 --> 01:29:41.720
with his men being defeated after a series of three battles.

01:29:41.720 --> 01:29:44.090
While Jamukha was able to flee this conflict

01:29:44.090 --> 01:29:46.640
as well as success of efforts to capture him,

01:29:46.640 --> 01:29:48.680
he was eventually taken prisoner

01:29:48.680 --> 01:29:52.250
by Genghis after being betrayed by his own men.

01:29:52.250 --> 01:29:54.410
Taking pity on his childhood friend,

01:29:54.410 --> 01:29:56.480
Genghis offered him a chance to live

01:29:56.480 --> 01:29:58.580
and join his clan once again.

01:29:58.580 --> 01:30:01.850
Though Jamukha refused and asked to be put to death.

01:30:01.850 --> 01:30:05.150
Some accounts state Jamukha was executed honorably

01:30:05.150 --> 01:30:07.040
without spilling any blood

01:30:07.040 --> 01:30:09.470
and that he was suffocated to death in a carpet

01:30:09.470 --> 01:30:10.700
by the Khan's men,

01:30:10.700 --> 01:30:13.700
while others claim he was violently dismembered,

01:30:13.700 --> 01:30:16.250
what do we know for certain however is that Genghis

01:30:16.250 --> 01:30:19.340
would face no more opposition from his blood brother

01:30:19.340 --> 01:30:20.870
turned mortal enemy.

01:30:20.870 --> 01:30:24.320
Genghis had now taken control over a million people

01:30:24.320 --> 01:30:26.630
and was the sole ruler of the step

01:30:26.630 --> 01:30:28.730
after promptly subjugating the remaining

01:30:28.730 --> 01:30:30.830
smaller forces of Mongolia.

01:30:30.830 --> 01:30:34.460
That was not nearly enough however, for the famed ruler,

01:30:34.460 --> 01:30:37.220
he set his sights on the whole of China

01:30:37.220 --> 01:30:40.250
declaring that he was destined to take the land.

01:30:40.250 --> 01:30:42.350
The North was still ruled by the Jin

01:30:42.350 --> 01:30:44.720
while the south was still ruled by the Song

01:30:44.720 --> 01:30:46.490
though the first step for the Mongols

01:30:46.490 --> 01:30:48.500
was to conquer the Western Xia,

01:30:48.500 --> 01:30:50.720
which rested in the northwest of China

01:30:50.720 --> 01:30:53.300
directly between the Jin and Song.

01:30:53.300 --> 01:30:56.960
It was a strategic location to begin the major conquest from

01:30:56.960 --> 01:30:58.730
and was an important trade route

01:30:58.730 --> 01:31:00.710
that connected China to the west.

01:31:00.710 --> 01:31:03.230
In 1207, he launched his campaign

01:31:03.230 --> 01:31:05.930
and conquered the Western Xia with a relative ease

01:31:05.930 --> 01:31:07.790
over the course of two years.

01:31:07.790 --> 01:31:10.160
The small dynasty had tried to enlist the help

01:31:10.160 --> 01:31:13.490
of the Jin Dynasty while they were under attack.

01:31:13.490 --> 01:31:15.350
Though the Monarch Wanyan Yongji

01:31:15.350 --> 01:31:18.860
of Jin denied their request stating that the warring of two

01:31:18.860 --> 01:31:22.100
of their rivals was very advantageous for the Jin.

01:31:22.100 --> 01:31:25.340
With yet another major victory, Genghis was now able

01:31:25.340 --> 01:31:27.740
to fully focus on the Jin Dynasty.

01:31:27.740 --> 01:31:31.070
He attempted to send peace envoys over the wall to Jin,

01:31:31.070 --> 01:31:34.400
though the rightfully suspicious empire swiftly executed

01:31:34.400 --> 01:31:35.690
the assigned men.

01:31:35.690 --> 01:31:39.050
In 1211 and enraged Genghis and his cavalry men

01:31:39.050 --> 01:31:41.570
were able to breach the Great Wall of China

01:31:41.570 --> 01:31:44.870
and decimated the greatly outmatched encampments.

01:31:44.870 --> 01:31:46.970
A great number of towns were lost

01:31:46.970 --> 01:31:50.210
and many Jin soldiers defected the Genghis' army

01:31:50.210 --> 01:31:53.030
after witnessing his usual ruthlessness.

01:31:53.030 --> 01:31:57.170
By 1213, the Mongols had reached the capital of Zhongdu,

01:31:57.170 --> 01:32:00.560
which is modern day Beijing and utilized catapults

01:32:00.560 --> 01:32:03.800
and siege towers to take the city after a year of battle.

01:32:03.800 --> 01:32:06.980
They plunder the northern regions of the dynasty's land

01:32:06.980 --> 01:32:09.800
and continued taking great chunks of territory.

01:32:09.800 --> 01:32:13.220
However, in 1227, Genghis Khan died

01:32:13.220 --> 01:32:16.280
after struggling with the fever for a little over a week.

01:32:16.280 --> 01:32:18.680
The legacy Genghis Khan left on Earth

01:32:18.680 --> 01:32:20.540
is impossible to forget.

01:32:20.540 --> 01:32:23.810
Since his wartime tactics typically employed slaughtering

01:32:23.810 --> 01:32:27.020
every last person in a civilian population,

01:32:27.020 --> 01:32:29.330
it is estimated that he and his armies killed

01:32:29.330 --> 01:32:31.850
as many as 40 million people,

01:32:31.850 --> 01:32:35.060
more than Hitler and Stalin combined.

01:32:35.060 --> 01:32:38.450
At his time of death, he had fornicated with so many women

01:32:38.450 --> 01:32:42.020
along his campaigns that he fathered hundreds of children

01:32:42.020 --> 01:32:46.310
with some estimates showing potentially one to 2000.

01:32:46.310 --> 01:32:49.940
Today, one in 200 men are direct descendants

01:32:49.940 --> 01:32:53.150
of the terrifying sex crazed leader.

01:32:53.150 --> 01:32:56.000
The Mongols, however, did not slip out of power

01:32:56.000 --> 01:32:57.583
once their fierce leader died.

01:32:57.583 --> 01:33:01.400
Genghis was succeeded by his third son, Ogedei Khan,

01:33:01.400 --> 01:33:03.290
and they kept pushing forward.

01:33:03.290 --> 01:33:06.260
In the 1230s the Southern Song joined forces

01:33:06.260 --> 01:33:08.450
with the Mongols to defeat the common enemy

01:33:08.450 --> 01:33:10.040
of the Jin Dynasty,

01:33:10.040 --> 01:33:12.860
not realizing that this move would eventually lead

01:33:12.860 --> 01:33:14.510
to their own collapse.

01:33:14.510 --> 01:33:16.970
The Jin collapsed in 1234

01:33:16.970 --> 01:33:19.640
and so began the Mongols next campaign

01:33:19.640 --> 01:33:21.350
against the Southern Song.

01:33:21.350 --> 01:33:24.680
The invasion of the Song is split up into two stages.

01:33:24.680 --> 01:33:28.970
The first stage lasted from 1235 to 1248 AD

01:33:28.970 --> 01:33:31.580
though it was not as severe as one might expect

01:33:31.580 --> 01:33:34.250
with the Mongols only gaining relatively small

01:33:34.250 --> 01:33:36.620
northern pieces of Song territory,

01:33:36.620 --> 01:33:38.900
it ended in something of a stalemate

01:33:38.900 --> 01:33:41.960
with a ceasefire briefly halting the invasion.

01:33:41.960 --> 01:33:45.620
The second stage began in 1251 with the Khan election

01:33:45.620 --> 01:33:48.710
of Mongke, a grandson of Genghis'.

01:33:48.710 --> 01:33:52.130
He adopted a much more intense approach to the conquest

01:33:52.130 --> 01:33:53.360
of the Southern Song

01:33:53.360 --> 01:33:56.420
and gained significant ground not only in China,

01:33:56.420 --> 01:33:58.640
but in Iraq and Syria as well.

01:33:58.640 --> 01:34:01.580
This stage lasted until 1259

01:34:01.580 --> 01:34:04.370
and though they hadn't destroyed the Southern Song Empire

01:34:04.370 --> 01:34:07.160
quite yet, the tides turned when Mongke

01:34:07.160 --> 01:34:09.770
appointed his brother Kublai Khan.

01:34:09.770 --> 01:34:11.990
Recognizing geographic advantages

01:34:11.990 --> 01:34:15.500
that the Southern Song held Kublai Khan employed a series

01:34:15.500 --> 01:34:18.230
of innovative military strategies to adapt

01:34:18.230 --> 01:34:20.540
to southern China's difficult terrains.

01:34:20.540 --> 01:34:22.520
A significant achievement of the leader

01:34:22.520 --> 01:34:24.860
who would become Khan in 1264

01:34:24.860 --> 01:34:27.350
after a power struggle was the development

01:34:27.350 --> 01:34:29.600
of a powerful navy force

01:34:29.600 --> 01:34:32.630
that allowed the Mongols unprecedented navigation

01:34:32.630 --> 01:34:34.760
of China's many waterways.

01:34:34.760 --> 01:34:36.260
With the mix of both new

01:34:36.260 --> 01:34:39.590
and classic proven siege techniques established

01:34:39.590 --> 01:34:41.930
by his lineage, the Mongols were able

01:34:41.930 --> 01:34:45.923
to subdue the Southern Song Dynasty in 1279.

01:34:48.640 --> 01:34:51.390
(dramatic music)

01:34:53.450 --> 01:34:56.540
The Yuan Dynasty was the new dominant empire

01:34:56.540 --> 01:35:00.260
making Kublai Khan the first non-native to rule over China.

01:35:00.260 --> 01:35:02.000
As the result of a civil war,

01:35:02.000 --> 01:35:03.860
the Mongol Empire was by this point,

01:35:03.860 --> 01:35:05.900
divided into four Khanates.

01:35:05.900 --> 01:35:07.700
The Yuan Dynasty in China,

01:35:07.700 --> 01:35:09.650
the Golden Hordes in the northeast,

01:35:09.650 --> 01:35:11.960
the Ilkhanate in the southeast in Persia

01:35:11.960 --> 01:35:16.160
or modern day Iran and the Chagatai Khanate in Central Asia.

01:35:16.160 --> 01:35:19.400
Kublai Khan said his empire's capital is Khanbaliq,

01:35:19.400 --> 01:35:23.120
which is now in Beijing, China's current capital city.

01:35:23.120 --> 01:35:25.580
Just like his insatiable predecessors,

01:35:25.580 --> 01:35:29.240
the new great leader set his sights on further expansion.

01:35:29.240 --> 01:35:31.760
Vietnam had slipped away from Chinese control

01:35:31.760 --> 01:35:34.010
with the decline of the Tang Dynasty

01:35:34.010 --> 01:35:36.470
and the Yuan aimed to take it back.

01:35:36.470 --> 01:35:38.690
They also desired islands that belonged

01:35:38.690 --> 01:35:42.470
to modern day Indonesia as well as Japan and the East.

01:35:42.470 --> 01:35:45.050
They were largely unsuccessful however,

01:35:45.050 --> 01:35:48.380
with many battles ending in disastrous defeats,

01:35:48.380 --> 01:35:51.350
they failed to take control of any of these regions.

01:35:51.350 --> 01:35:53.210
It was clear that the Mongols needed

01:35:53.210 --> 01:35:56.240
to establish a stronger governmental base

01:35:56.240 --> 01:36:00.080
and so Kublai Khan established a caste system society

01:36:00.080 --> 01:36:01.520
with four tiers.

01:36:01.520 --> 01:36:03.470
Each ethnic group was ranked according

01:36:03.470 --> 01:36:05.300
to the dates in which they were defeated.

01:36:05.300 --> 01:36:07.490
The Mongols, of course, sat at the top

01:36:07.490 --> 01:36:10.160
of the list while other central Asian peoples

01:36:10.160 --> 01:36:11.450
were the second highest.

01:36:11.450 --> 01:36:13.670
Most of the empire's population belonged

01:36:13.670 --> 01:36:15.350
to the bottom two tiers

01:36:15.350 --> 01:36:17.600
with the Northern Chinese ranked third

01:36:17.600 --> 01:36:20.210
and the recently defeated Southern Chinese

01:36:20.210 --> 01:36:21.680
at the very bottom.

01:36:21.680 --> 01:36:23.750
Each class was given different rights

01:36:23.750 --> 01:36:26.300
with most of the real power residing at the top

01:36:26.300 --> 01:36:28.820
of the pyramid in the hands of the Mongols.

01:36:28.820 --> 01:36:31.160
Punishments for crime had varying levels

01:36:31.160 --> 01:36:33.680
of severity based on your ethnic class

01:36:33.680 --> 01:36:37.430
and the ethnic Chinese were not allowed to own weapons, dogs

01:36:37.430 --> 01:36:39.890
or eagles, just in case they may try

01:36:39.890 --> 01:36:41.990
to revolt against the empire.

01:36:41.990 --> 01:36:45.230
Despite the incredibly high levels of ethnic discrimination,

01:36:45.230 --> 01:36:48.110
the empire entered an age of prosperity.

01:36:48.110 --> 01:36:50.960
Trade increased as the Silk Road was stabilized

01:36:50.960 --> 01:36:52.370
and heavily utilized.

01:36:52.370 --> 01:36:55.130
Cities bloomed and Buddhist leaders were employed

01:36:55.130 --> 01:36:57.050
as Khan favored the religion.

01:36:57.050 --> 01:36:59.930
Kublai Khan also restored the Grand Canal,

01:36:59.930 --> 01:37:03.200
a waterway network that spans 2000 kilometers

01:37:03.200 --> 01:37:06.590
and links five incredibly important river basins of China,

01:37:06.590 --> 01:37:10.313
two being the storied Yangtze and Yellow Rivers.

01:37:11.180 --> 01:37:13.070
The themed Venetian merchant,

01:37:13.070 --> 01:37:17.300
Marco Polo lived in China for 17 years during the period

01:37:17.300 --> 01:37:19.670
and wrote all of the incredible inventions

01:37:19.670 --> 01:37:22.580
and ways of life in the Yuan Dynasty's China

01:37:22.580 --> 01:37:24.350
upon his return to Europe.

01:37:24.350 --> 01:37:27.830
What particularly fascinated him was the use of paper money,

01:37:27.830 --> 01:37:30.740
the use of coal as fuel, silk production

01:37:30.740 --> 01:37:32.990
and the intriguing sexual practices

01:37:32.990 --> 01:37:35.480
of the citizens under Mongol rule.

01:37:35.480 --> 01:37:37.580
Like all other dynasties and golden ages

01:37:37.580 --> 01:37:39.020
of days past however,

01:37:39.020 --> 01:37:41.960
the Mongol Empire did not last forever.

01:37:41.960 --> 01:37:45.170
Low tax revenues, corruption, inept leadership

01:37:45.170 --> 01:37:48.170
and failed military campaigns all contributed

01:37:48.170 --> 01:37:50.360
to the downfall of the Yuan Dynasty

01:37:50.360 --> 01:37:53.690
following the death of Kublai Khan in 1294.

01:37:53.690 --> 01:37:56.120
However, one of the most crippling factors

01:37:56.120 --> 01:37:59.630
was the plague epidemic of the 1330s.

01:37:59.630 --> 01:38:02.780
There is plenty of mystery surrounding the exact cause

01:38:02.780 --> 01:38:05.690
of the bubonic plague that would eventually ravage Europe

01:38:05.690 --> 01:38:08.000
killing a third of the continent in its wake,

01:38:08.000 --> 01:38:10.430
but what we do know is that it originated

01:38:10.430 --> 01:38:13.040
amongst Mongol soldiers in Crimea.

01:38:13.040 --> 01:38:15.680
China was the first country to suffer at the hands

01:38:15.680 --> 01:38:19.250
of the black plague after it was contracted by the soldiers

01:38:19.250 --> 01:38:22.340
and spread rapidly over the course of a four year span

01:38:22.340 --> 01:38:26.020
from 1331 to 1334.

01:38:26.020 --> 01:38:28.580
13 million died and it spread to the rest

01:38:28.580 --> 01:38:31.400
of the modern world through the Silk Road trading route.

01:38:31.400 --> 01:38:35.180
By the time the second surge came to China in the 1350s,

01:38:35.180 --> 01:38:37.820
the death toll only continued to grow.

01:38:37.820 --> 01:38:40.730
Though the exact figure is not known today.

01:38:40.730 --> 01:38:42.080
It was through all this time

01:38:42.080 --> 01:38:45.260
that a peasant rebellion called the Red Turbans began

01:38:45.260 --> 01:38:48.470
to gain traction in northern China, ignited by a series

01:38:48.470 --> 01:38:51.740
of epidemics, natural disasters, famines

01:38:51.740 --> 01:38:53.570
coinciding with all this hardship,

01:38:53.570 --> 01:38:56.420
the civilian founded resistance opposed the rule

01:38:56.420 --> 01:38:58.160
of the invasive Mongols.

01:38:58.160 --> 01:39:00.920
The Red Turbans were very skilled in battle

01:39:00.920 --> 01:39:04.880
under the leadership of former Buddhist monk, Zhu Yuanzhang,

01:39:04.880 --> 01:39:06.830
and were able to forcefully overthrow

01:39:06.830 --> 01:39:09.710
the Mongol empire by 1368.

01:39:09.710 --> 01:39:12.800
Although the Yuan had not even lasted a century at the helm

01:39:12.800 --> 01:39:16.760
of China, their legacy was incredibly influential.

01:39:16.760 --> 01:39:19.460
China was far more open to the western world.

01:39:19.460 --> 01:39:20.780
Trade had been improved

01:39:20.780 --> 01:39:23.000
and the empire was unified once again

01:39:23.000 --> 01:39:25.550
with great territorial gains to boot.

01:39:25.550 --> 01:39:27.260
Even today, Genghis Khan

01:39:27.260 --> 01:39:30.650
and Kublai Khan remain as two of the most prominent figures

01:39:30.650 --> 01:39:34.793
of Chinese history despite their non-Chinese ethnicity.

01:39:36.471 --> 01:39:39.054
(gentle music)

01:39:40.850 --> 01:39:45.230
After the fleeing of the final Yuan Emperor in 1368 AD,

01:39:45.230 --> 01:39:48.350
rebel leader Zhu Yuanzhang proclaimed himself emperor

01:39:48.350 --> 01:39:53.350
of the Ming Dynasty, which would last until 1644 AD.

01:39:53.540 --> 01:39:56.450
Ming would become one of the most powerful empires

01:39:56.450 --> 01:39:57.290
in the world.

01:39:57.290 --> 01:40:00.980
As Zhu Yuanzhang widely known as the Hongwu Emperor

01:40:00.980 --> 01:40:02.600
consolidated his power

01:40:02.600 --> 01:40:05.870
and amassed a standing army of over a million men.

01:40:05.870 --> 01:40:08.540
A military much larger than any European

01:40:08.540 --> 01:40:10.940
contemporaries were boasting.

01:40:10.940 --> 01:40:12.830
When the new emperor came into power,

01:40:12.830 --> 01:40:15.380
he declared Nanjing the capital city

01:40:15.380 --> 01:40:17.840
and a heavy emphasis was placed on the revival

01:40:17.840 --> 01:40:19.670
of traditional Han culture.

01:40:19.670 --> 01:40:23.540
Neo-Confucianism returned as the prominent school of thought

01:40:23.540 --> 01:40:26.750
and the arts blossomed in this newfound time of prosperity

01:40:26.750 --> 01:40:28.430
for the ethnic Chinese.

01:40:28.430 --> 01:40:31.527
One of the most famous historical novels of all time,

01:40:31.527 --> 01:40:33.650
"Romance of the Three Kingdoms,"

01:40:33.650 --> 01:40:36.020
which focused on the unstable later years

01:40:36.020 --> 01:40:39.290
of the Han Dynasty was written during this time.

01:40:39.290 --> 01:40:42.050
The Confucian civil service exams were brought back

01:40:42.050 --> 01:40:44.360
to ensure politicians earned their roles

01:40:44.360 --> 01:40:47.750
with merit and knowledge, and Mongol related names

01:40:47.750 --> 01:40:50.630
and garments were banned across the empire.

01:40:50.630 --> 01:40:53.720
Public service projects flourished at this time as well,

01:40:53.720 --> 01:40:55.730
a former peasant who himself suffered

01:40:55.730 --> 01:40:58.730
through intense famines and natural disasters,

01:40:58.730 --> 01:41:02.510
the Hongwu Emperor established vast irrigation systems

01:41:02.510 --> 01:41:05.390
in dikes with the aim of helping to improve the lives

01:41:05.390 --> 01:41:07.160
and crop yields of farmers.

01:41:07.160 --> 01:41:10.700
As a result, the economy boomed, trade routes were restored

01:41:10.700 --> 01:41:14.180
and expanded further, and the population grew massively.

01:41:14.180 --> 01:41:17.840
Under Hongwu's command that 10% of military personnel

01:41:17.840 --> 01:41:19.520
should be gunners,

01:41:19.520 --> 01:41:22.940
the Ming Dynasty heavily embraced the use of gunpowder

01:41:22.940 --> 01:41:27.140
and developed firearm prototypes and cannon batteries.

01:41:27.140 --> 01:41:28.400
This improvement allowed them

01:41:28.400 --> 01:41:30.800
to repel various invading forces

01:41:30.800 --> 01:41:33.080
such as the Mongol tribes in the north

01:41:33.080 --> 01:41:34.550
and maintain their status

01:41:34.550 --> 01:41:37.460
as one of the world's most powerful forces.

01:41:37.460 --> 01:41:41.180
It truly was a time of great innovation and transformation

01:41:41.180 --> 01:41:42.593
under the emperor's rule.

01:41:43.760 --> 01:41:46.790
Though there was a dark side to the Hongwu Emperor,

01:41:46.790 --> 01:41:50.090
he was incredibly paranoid about losing his grip on power

01:41:50.090 --> 01:41:53.900
and enacted a strict legal code that introduced all kinds

01:41:53.900 --> 01:41:56.690
of brutal executions to Chinese law.

01:41:56.690 --> 01:42:01.460
These included lingchi or the death by a thousand cuts

01:42:01.460 --> 01:42:03.320
where pieces of the body are slowly

01:42:03.320 --> 01:42:07.250
and gradually removed by a small knife as well as fleeing

01:42:07.250 --> 01:42:10.520
where the skin is continuously removed in a torturous

01:42:10.520 --> 01:42:13.250
fashion, massacres were carried out on those

01:42:13.250 --> 01:42:16.010
who oppose the emperor to ensure no rebellions

01:42:16.010 --> 01:42:19.340
or coups could form, fearing not just insurrections

01:42:19.340 --> 01:42:22.040
from within, but the Mongols in the north as well.

01:42:22.040 --> 01:42:25.940
Hongwu desired stronger borders to protect the empire.

01:42:25.940 --> 01:42:28.160
This important sentiment would be passed on

01:42:28.160 --> 01:42:29.750
for generations.

01:42:29.750 --> 01:42:32.150
Under the Ming, particularly during the reign

01:42:32.150 --> 01:42:37.150
of the Hongzhi Emperor who ruled from 1487 to 1505 AD,

01:42:37.250 --> 01:42:39.500
plenty of resources went towards building

01:42:39.500 --> 01:42:41.330
and maintaining the Great Wall.

01:42:41.330 --> 01:42:44.060
The construction under the Ming forms the most visible

01:42:44.060 --> 01:42:47.090
contemporary sections of the Great Wall today.

01:42:47.090 --> 01:42:50.300
The desire for strengthened borders was not the only trade

01:42:50.300 --> 01:42:53.000
passed on by the Empire's first ruler however,

01:42:53.000 --> 01:42:55.190
throughout the generations of Ming rulers

01:42:55.190 --> 01:42:57.890
were similarly power hungry and cruel.

01:42:57.890 --> 01:42:59.750
The last emperor of the dynasty,

01:42:59.750 --> 01:43:03.140
Chongzhen assumed the throne at just 16

01:43:03.140 --> 01:43:06.320
after his illiterate and possibly disabled brother,

01:43:06.320 --> 01:43:10.190
the Tianqi Emperor died in 1627.

01:43:10.190 --> 01:43:11.840
By the time he had taken office,

01:43:11.840 --> 01:43:14.690
the army was in a miserable state of disarray.

01:43:14.690 --> 01:43:17.660
The economy was in the gutter because of corruption, greed,

01:43:17.660 --> 01:43:20.240
and the self-preservation of emperors powers.

01:43:20.240 --> 01:43:23.180
Instead of a focus on building a greater nation.

01:43:23.180 --> 01:43:25.940
Enemies at every turn were destroying the empire

01:43:25.940 --> 01:43:28.430
and new rebellions aim to overthrow the Ming

01:43:28.430 --> 01:43:31.370
in a series of resistances aptly named

01:43:31.370 --> 01:43:33.890
the Late Ming Peasant Rebellions.

01:43:33.890 --> 01:43:36.950
The Ming Dynasty had lost the mandate of heaven.

01:43:36.950 --> 01:43:41.950
This era culminated in 1644 AD when the warlord Li Zicheng

01:43:41.960 --> 01:43:45.590
and his men marched on Beijing, prompting the Ming Emperor

01:43:45.590 --> 01:43:46.970
to hang himself.

01:43:46.970 --> 01:43:49.820
Zicheng immediately named himself emperor,

01:43:49.820 --> 01:43:51.970
claiming that he had the mandate of heaven.

01:43:54.449 --> 01:43:57.032
(gentle music)

01:43:59.685 --> 01:44:01.220
He was not the only one looking

01:44:01.220 --> 01:44:03.890
to take the crumbling Ming's power however,

01:44:03.890 --> 01:44:06.140
the Manchus of Northeast Asia

01:44:06.140 --> 01:44:08.180
who had been steadily growing their power

01:44:08.180 --> 01:44:11.120
throughout the Ming Dynasty and attacking the empire

01:44:11.120 --> 01:44:13.850
at every turn immediately claimed the throne

01:44:13.850 --> 01:44:15.980
and began the Qing Dynasty.

01:44:15.980 --> 01:44:20.180
This began China's second non-native dynasty proceeded only

01:44:20.180 --> 01:44:22.010
by the Mongol empire.

01:44:22.010 --> 01:44:24.440
Under the reign of the Shunzhi Emperor,

01:44:24.440 --> 01:44:26.480
all Chinese men were forced to adopt

01:44:26.480 --> 01:44:28.550
the Manchu Queue hairstyle

01:44:28.550 --> 01:44:31.070
where hair on the top of the scalp is grown long

01:44:31.070 --> 01:44:34.100
and braided while the rest of the head is shaved bald.

01:44:34.100 --> 01:44:36.260
Cutting your hair differently was seen as a sign

01:44:36.260 --> 01:44:38.510
of rebellion and the haircut would go on

01:44:38.510 --> 01:44:41.630
to become a cultural symbol of the Qing Dynasty.

01:44:41.630 --> 01:44:44.060
It also ensured at this time that over half

01:44:44.060 --> 01:44:47.690
of all high ranking government officials must be Manchu

01:44:47.690 --> 01:44:50.510
to preserve their people's power in the empire.

01:44:50.510 --> 01:44:54.707
After the Shunzhi Emperor's death of smallpox in 1661,

01:44:54.707 --> 01:44:58.820
the 61 year reign of the Kangxi Emperor began,

01:44:58.820 --> 01:45:02.510
which would be the longest of any leader in Chinese history.

01:45:02.510 --> 01:45:05.780
Despite his leanings towards a Neo-Confucianism,

01:45:05.780 --> 01:45:08.420
the emperor embraced multiculturalism

01:45:08.420 --> 01:45:11.840
and the presence of various religious identities in China.

01:45:11.840 --> 01:45:15.110
He went so far as to allow Jesuit missionaries

01:45:15.110 --> 01:45:17.510
to spread their beliefs across the nation,

01:45:17.510 --> 01:45:21.680
propagating the spread of Roman Catholicism in China.

01:45:21.680 --> 01:45:22.820
The main feats of his rule,

01:45:22.820 --> 01:45:26.450
however, were his many grand public work projects.

01:45:26.450 --> 01:45:29.390
The Grand Canal was repaired to make the transportation

01:45:29.390 --> 01:45:30.980
of food far easier

01:45:30.980 --> 01:45:33.680
and massive dredging projects protected farmers

01:45:33.680 --> 01:45:35.750
from the flooding of the Yangtze River.

01:45:35.750 --> 01:45:40.400
Prior to his death in 1722 Kangxi constantly worked day

01:45:40.400 --> 01:45:43.580
and night to stay updated on the happenings of the empire

01:45:43.580 --> 01:45:45.440
and plan further projects.

01:45:45.440 --> 01:45:48.440
Because of this, as well as as many major successes,

01:45:48.440 --> 01:45:51.470
he's generally recognized as one of the most competent

01:45:51.470 --> 01:45:54.050
and committed rulers in Chinese history.

01:45:54.050 --> 01:45:56.690
In the 18th century, commerce and the arts

01:45:56.690 --> 01:45:57.890
continued to thrive

01:45:57.890 --> 01:46:00.969
and prosper under Kangxi's successive rulers.

01:46:00.969 --> 01:46:05.513
Yongzheng, who ruled from 1722 to 1735

01:46:05.513 --> 01:46:10.513
and Qianlong, who ruled from 1735 to 1796.

01:46:10.520 --> 01:46:13.100
Their success, however, would not be continued

01:46:13.100 --> 01:46:15.413
as we moved into the 1800s.

01:46:17.408 --> 01:46:20.158
(dramatic music)

01:46:21.800 --> 01:46:24.650
The 19th century was truly an age of adventure

01:46:24.650 --> 01:46:26.330
for the merchants and travelers

01:46:26.330 --> 01:46:28.310
of the west financially burdened

01:46:28.310 --> 01:46:30.980
by their colonial failures in the Americas,

01:46:30.980 --> 01:46:33.440
Great Britain began searching for other avenues

01:46:33.440 --> 01:46:36.230
of resource extraction and financial gain.

01:46:36.230 --> 01:46:38.720
This led to an increased interest in China

01:46:38.720 --> 01:46:40.790
who were now well known for their products

01:46:40.790 --> 01:46:43.280
such as silk, tea and porcelain.

01:46:43.280 --> 01:46:44.540
The Chinese ruling class,

01:46:44.540 --> 01:46:47.330
however, was not so keen on the trade relationship

01:46:47.330 --> 01:46:48.860
desired by the British.

01:46:48.860 --> 01:46:51.170
Very much aware of the destabilization

01:46:51.170 --> 01:46:53.450
that could occur by opening up their empire

01:46:53.450 --> 01:46:56.600
to great imperial powers for the sake of trade,

01:46:56.600 --> 01:46:59.630
the Qing Dynasty restricted trade with foreigners

01:46:59.630 --> 01:47:02.960
and regulated internal transactions as they saw fit.

01:47:02.960 --> 01:47:05.930
They feared that an increased reliance on foreign trade

01:47:05.930 --> 01:47:08.450
would weaken the central authority as the people

01:47:08.450 --> 01:47:09.470
of China could become

01:47:09.470 --> 01:47:12.290
as economically reliant on Western rulers

01:47:12.290 --> 01:47:13.850
as they were on their own.

01:47:13.850 --> 01:47:16.895
They also did not want the Chinese culture to be eroded

01:47:16.895 --> 01:47:19.040
for the sake of Western prophets.

01:47:19.040 --> 01:47:22.040
Because of this, the Qing had previously established

01:47:22.040 --> 01:47:24.440
the Canton system, a set of rules

01:47:24.440 --> 01:47:27.170
and regulations to limit the economic influence

01:47:27.170 --> 01:47:28.640
of foreign merchants.

01:47:28.640 --> 01:47:30.980
Foreigners were only allowed to trade through the ports

01:47:30.980 --> 01:47:33.890
of Canton, and the regulations imposed on their trading

01:47:33.890 --> 01:47:35.300
were as follows.

01:47:35.300 --> 01:47:38.300
One, the Qing Dynasty restricted foreign trade

01:47:38.300 --> 01:47:39.830
during the winter months,

01:47:39.830 --> 01:47:42.590
two, foreigners visiting Canton were required

01:47:42.590 --> 01:47:46.490
to stay in designated areas, dubbed the foreign factories,

01:47:46.490 --> 01:47:48.530
and live under the supervision of a guild

01:47:48.530 --> 01:47:51.440
of Chinese merchants known as the Cohong.

01:47:51.440 --> 01:47:55.070
Three, Chinese citizens were barred from borrowing capital

01:47:55.070 --> 01:47:57.650
or seeking employment from foreign traders.

01:47:57.650 --> 01:48:00.830
Four Chinese citizens were not allowed to seek out trading

01:48:00.830 --> 01:48:03.140
or market information from foreigners.

01:48:03.140 --> 01:48:06.170
Five, foreign vessels arriving in Canton were required

01:48:06.170 --> 01:48:08.090
to anchor at Whampoa Roads,

01:48:08.090 --> 01:48:11.330
a designated anchorage area downstream from Canton

01:48:11.330 --> 01:48:14.630
and were subject to inspection from Chinese authorities.

01:48:14.630 --> 01:48:18.050
European merchants could not stand these restrictions

01:48:18.050 --> 01:48:20.450
as they inhibited their ability to trade freely

01:48:20.450 --> 01:48:22.490
and make profits after they had traveled

01:48:22.490 --> 01:48:23.750
all the way to China.

01:48:23.750 --> 01:48:26.300
The rules were seen as far too strict,

01:48:26.300 --> 01:48:29.570
and the result of this was a major spike in smuggling goods

01:48:29.570 --> 01:48:31.640
and piracy among foreigners.

01:48:31.640 --> 01:48:33.830
Despite this, the European desire

01:48:33.830 --> 01:48:36.350
for Chinese goods continue to increase.

01:48:36.350 --> 01:48:38.330
Tea alone accounted for 10%

01:48:38.330 --> 01:48:40.040
of the British government's revenue,

01:48:40.040 --> 01:48:41.960
and they were not going to back down

01:48:41.960 --> 01:48:45.830
from the potential goldmine of Chinese trade so easily.

01:48:45.830 --> 01:48:48.200
They needed leverage and they found it

01:48:48.200 --> 01:48:51.350
in the highly addictive narcotic that is opium.

01:48:51.350 --> 01:48:53.090
The East India Company,

01:48:53.090 --> 01:48:56.390
a British trading company had previously conquered regions

01:48:56.390 --> 01:49:00.350
of India and grew poppies for opium on the land.

01:49:00.350 --> 01:49:04.400
The Chinese desired opium for a number of medical, social,

01:49:04.400 --> 01:49:08.540
and recreational reasons making for a perfect trade-off

01:49:08.540 --> 01:49:10.430
between the East India Company

01:49:10.430 --> 01:49:13.550
and the Chinese, tea for drugs.

01:49:13.550 --> 01:49:16.730
The issue is that the Qing Dynasty recognized the health

01:49:16.730 --> 01:49:19.940
and social hazards of widespread opium use.

01:49:19.940 --> 01:49:23.960
Opium was illegal in China, as was the importation of it.

01:49:23.960 --> 01:49:26.480
A major uncontrolled importation

01:49:26.480 --> 01:49:29.750
by foreign powers was especially illegal.

01:49:29.750 --> 01:49:32.330
The traders were not concerned with this however,

01:49:32.330 --> 01:49:34.190
they set up shop along the borders

01:49:34.190 --> 01:49:37.220
and smuggled in copious amounts of opium for trade.

01:49:37.220 --> 01:49:40.610
The number of opium addicts in the country boomed.

01:49:40.610 --> 01:49:42.890
The economy was drained of its silver

01:49:42.890 --> 01:49:46.070
and the once impressive Chinese trade surplus

01:49:46.070 --> 01:49:47.660
was utterly destroyed.

01:49:47.660 --> 01:49:50.810
The Daoguang Emperor was met with numerous proposals

01:49:50.810 --> 01:49:54.560
to legalize and tax the drug, all of which he rejected.

01:49:54.560 --> 01:49:56.660
It was clear he needed to act swiftly

01:49:56.660 --> 01:49:59.240
to prevent any further decay of the empire.

01:49:59.240 --> 01:50:02.360
In 1839, he sent Chinese Viceroy

01:50:02.360 --> 01:50:05.420
and political philosopher Lin Zexu with the task

01:50:05.420 --> 01:50:07.790
of completely halting the trade of opium.

01:50:07.790 --> 01:50:11.240
Initially, Zexu wrote a letter to Queen Victoria stating

01:50:11.240 --> 01:50:14.510
that she had a moral responsibility to pull Britain out

01:50:14.510 --> 01:50:15.800
of the opium trade.

01:50:15.800 --> 01:50:18.260
Though the letter was never even read,

01:50:18.260 --> 01:50:21.770
Zexu was forced to resort to harsher punishments.

01:50:21.770 --> 01:50:25.010
By late January, he had organized a coastal defense

01:50:25.010 --> 01:50:27.890
in the province and begun arresting thousands

01:50:27.890 --> 01:50:30.290
of opium traders and users.

01:50:30.290 --> 01:50:33.770
By March, approximately 2.4 million pounds

01:50:33.770 --> 01:50:35.060
of opium were seized

01:50:35.060 --> 01:50:37.400
and set on fire as a public display

01:50:37.400 --> 01:50:39.050
of the government's determination

01:50:39.050 --> 01:50:43.610
to completely derail the trade and usage of opium in China.

01:50:43.610 --> 01:50:46.490
British merchants were bankrupted by the ordeal

01:50:46.490 --> 01:50:48.170
and tensions between the British

01:50:48.170 --> 01:50:50.450
and Chinese continued to escalate.

01:50:50.450 --> 01:50:53.330
Charles Elliot, a British diplomat in China

01:50:53.330 --> 01:50:57.080
was doing a poor job of mediation and things only got worse

01:50:57.080 --> 01:51:00.200
after two British sailors murdered a Chinese villager

01:51:00.200 --> 01:51:02.960
and faced no repercussions from Elliot

01:51:02.960 --> 01:51:04.550
or the British government.

01:51:04.550 --> 01:51:07.670
They refused to hand the men over to the Chinese authorities

01:51:07.670 --> 01:51:10.760
for execution, which enraged Zexu.

01:51:10.760 --> 01:51:12.890
The Viceroy cut off the food supplies

01:51:12.890 --> 01:51:15.350
to the British merchants, prompting the traitors

01:51:15.350 --> 01:51:16.910
to retreat to Hong Kong.

01:51:16.910 --> 01:51:19.610
On trips to retrieve supplies from the Chinese ports

01:51:19.610 --> 01:51:22.370
for the merchants, a naval battle between British

01:51:22.370 --> 01:51:25.160
and Chinese ships erupted marking the start

01:51:25.160 --> 01:51:27.170
of the first opium war.

01:51:27.170 --> 01:51:29.630
The fighting continued with the Chinese suffering

01:51:29.630 --> 01:51:32.450
continuous major losses at the hands of the Britt's,

01:51:32.450 --> 01:51:35.120
vastly superior naval forces.

01:51:35.120 --> 01:51:38.630
In 1840, Lin Zexu was dismissed by the emperor

01:51:38.630 --> 01:51:40.490
because of his continued failures

01:51:40.490 --> 01:51:42.830
in stopping the conflict's escalation

01:51:42.830 --> 01:51:46.910
and was replaced by the new acting viceroy, Qishan.

01:51:46.910 --> 01:51:49.880
Qishan was tasked with negotiating a peace treaty

01:51:49.880 --> 01:51:52.430
with the British and reached a tentative agreement

01:51:52.430 --> 01:51:54.740
with Elliot in 1841.

01:51:54.740 --> 01:51:57.560
It was titled the Convention of Chuenpi,

01:51:57.560 --> 01:52:00.440
and stated that the Qing Empire would pay the British

01:52:00.440 --> 01:52:02.210
6 million pounds

01:52:02.210 --> 01:52:06.470
and handover Hong Kong in order for the war to end.

01:52:06.470 --> 01:52:09.140
Both Elliot and Qishan were happy,

01:52:09.140 --> 01:52:10.940
but there was a major issue.

01:52:10.940 --> 01:52:12.920
Qishan had not asked for approval

01:52:12.920 --> 01:52:15.920
from the Qing Imperial Court and agreed to the terms

01:52:15.920 --> 01:52:18.590
without any input from his superiors.

01:52:18.590 --> 01:52:20.300
The emperor was furious

01:52:20.300 --> 01:52:23.960
and had Qishan arrested while Elliot's superiors fired him

01:52:23.960 --> 01:52:27.200
from his role as they saw the deal to be insufficient.

01:52:27.200 --> 01:52:29.900
Many British soldiers and diplomats wanted the war

01:52:29.900 --> 01:52:33.200
to continue and did not wanna let up so easily.

01:52:33.200 --> 01:52:35.330
After the British continued to push further

01:52:35.330 --> 01:52:38.540
and further into China, it became increasingly clear

01:52:38.540 --> 01:52:41.330
to the Chinese that they could resist no longer.

01:52:41.330 --> 01:52:43.670
Thousands of Chinese soldiers had been killed

01:52:43.670 --> 01:52:45.770
in battle over the course of the conflict,

01:52:45.770 --> 01:52:47.240
which was astoundingly high

01:52:47.240 --> 01:52:49.250
compared to the British casualty count,

01:52:49.250 --> 01:52:51.040
which was less than 100.

01:52:51.040 --> 01:52:54.740
In 1842, the Treaty of Nanjing was signed,

01:52:54.740 --> 01:52:57.770
which included the following significant rulings.

01:52:57.770 --> 01:52:59.840
One, the Chinese government would pay

01:52:59.840 --> 01:53:02.030
20 million pounds to Britain.

01:53:02.030 --> 01:53:04.550
Two, the island of Hong Kong would be seated

01:53:04.550 --> 01:53:05.570
to the British.

01:53:05.570 --> 01:53:08.030
Three, the Cohong would be dissolved.

01:53:08.030 --> 01:53:11.000
Four, five ports would be open for trade.

01:53:11.000 --> 01:53:13.340
Five, British citizens were subject

01:53:13.340 --> 01:53:16.460
to British law in China, not Chinese.

01:53:16.460 --> 01:53:18.650
This marked the first of several treaties

01:53:18.650 --> 01:53:22.550
that would be dubbed the unequal treaties by the Chinese.

01:53:22.550 --> 01:53:25.823
Agreements that humiliated and exploited the empire.

01:53:27.480 --> 01:53:30.230
(dramatic music)

01:53:32.120 --> 01:53:35.180
In the aftermath, there was a major internal threat

01:53:35.180 --> 01:53:37.100
to the Qing Dynasty brewing.

01:53:37.100 --> 01:53:40.910
The first opium war had damaged the economy and banditry

01:53:40.910 --> 01:53:42.770
and rebellion were on the rise.

01:53:42.770 --> 01:53:45.800
One rebellion, the Taiping Rebellion would mark one

01:53:45.800 --> 01:53:48.860
of the bloodiest conflicts in the history of the world

01:53:48.860 --> 01:53:52.130
with somewhere between 20 to 30 million dying

01:53:52.130 --> 01:53:53.240
in the Civil War.

01:53:53.240 --> 01:53:57.500
But where exactly did the Taiping Rebellion come from?

01:53:57.500 --> 01:53:59.690
Years ago in 1814,

01:53:59.690 --> 01:54:02.150
a boy named Hong Xiuquan was born

01:54:02.150 --> 01:54:04.640
in the Huadu district of Guangzhou.

01:54:04.640 --> 01:54:07.070
Hong was said to be incredibly intelligent

01:54:07.070 --> 01:54:09.800
and dreamed of academia from a young age.

01:54:09.800 --> 01:54:12.710
However, the Imperial examinations required

01:54:12.710 --> 01:54:16.370
to earn spots in academies and high paying government jobs

01:54:16.370 --> 01:54:19.250
were incredibly difficult and competitive.

01:54:19.250 --> 01:54:21.920
Millions of applicants would take the tests

01:54:21.920 --> 01:54:25.310
and while Hong did exceedingly well on preliminary tests,

01:54:25.310 --> 01:54:27.470
he was unable to seize a position

01:54:27.470 --> 01:54:29.900
after his first attempt on the exams.

01:54:29.900 --> 01:54:32.660
He returned to his small village to become a school teacher

01:54:32.660 --> 01:54:33.920
and save up some money.

01:54:33.920 --> 01:54:37.490
Though he remained transfixed on his dreams of academia

01:54:37.490 --> 01:54:39.050
and governmental work,

01:54:39.050 --> 01:54:41.330
he continued to sink his money into returns

01:54:41.330 --> 01:54:42.770
to the city of Guangzhou

01:54:42.770 --> 01:54:44.960
for the purpose of writing the exams.

01:54:44.960 --> 01:54:47.030
Though after his third failure,

01:54:47.030 --> 01:54:49.850
Hong was driven into a mental breakdown.

01:54:49.850 --> 01:54:51.800
His family believed he would die

01:54:51.800 --> 01:54:54.260
as Hong was completely delirious.

01:54:54.260 --> 01:54:56.390
At this time, Hong dreamed of heaven

01:54:56.390 --> 01:54:58.910
and discovered a heavenly family.

01:54:58.910 --> 01:55:01.940
Hong's Heavenly Father dawned a long golden beard

01:55:01.940 --> 01:55:03.650
and black dragon robe,

01:55:03.650 --> 01:55:06.020
which were worn by the emperors of China.

01:55:06.020 --> 01:55:08.660
He complained that the men under his reign were worshiping

01:55:08.660 --> 01:55:11.990
demons instead of himself and gave Hong a sword

01:55:11.990 --> 01:55:15.380
to fight against the demons destroying the heavenly realm.

01:55:15.380 --> 01:55:18.200
Hong and his heavenly brother led a spiritual army

01:55:18.200 --> 01:55:20.750
that vanquished the demons and saved heaven.

01:55:20.750 --> 01:55:24.110
Hong also reported seeing Confucius being punished

01:55:24.110 --> 01:55:25.280
by the heavenly Father

01:55:25.280 --> 01:55:27.620
for leading the Chinese people astray.

01:55:27.620 --> 01:55:29.420
The dream stuck with Hong,

01:55:29.420 --> 01:55:34.100
who reportedly became far more careful, friendly, and open.

01:55:34.100 --> 01:55:36.260
After teaching for several more years,

01:55:36.260 --> 01:55:39.530
Hong decided he would take the Imperial examinations

01:55:39.530 --> 01:55:42.920
and met the same fate he had the first three times.

01:55:42.920 --> 01:55:44.600
After this final failure,

01:55:44.600 --> 01:55:47.060
a cousin of Hong suggested that he re-examine

01:55:47.060 --> 01:55:50.360
a Christian pamphlet that he had been given by a missionary

01:55:50.360 --> 01:55:52.610
after filling the exams years ago

01:55:52.610 --> 01:55:55.610
for the second time when he was 22.

01:55:55.610 --> 01:55:58.040
After reading the material, Hong decided

01:55:58.040 --> 01:56:00.500
that Christianity was directly connected

01:56:00.500 --> 01:56:02.630
with the fever dreams he had suffered

01:56:02.630 --> 01:56:05.990
in his state of delirium during his mental breakdown.

01:56:05.990 --> 01:56:08.240
The heavenly Father must have been God

01:56:08.240 --> 01:56:09.890
and the brother he fought alongside

01:56:09.890 --> 01:56:13.370
with these spiritual army must have been Jesus Christ.

01:56:13.370 --> 01:56:17.030
Hong believed that he was the literal son of God

01:56:17.030 --> 01:56:19.100
and a brother of Jesus.

01:56:19.100 --> 01:56:20.750
He destroyed all the Buddhist

01:56:20.750 --> 01:56:22.970
and Confucianist imagery in his home

01:56:22.970 --> 01:56:26.000
and began vehemently preaching Christianity.

01:56:26.000 --> 01:56:28.730
He was eventually banned from teaching in his own village

01:56:28.730 --> 01:56:32.510
after toppling various religious and philosophical monuments

01:56:32.510 --> 01:56:34.550
and idols that he did not believe

01:56:34.550 --> 01:56:36.590
aligned with his Christian faith.

01:56:36.590 --> 01:56:40.610
In 1844, Hong and a handful of relatives, schoolmates

01:56:40.610 --> 01:56:42.260
and followers left the country

01:56:42.260 --> 01:56:45.080
to preach the religious doctrine across China.

01:56:45.080 --> 01:56:47.840
After the group steadily grew, Hong became the leader

01:56:47.840 --> 01:56:51.680
of a religious movement called the God Worshiping Society,

01:56:51.680 --> 01:56:54.110
which attracted thousands of converts.

01:56:54.110 --> 01:56:57.800
Many peasant followers adored the anti-government rhetoric

01:56:57.800 --> 01:57:00.290
preached by the society as Hong believed

01:57:00.290 --> 01:57:02.630
that the demon infested Qing Dynasty

01:57:02.630 --> 01:57:04.100
needed to be destroyed.

01:57:04.100 --> 01:57:06.470
Hong had created his own adaptation

01:57:06.470 --> 01:57:09.800
of the Bible called the authorized Taiping version

01:57:09.800 --> 01:57:11.300
of the Bible, and explained

01:57:11.300 --> 01:57:13.880
that the religion had existed long ago,

01:57:13.880 --> 01:57:16.700
but was wiped out by the evil Confucius

01:57:16.700 --> 01:57:18.710
and the Imperial system.

01:57:18.710 --> 01:57:22.820
By 1850, Hong had tens of thousands of followers

01:57:22.820 --> 01:57:25.220
with modern size estimates ranging all the way

01:57:25.220 --> 01:57:27.170
to 30,000 members.

01:57:27.170 --> 01:57:30.200
The Qing Dynasty feared the steadily growing cult

01:57:30.200 --> 01:57:32.660
and decided to take action against it.

01:57:32.660 --> 01:57:34.460
In the province of Guangxi,

01:57:34.460 --> 01:57:36.620
many peasants who had suffered through famine

01:57:36.620 --> 01:57:39.590
and economic struggles were drawn to Hong's movement,

01:57:39.590 --> 01:57:43.010
but were ordered not to join by imperial troops.

01:57:43.010 --> 01:57:45.740
Any new converts were to be executed.

01:57:45.740 --> 01:57:48.050
By January, 1851,

01:57:48.050 --> 01:57:51.290
the God Worshiping Society quickly militarized

01:57:51.290 --> 01:57:55.010
and battled against 7,000 Qing soldiers.

01:57:55.010 --> 01:57:57.110
It is said that the command of the cult

01:57:57.110 --> 01:58:00.650
was shockingly organized compared to prior rebellions,

01:58:00.650 --> 01:58:03.380
and after the bloodshed of over a thousand men,

01:58:03.380 --> 01:58:05.930
Hong soldiers emerged victorious.

01:58:05.930 --> 01:58:09.020
Hong then declared the founding of the heavenly kingdom

01:58:09.020 --> 01:58:10.850
of transcendent peace,

01:58:10.850 --> 01:58:14.030
his movement that would hopefully topple the Qing Dynasty.

01:58:14.030 --> 01:58:17.390
The movement marched from city to city to recruit members,

01:58:17.390 --> 01:58:19.820
and it grew at an unprecedented rate.

01:58:19.820 --> 01:58:23.000
Both men and women in many major settlements were prepared

01:58:23.000 --> 01:58:24.800
to die for the cause.

01:58:24.800 --> 01:58:28.790
In March of the Year 1853, one of Hong's forces,

01:58:28.790 --> 01:58:32.480
which consisted of over 500,000 soldiers

01:58:32.480 --> 01:58:35.240
launched a siege on the city of Nanjing,

01:58:35.240 --> 01:58:39.653
which was defended by somewhere between 40,000 to 80,000

01:58:39.653 --> 01:58:41.180
Qing soldiers.

01:58:41.180 --> 01:58:43.670
After 13 days of a ruthless battle,

01:58:43.670 --> 01:58:46.610
including major bombings, spy missions,

01:58:46.610 --> 01:58:49.940
and major violent charges, Hong soldiers

01:58:49.940 --> 01:58:53.000
or the Taiping Rebellion took the city

01:58:53.000 --> 01:58:55.610
and declared it as their capital city.

01:58:55.610 --> 01:58:58.400
The movement's ruling was divided between kings

01:58:58.400 --> 01:59:01.550
who all claimed they could communicate with God himself.

01:59:01.550 --> 01:59:04.400
The most notable of these was Yang Xiuqing,

01:59:04.400 --> 01:59:06.410
who served as King of the East.

01:59:06.410 --> 01:59:08.450
He served as Hong's right hand man

01:59:08.450 --> 01:59:11.930
and implemented reforms such as the outlawing of opium

01:59:11.930 --> 01:59:15.230
and the social equalization of both men and women.

01:59:15.230 --> 01:59:17.240
The two genders were separated.

01:59:17.240 --> 01:59:19.670
That is outside of Hong's Harem.

01:59:19.670 --> 01:59:22.550
European travelers observing the new Christian kingdom

01:59:22.550 --> 01:59:26.390
in South China, much of which was now under Taiping control,

01:59:26.390 --> 01:59:29.990
were astounded by how rigid the rules of the land were.

01:59:29.990 --> 01:59:33.590
Sex, drinking, gambling, tobacco, prostitution,

01:59:33.590 --> 01:59:36.290
and dancing were all outlawed

01:59:36.290 --> 01:59:40.010
and disobeying these rules resulted in the death penalty.

01:59:40.010 --> 01:59:42.557
Despite the distrust between the Qing Dynasty

01:59:42.557 --> 01:59:45.860
and Western powers as a result of the opium wars,

01:59:45.860 --> 01:59:49.010
the Taiping rebellion was not supported by Europe.

01:59:49.010 --> 01:59:51.020
Hong had reached out to the Western powers

01:59:51.020 --> 01:59:53.930
for assistance since they now shared a religion.

01:59:53.930 --> 01:59:55.700
The United States viewed Hong

01:59:55.700 --> 01:59:58.130
and the rebellion quite favorably

01:59:58.130 --> 02:00:01.550
and prepared to recognize their independence from the Qing.

02:00:01.550 --> 02:00:04.610
Though nothing solidified, Britain, France

02:00:04.610 --> 02:00:07.370
and the Americans eventually supported the Qing

02:00:07.370 --> 02:00:08.960
for a handful of reasons

02:00:08.960 --> 02:00:11.210
and came to see the Taiping Rebellion

02:00:11.210 --> 02:00:14.240
as a diametrically oppositional force

02:00:14.240 --> 02:00:16.280
rather than brothers in Christ.

02:00:16.280 --> 02:00:18.650
The British wanted their payments that were outlawed

02:00:18.650 --> 02:00:21.200
and the treaty signed during the opium wars,

02:00:21.200 --> 02:00:23.990
which the Taiping peasant rebellion obviously

02:00:23.990 --> 02:00:25.490
would not be paying.

02:00:25.490 --> 02:00:29.150
Furthermore, Hong's claims of being directly related to God

02:00:29.150 --> 02:00:33.710
and Jesus were seen as disrespectful by many Europeans,

02:00:33.710 --> 02:00:35.690
and they distrusted the leader's agenda

02:00:35.690 --> 02:00:37.760
given how much violence and death occurred

02:00:37.760 --> 02:00:39.890
with each move of the Taiping.

02:00:39.890 --> 02:00:42.980
A particularly disturbing example of this violence

02:00:42.980 --> 02:00:47.980
occurred in 1856 in an event called the Tianjing incident.

02:00:48.500 --> 02:00:51.320
Yang Xiuqing overstepped his political bounds

02:00:51.320 --> 02:00:53.780
when he began claiming that he was the true vessel

02:00:53.780 --> 02:00:55.040
for God's word.

02:00:55.040 --> 02:00:58.130
He had been gaining traction as a leader in his own right

02:00:58.130 --> 02:01:00.590
and wanted to seize power over the kingdom

02:01:00.590 --> 02:01:03.470
and had amassed thousands of followers himself.

02:01:03.470 --> 02:01:05.780
He continuously pretended to be possessed

02:01:05.780 --> 02:01:07.040
by the heavenly Father

02:01:07.040 --> 02:01:09.590
and accused Hong of being an imposter.

02:01:09.590 --> 02:01:12.290
Considering such rhetoric to be treasonous,

02:01:12.290 --> 02:01:15.380
Hong did not take kindly to Yang's actions

02:01:15.380 --> 02:01:18.710
and dispatch the King of the West, as well as a handful

02:01:18.710 --> 02:01:21.860
of generals to exterminate the King of the East,

02:01:21.860 --> 02:01:25.070
as well as all of his followers and relatives.

02:01:25.070 --> 02:01:27.920
They stormed Yang's palace and killed him,

02:01:27.920 --> 02:01:29.930
then slaughtered all of his family members

02:01:29.930 --> 02:01:32.210
before moving on to his followers.

02:01:32.210 --> 02:01:34.490
Many were tricked into entering the palace

02:01:34.490 --> 02:01:36.980
and were systematically executed.

02:01:36.980 --> 02:01:38.960
Over the course of three months,

02:01:38.960 --> 02:01:42.470
Hong's men would kill 27,000 civilians

02:01:42.470 --> 02:01:44.450
in the mass executions.

02:01:44.450 --> 02:01:47.210
The cult was becoming increasingly more dangerous

02:01:47.210 --> 02:01:49.160
under Hong's tyrannical rule

02:01:49.160 --> 02:01:52.250
and reports of indiscriminate slaughterings of civilians

02:01:52.250 --> 02:01:56.000
with each new land they took became more and more common.

02:01:56.000 --> 02:01:59.240
However, the Qing Dynasty's attention needed to be divided

02:01:59.240 --> 02:02:01.040
between the Taiping rebellion

02:02:01.040 --> 02:02:03.140
and the western European powers.

02:02:03.140 --> 02:02:06.173
A second opium war was on the way.

02:02:07.612 --> 02:02:10.029
(calm music)

02:02:12.380 --> 02:02:15.620
Despite the overwhelming victory of the first opium war,

02:02:15.620 --> 02:02:18.830
Western powers such as the British government, France

02:02:18.830 --> 02:02:21.530
and the United States were still not satisfied

02:02:21.530 --> 02:02:23.270
with their earnings in China.

02:02:23.270 --> 02:02:26.480
They wanted opium to be wholly legalized in China

02:02:26.480 --> 02:02:28.640
and were not content with the results of the Treaty

02:02:28.640 --> 02:02:32.120
of Nanjing and other treaties signed in later years.

02:02:32.120 --> 02:02:34.010
The British were looking for an excuse

02:02:34.010 --> 02:02:37.310
to extend their trading rights and reinvade China,

02:02:37.310 --> 02:02:41.300
and in October of 1856, the opportunity came.

02:02:41.300 --> 02:02:43.880
The Chinese crew of a British registered ship

02:02:43.880 --> 02:02:46.070
called the Arrow were arrested

02:02:46.070 --> 02:02:49.100
by the Chinese officials in Canton on suspicion

02:02:49.100 --> 02:02:50.360
of being pirates.

02:02:50.360 --> 02:02:52.370
The captain of the ship, a Brit by the name

02:02:52.370 --> 02:02:55.670
of Thomas Kennedy, was aboard in nearby ship at the time

02:02:55.670 --> 02:02:58.490
and reported that he saw the British flag being lowered

02:02:58.490 --> 02:03:01.160
by the Chinese Marines during the ordeal.

02:03:01.160 --> 02:03:03.320
Furious British diplomats demanded

02:03:03.320 --> 02:03:05.720
that an apology be issued immediately

02:03:05.720 --> 02:03:08.750
and that the 12 arrested crew members be released.

02:03:08.750 --> 02:03:11.420
Much to their surprise, the new Viceroy

02:03:11.420 --> 02:03:14.720
Ye Mingchen only released nine of the 12,

02:03:14.720 --> 02:03:16.910
refusing to let the other three go.

02:03:16.910 --> 02:03:19.160
Within the month, a bombardment of Canton

02:03:19.160 --> 02:03:22.820
by the British began with a powerful army firing a shot

02:03:22.820 --> 02:03:24.770
at the poorly protected city.

02:03:24.770 --> 02:03:26.330
In their efforts to fight back,

02:03:26.330 --> 02:03:28.610
the Chinese attacked American ships,

02:03:28.610 --> 02:03:31.340
which drew yet another powerful nation in

02:03:31.340 --> 02:03:33.020
on the fight against the Qing.

02:03:33.020 --> 02:03:37.010
Ye Mingchen offered a bounty for every British had taken,

02:03:37.010 --> 02:03:38.870
but it was of little use.

02:03:38.870 --> 02:03:42.080
After blasting holes in the flimsy city walls,

02:03:42.080 --> 02:03:45.830
skirmishes broke out between the Western and Chinese troops.

02:03:45.830 --> 02:03:47.870
As the attackers entered Canton,

02:03:47.870 --> 02:03:50.240
the American flag was planted on the residence

02:03:50.240 --> 02:03:52.580
of Ye Mingchen by the US console

02:03:52.580 --> 02:03:54.740
as a symbol of their dominance.

02:03:54.740 --> 02:03:57.560
After negotiations to cease fighting failed,

02:03:57.560 --> 02:03:59.540
the British struck even harder

02:03:59.540 --> 02:04:03.260
with over 20 Chinese ships being destroyed in November.

02:04:03.260 --> 02:04:04.400
Though the United States

02:04:04.400 --> 02:04:07.340
and Russia were both disinterested in formal alliances

02:04:07.340 --> 02:04:09.560
with the British against the Chinese,

02:04:09.560 --> 02:04:13.280
the French joined their fight against China in late 1857.

02:04:13.280 --> 02:04:14.900
Their official excuse for joining

02:04:14.900 --> 02:04:18.200
or casus belli, was the Chinese execution

02:04:18.200 --> 02:04:21.230
of a French missionary, Auguste Chapdelaine,

02:04:21.230 --> 02:04:23.420
who was accused of plotting insurrection

02:04:23.420 --> 02:04:26.420
in a region foreigners were not supposed to be in.

02:04:26.420 --> 02:04:29.330
He refused to pay a bribe to the arresting officials,

02:04:29.330 --> 02:04:31.940
and as a result was sentenced to death,

02:04:31.940 --> 02:04:35.450
the missionary had been beaten 100 times on the cheek,

02:04:35.450 --> 02:04:37.670
causing his teeth to be knocked out.

02:04:37.670 --> 02:04:40.550
His jaw was completely lacerated by this

02:04:40.550 --> 02:04:42.500
and his face was destroyed.

02:04:42.500 --> 02:04:45.260
He was then placed in a tiny iron cage,

02:04:45.260 --> 02:04:47.120
which hung at the gate of the jail.

02:04:47.120 --> 02:04:49.190
His death was by suffocation.

02:04:49.190 --> 02:04:51.200
As the Chinese removed the wooden plank

02:04:51.200 --> 02:04:54.020
he stood on one by one, which strained the muscles

02:04:54.020 --> 02:04:56.060
of his neck until he died.

02:04:56.060 --> 02:04:57.950
Chinese children hurled stones

02:04:57.950 --> 02:05:01.160
at Chapdelaine's decapitated head until it toppled

02:05:01.160 --> 02:05:04.340
to the ground and was eaten by stray dogs.

02:05:04.340 --> 02:05:07.670
On January 1st, 1858, the combined British

02:05:07.670 --> 02:05:09.830
and French forces cruised the victory

02:05:09.830 --> 02:05:12.050
after a joint attack on Canton

02:05:12.050 --> 02:05:14.870
and captured Ye Mingchen as their prisoner.

02:05:14.870 --> 02:05:17.900
The Western power suffered only 15 casualties.

02:05:17.900 --> 02:05:20.510
While somewhere between 200 to 650

02:05:20.510 --> 02:05:23.960
of the hemmed-in militarily inferior Chinese

02:05:23.960 --> 02:05:25.430
were killed in action.

02:05:25.430 --> 02:05:28.280
Viceroy Ye Mingchen was exiled to India

02:05:28.280 --> 02:05:30.410
where he starved himself to death.

02:05:30.410 --> 02:05:33.890
Utterly humiliated, the Chinese were forced to negotiate

02:05:33.890 --> 02:05:34.880
once again.

02:05:34.880 --> 02:05:36.710
An alliance was formed at this time

02:05:36.710 --> 02:05:40.340
between Great Britain, France, the United States and Russia.

02:05:40.340 --> 02:05:43.670
So each respective global power benefited greatly

02:05:43.670 --> 02:05:46.520
from their new deal, the Treaty of Tianjin.

02:05:46.520 --> 02:05:48.230
The new treaty stated that one,

02:05:48.230 --> 02:05:49.670
all four countries had the right

02:05:49.670 --> 02:05:51.830
to establish embassies in Beijing,

02:05:51.830 --> 02:05:54.110
which was close to foreigners at the time.

02:05:54.110 --> 02:05:57.620
Two, more Chinese ports would be opened for foreign trade.

02:05:57.620 --> 02:05:59.660
Three, free travel would be established

02:05:59.660 --> 02:06:02.480
along the Yangtze River for all foreign ships,

02:06:02.480 --> 02:06:05.750
four, free travel in mainland China would be established

02:06:05.750 --> 02:06:07.340
as a right for foreigners.

02:06:07.340 --> 02:06:10.760
Five, China would pay millions of taels of silver

02:06:10.760 --> 02:06:12.950
to both Britain and France.

02:06:12.950 --> 02:06:15.260
Shortly after this disastrous treaty

02:06:15.260 --> 02:06:17.150
for the Chinese was agreed to,

02:06:17.150 --> 02:06:19.760
ministers urge the Xianfeng Emperor

02:06:19.760 --> 02:06:23.000
to resist against the western powers once again.

02:06:23.000 --> 02:06:24.770
The emperor decided he was going

02:06:24.770 --> 02:06:26.750
to deny the four country's ability

02:06:26.750 --> 02:06:29.330
to set up foreign litigations in Beijing,

02:06:29.330 --> 02:06:31.490
and the alliance caught wind of this.

02:06:31.490 --> 02:06:33.800
Once again, the war was on.

02:06:33.800 --> 02:06:36.650
Three battles were fought at the Taku Forts.

02:06:36.650 --> 02:06:38.060
The battles were fought there

02:06:38.060 --> 02:06:40.250
as the forts were in a strategic position

02:06:40.250 --> 02:06:42.320
that allowed access to Beijing.

02:06:42.320 --> 02:06:43.730
After split losses

02:06:43.730 --> 02:06:46.610
and hundreds of deaths scattered amongst both sides,

02:06:46.610 --> 02:06:50.390
the Western forces eventually emerged victorious once again.

02:06:50.390 --> 02:06:52.970
They pushed into Beijing with the British troops

02:06:52.970 --> 02:06:55.940
burning down the Xianfeng Emperor's summer palace

02:06:55.940 --> 02:06:57.560
when they arrived at the city.

02:06:57.560 --> 02:06:59.450
The old palace is said to have burnt

02:06:59.450 --> 02:07:01.580
for three days and three nights.

02:07:01.580 --> 02:07:04.340
The Qing army was rendered useless by this point,

02:07:04.340 --> 02:07:06.200
so the emperor fled the capital,

02:07:06.200 --> 02:07:09.830
leaving his brother Prince Gong behind a negotiate peace

02:07:09.830 --> 02:07:11.300
with Britain and France.

02:07:11.300 --> 02:07:14.030
A new treaty was reached in 1860,

02:07:14.030 --> 02:07:15.950
which amongst other concessions,

02:07:15.950 --> 02:07:18.290
such as major payments to the Western powers

02:07:18.290 --> 02:07:21.050
and freedom of religion for Christians contained

02:07:21.050 --> 02:07:23.600
the final blow for the Chinese empire.

02:07:23.600 --> 02:07:25.970
The legalization of opium.

02:07:25.970 --> 02:07:29.510
The massive defeats in the two successive opium wars marked

02:07:29.510 --> 02:07:32.210
the beginning of the end for the Qing Dynasty.

02:07:32.210 --> 02:07:36.230
The era is known today as the century of humiliation.

02:07:36.230 --> 02:07:38.750
The days of being cut off from the western world

02:07:38.750 --> 02:07:39.650
were long gone,

02:07:39.650 --> 02:07:42.863
and a stretch of great instability was about to begin.

02:07:43.907 --> 02:07:46.657
(dramatic music)

02:07:49.820 --> 02:07:52.730
All this time, Hong and the Taiping Rebellion

02:07:52.730 --> 02:07:54.500
had not yet subsided.

02:07:54.500 --> 02:07:56.510
More cities had been taken over the course

02:07:56.510 --> 02:07:58.280
of the second opium war,

02:07:58.280 --> 02:08:00.110
while the Qing were thinly stretched,

02:08:00.110 --> 02:08:03.080
fighting against vastly superior powers.

02:08:03.080 --> 02:08:05.510
It was around this time that the Qing rulers

02:08:05.510 --> 02:08:07.520
sided with regional warlords

02:08:07.520 --> 02:08:12.350
or the new armies that oppose the expanding Taiping Kingdom.

02:08:12.350 --> 02:08:15.620
Western countries also began to oppose the Taiping

02:08:15.620 --> 02:08:17.870
as the cult had begun attacking regions

02:08:17.870 --> 02:08:20.210
with important treating ports for foreigners.

02:08:20.210 --> 02:08:22.910
The Brits and Americans supplied the struggling Qing

02:08:22.910 --> 02:08:25.640
with weaponry and training, and thus a fresh

02:08:25.640 --> 02:08:27.680
and prepared Qing army was able

02:08:27.680 --> 02:08:30.740
to launch a major offensive against the Taiping.

02:08:30.740 --> 02:08:32.600
The Qing adopted the vicious

02:08:32.600 --> 02:08:34.490
and savage military techniques

02:08:34.490 --> 02:08:38.420
of the Taiping Rebellion burning entire towns to the ground

02:08:38.420 --> 02:08:40.850
and executing civilians and mass.

02:08:40.850 --> 02:08:42.470
Famine and plagues began

02:08:42.470 --> 02:08:45.140
as each side destroyed an unfathomable amount

02:08:45.140 --> 02:08:46.880
of crops and settlements.

02:08:46.880 --> 02:08:49.820
Hundreds of cities were entirely destroyed.

02:08:49.820 --> 02:08:51.470
Their citizens murdered.

02:08:51.470 --> 02:08:54.140
Some Taiping citizens and besieged cities

02:08:54.140 --> 02:08:57.110
resorted to cannibalism and selling human flesh

02:08:57.110 --> 02:08:59.210
because the famines were so bad.

02:08:59.210 --> 02:09:01.790
The Taiping were pushed further and further back

02:09:01.790 --> 02:09:03.920
losing much of their land in Southern China

02:09:03.920 --> 02:09:06.680
until only the capital of Nanjing remained.

02:09:06.680 --> 02:09:09.920
The Qing had the Taiping kingdom completely surrounded,

02:09:09.920 --> 02:09:12.650
and many began to starve within the city limits

02:09:12.650 --> 02:09:15.590
as the Qing forces ruin the supply lines.

02:09:15.590 --> 02:09:17.180
It was simply a matter of time

02:09:17.180 --> 02:09:19.310
before they were completely defeated.

02:09:19.310 --> 02:09:22.370
So Hong's officials urged him to evacuate the city

02:09:22.370 --> 02:09:24.710
to regroup and establish a new plan

02:09:24.710 --> 02:09:27.320
to fight against the renewed Qing forces.

02:09:27.320 --> 02:09:30.170
However, Hong truly believed the Taiping

02:09:30.170 --> 02:09:33.380
had got on their side and that they could not be defeated

02:09:33.380 --> 02:09:35.990
so long as they were his chosen people.

02:09:35.990 --> 02:09:38.510
After the city continued to deteriorate

02:09:38.510 --> 02:09:40.190
multiple push pull battles

02:09:40.190 --> 02:09:42.590
with his increasingly desperate advisors

02:09:42.590 --> 02:09:45.470
finally convinced Hong to leave the palace.

02:09:45.470 --> 02:09:47.120
Hong addressed his followers

02:09:47.120 --> 02:09:50.030
and stated that they would survive off of manna

02:09:50.030 --> 02:09:51.980
that God would send from heaven.

02:09:51.980 --> 02:09:54.380
Manna was an edible substance in the Bible

02:09:54.380 --> 02:09:56.390
that God provided for the Israelites

02:09:56.390 --> 02:09:58.130
during their travels in the desert,

02:09:58.130 --> 02:10:00.620
and Hong believed the divinity would offer the same

02:10:00.620 --> 02:10:04.130
substance and abundance for him and his followers.

02:10:04.130 --> 02:10:07.550
They began ingesting weeds, believing them to be manna,

02:10:07.550 --> 02:10:12.200
resulting in Hong's death of food poisoning in June of 1864.

02:10:12.200 --> 02:10:15.770
The Qing army finally marched into the city of Nanjing

02:10:15.770 --> 02:10:18.620
and killed all the remaining Taiping leaders.

02:10:18.620 --> 02:10:20.420
Though they were not finished there,

02:10:20.420 --> 02:10:23.390
many of Hong's followers were executed in house

02:10:23.390 --> 02:10:26.420
by house massacres at the hands of the Qing,

02:10:26.420 --> 02:10:28.040
while thousands of others resorted

02:10:28.040 --> 02:10:30.740
to burning themselves in mass suicides.

02:10:30.740 --> 02:10:32.870
On July 30th of the same year,

02:10:32.870 --> 02:10:36.110
the Qing forces located Hong Xiuquan's body

02:10:36.110 --> 02:10:38.240
and removed it from its burial place,

02:10:38.240 --> 02:10:41.570
wanting to punish the crazed leader for eternity

02:10:41.570 --> 02:10:43.760
and ensure that his body would never have

02:10:43.760 --> 02:10:45.260
a final resting place.

02:10:45.260 --> 02:10:48.380
They cut off his head and cremated the remains.

02:10:48.380 --> 02:10:51.140
Hong's ashes were then blasted out of a cannon

02:10:51.140 --> 02:10:54.710
so that they would be dispersed without any organization.

02:10:54.710 --> 02:10:56.840
After tens of millions of death,

02:10:56.840 --> 02:10:59.450
most of which were due to plague and famine,

02:10:59.450 --> 02:11:03.050
the war had been definitively won by the Qing Dynasty

02:11:03.050 --> 02:11:04.670
and they believed once again

02:11:04.670 --> 02:11:07.250
that they could hold onto their power in China.

02:11:07.250 --> 02:11:10.013
This belief, however, was misguiding.

02:11:11.691 --> 02:11:14.274
(gentle music)

02:11:16.700 --> 02:11:19.490
Corruption ran rampant in the unstable years

02:11:19.490 --> 02:11:21.230
following the Opium wars,

02:11:21.230 --> 02:11:24.563
and the Qing Dynasty lacked strong central leadership.

02:11:25.700 --> 02:11:29.180
To the east of China, grew an increasingly modernized Japan

02:11:29.180 --> 02:11:32.090
who was grappling with the effects of Western intrusions

02:11:32.090 --> 02:11:33.770
far better than the Qing.

02:11:33.770 --> 02:11:37.190
Under Emperor Meiji, Japan was expanding their territory

02:11:37.190 --> 02:11:40.040
with a rapidly strengthening military

02:11:40.040 --> 02:11:42.020
and set their sights on Korea

02:11:42.020 --> 02:11:44.360
even though the nation had been under China's grasp

02:11:44.360 --> 02:11:45.500
for centuries.

02:11:45.500 --> 02:11:49.130
In 1875, Korea was forced to sign a treaty

02:11:49.130 --> 02:11:51.230
that opened up their ports to foreigners

02:11:51.230 --> 02:11:53.840
with a heavy focus on Japanese trade.

02:11:53.840 --> 02:11:56.030
This effectively depleted the Chinese

02:11:56.030 --> 02:11:57.620
of their power in the region.

02:11:57.620 --> 02:11:59.600
As the Koreans were forced to declare

02:11:59.600 --> 02:12:03.140
their foreign relations as independent from the Qing.

02:12:03.140 --> 02:12:06.890
Both the Qing and the Japanese stationed troops in Korea,

02:12:06.890 --> 02:12:08.960
though there was no direct conflict,

02:12:08.960 --> 02:12:11.540
both sides forces were momentarily pulled

02:12:11.540 --> 02:12:13.430
after a series of treaties.

02:12:13.430 --> 02:12:16.370
The peace, however, did not last for very long.

02:12:16.370 --> 02:12:19.910
Tensions continued to rise over the next two decades

02:12:19.910 --> 02:12:22.580
with troops moving about until the two empires

02:12:22.580 --> 02:12:25.733
reached a boiling point in 1894.

02:12:26.810 --> 02:12:29.660
A series of coups and assassinations in Korea

02:12:29.660 --> 02:12:32.540
broke the convention that initially held the peace.

02:12:32.540 --> 02:12:35.510
And on August 1st war was officially declared

02:12:35.510 --> 02:12:39.050
between the Qing Empire and the Empire of Japan.

02:12:39.050 --> 02:12:42.050
Though the Chinese had four times as many troops

02:12:42.050 --> 02:12:45.560
as the Japanese, they were not as well prepared.

02:12:45.560 --> 02:12:49.280
Once again, the Japanese empire had done a much better job

02:12:49.280 --> 02:12:53.570
of modernizing and their troops were far more capable.

02:12:53.570 --> 02:12:55.460
The Chinese had, by this point,

02:12:55.460 --> 02:12:58.310
purchased plenty of modern military equipment.

02:12:58.310 --> 02:13:01.310
Though they were poorly trained and disorganized,

02:13:01.310 --> 02:13:04.640
the Japanese pushed the Chinese back time and time again

02:13:04.640 --> 02:13:08.270
in a series of devastating losses for the Qing troops.

02:13:08.270 --> 02:13:11.630
The navy nor the foot soldiers were any match

02:13:11.630 --> 02:13:13.850
for the Japanese.

02:13:13.850 --> 02:13:16.490
By the early spring of 1895,

02:13:16.490 --> 02:13:19.850
the Japanese had successfully invaded both Manchuria

02:13:19.850 --> 02:13:22.190
as well as the province of Shandong.

02:13:22.190 --> 02:13:25.340
The Chinese were defeated and the Treaty of Shimonoseki

02:13:25.340 --> 02:13:27.470
was signed on April 17th.

02:13:27.470 --> 02:13:30.200
It stated that China must cede Taiwan,

02:13:30.200 --> 02:13:32.630
recognized the independence of Korea

02:13:32.630 --> 02:13:35.960
and pay a massive sum of taels to Japan.

02:13:35.960 --> 02:13:38.660
Just like that the Qing Dynasty had suffered

02:13:38.660 --> 02:13:42.320
yet another major defeat that tacked onto the century

02:13:42.320 --> 02:13:43.733
of humiliation.

02:13:45.641 --> 02:13:49.040
(gentle music)

02:13:49.040 --> 02:13:51.170
In the aftermath of the Opium Wars,

02:13:51.170 --> 02:13:54.650
the Taiping Rebellion, the first Sino-Japanese war,

02:13:54.650 --> 02:13:58.130
and lastly, the Boxer Rebellion of 1900

02:13:58.130 --> 02:14:02.270
of violent anti foreigner movement run by a secret society,

02:14:02.270 --> 02:14:05.540
the Qing Dynasty was in a complete state of disarray.

02:14:05.540 --> 02:14:08.000
Other rebellions broke out across the empire

02:14:08.000 --> 02:14:11.150
as many people had lost faith in the Qing Dynasty's ability

02:14:11.150 --> 02:14:13.970
to maintain China's power in a rapidly

02:14:13.970 --> 02:14:16.070
industrializing modern world.

02:14:16.070 --> 02:14:19.910
In 1910, there were 285 rebellions

02:14:19.910 --> 02:14:21.800
in the calendar year alone.

02:14:21.800 --> 02:14:24.620
However, most were spearheaded by peasants

02:14:24.620 --> 02:14:25.670
who had little direction

02:14:25.670 --> 02:14:29.570
in terms of what exactly the new China should look like.

02:14:29.570 --> 02:14:32.060
One movement stood out from the rest of the pack,

02:14:32.060 --> 02:14:34.220
the Revolutionary Alliance.

02:14:34.220 --> 02:14:38.330
Dr. Sun Yat-sen, a former physician turned revolutionary,

02:14:38.330 --> 02:14:41.840
had founded the group and amassed 10,000 followers

02:14:41.840 --> 02:14:45.620
by the year 1911, many of which were well-educated

02:14:45.620 --> 02:14:47.300
and had studied abroad.

02:14:47.300 --> 02:14:49.790
The aim to radicalize Qing soldiers

02:14:49.790 --> 02:14:51.710
to fight against the dynasty

02:14:51.710 --> 02:14:54.680
and successfully continued to grow in the shadows.

02:14:54.680 --> 02:14:56.960
(rifles booming)

02:14:56.960 --> 02:14:59.360
The Revolutionary alliance spread their rhetoric

02:14:59.360 --> 02:15:02.420
through fake book clubs and other such harmless things

02:15:02.420 --> 02:15:04.040
and would simply dissolve the groups

02:15:04.040 --> 02:15:06.065
if the authorities investigated.

02:15:06.065 --> 02:15:09.020
(rifles booming)

02:15:09.020 --> 02:15:12.140
Many soldiers across China were radicalized

02:15:12.140 --> 02:15:14.510
and ready to turn against the Qing.

02:15:14.510 --> 02:15:18.650
On October 11th, 1911, the first attack was launched,

02:15:18.650 --> 02:15:21.740
turned members of the new army stationed in Wuchang,

02:15:21.740 --> 02:15:24.290
attacked a Viceroy's place of residence

02:15:24.290 --> 02:15:27.050
and took command of the city after he fled.

02:15:27.050 --> 02:15:30.470
500 Manchu soldiers were killed in the process

02:15:30.470 --> 02:15:32.900
and another 300 were captured.

02:15:32.900 --> 02:15:35.810
The ammunition depots and mint were now under control

02:15:35.810 --> 02:15:39.410
of the mutiny, and so a military government was formed.

02:15:39.410 --> 02:15:42.740
However, the rebels did not yet have central leadership.

02:15:42.740 --> 02:15:46.820
As Dr. Sun Yat-sen was not even in China at the time.

02:15:46.820 --> 02:15:50.300
He was making the rounds in the West, lobbying for American,

02:15:50.300 --> 02:15:53.060
British and French support and funds

02:15:53.060 --> 02:15:55.040
and requesting that they stop assisting

02:15:55.040 --> 02:15:57.110
the Qing Dynasty financially.

02:15:57.110 --> 02:15:58.550
After securing the leadership

02:15:58.550 --> 02:16:01.610
of a high ranking officer named Li Yuanhong,

02:16:01.610 --> 02:16:03.980
the mutant years conquest continued.

02:16:03.980 --> 02:16:05.600
Two more cities were taken

02:16:05.600 --> 02:16:08.420
and the threat that they would take the whole Hubei province

02:16:08.420 --> 02:16:10.340
was becoming very real.

02:16:10.340 --> 02:16:12.650
The Qing needed to respond fast

02:16:12.650 --> 02:16:16.250
and urged a retired Viceroy by the name of Yuan Shikai

02:16:16.250 --> 02:16:19.850
to take control of the situation and stop the rebellion.

02:16:19.850 --> 02:16:22.430
While he pondered whether or not he should accept,

02:16:22.430 --> 02:16:24.440
the rebellion grew and grew.

02:16:24.440 --> 02:16:27.860
Qing political figures and their families were massacred.

02:16:27.860 --> 02:16:30.260
Their army supply lines were blocked

02:16:30.260 --> 02:16:33.110
and the rebellion gained more and more land.

02:16:33.110 --> 02:16:35.870
After Li Yuanhong finally accepted,

02:16:35.870 --> 02:16:37.640
he was appointed as Prime Minister

02:16:37.640 --> 02:16:39.950
on the 1st of November, 1911,

02:16:39.950 --> 02:16:43.160
and began negotiations with the revolutionaries.

02:16:43.160 --> 02:16:45.260
Shortly after, Sun Yat-sen,

02:16:45.260 --> 02:16:47.660
the founder of the Revolutionary Alliance,

02:16:47.660 --> 02:16:50.180
returned from his diplomatic travels

02:16:50.180 --> 02:16:51.650
and was elected the president

02:16:51.650 --> 02:16:54.050
of the provisional Republican government.

02:16:54.050 --> 02:16:57.740
The center of Yat-sen's newly declared Republic of China,

02:16:57.740 --> 02:16:59.660
was based in the city of Nanjing,

02:16:59.660 --> 02:17:01.700
which they had recently captured.

02:17:01.700 --> 02:17:04.670
The Qing Dynasty were all but defeated.

02:17:04.670 --> 02:17:08.720
Their plan was a classic example of too little, too late,

02:17:08.720 --> 02:17:11.060
and as a result, the royal family

02:17:11.060 --> 02:17:15.260
and emperor abdicated the throne in early 1912.

02:17:15.260 --> 02:17:18.110
This major change was not like the power struggles

02:17:18.110 --> 02:17:21.890
between rivaling families and warlords of days gone by

02:17:21.890 --> 02:17:25.610
with the Qing dynasties usurping by the Republic of China,

02:17:25.610 --> 02:17:28.370
the dynastic cycle of China ended.

02:17:28.370 --> 02:17:32.120
Thousands of years of dynasties had come to a close

02:17:32.120 --> 02:17:35.723
as China moved in a new direction in the modern age.

02:17:37.802 --> 02:17:40.552
(dramatic music)

02:17:41.840 --> 02:17:45.140
Dr. Sun Yat-sen handed the presidency of the Republic

02:17:45.140 --> 02:17:48.770
over to Yuan Shikai as part of their prior negotiations

02:17:48.770 --> 02:17:51.020
that included that Yuan would seize the title

02:17:51.020 --> 02:17:52.820
of the newly established reign,

02:17:52.820 --> 02:17:56.150
should he convince the emperor of Qing to abdicate.

02:17:56.150 --> 02:17:58.700
Sun Yat-sen had no problem with this deal

02:17:58.700 --> 02:18:01.880
so long as it meant that the Qing Dynasty would end.

02:18:01.880 --> 02:18:06.410
Unfortunately, just a few short years later, in late 1915,

02:18:06.410 --> 02:18:08.750
the politically ambitious Yuan Shikai

02:18:08.750 --> 02:18:12.080
decided that he wanted more than just the presidency,

02:18:12.080 --> 02:18:14.360
he wanted to be an emperor.

02:18:14.360 --> 02:18:17.540
He declared himself as the emperor of China,

02:18:17.540 --> 02:18:19.730
a decision that displeased many.

02:18:19.730 --> 02:18:22.190
The people did not want more of the same,

02:18:22.190 --> 02:18:25.040
and yet another emperor would be exactly that.

02:18:25.040 --> 02:18:27.680
He was almost immediately abdicated

02:18:27.680 --> 02:18:31.280
being removed from power in March of 1916.

02:18:31.280 --> 02:18:33.410
Though before that could happen,

02:18:33.410 --> 02:18:35.960
he died just three months later in June

02:18:35.960 --> 02:18:38.330
and left behind an unstable republic

02:18:38.330 --> 02:18:40.700
without a consolidated central government,

02:18:40.700 --> 02:18:44.180
all because of his selfish desire to restore the monarchy

02:18:44.180 --> 02:18:46.040
and rule as an emperor.

02:18:46.040 --> 02:18:49.730
What ensued was a period known as the warlord era,

02:18:49.730 --> 02:18:54.410
which lasted from 1916, all the way until 1928.

02:18:54.410 --> 02:18:56.210
Because so many political forces

02:18:56.210 --> 02:18:59.720
and regional warlords refused to follow Yuan Shikai,

02:18:59.720 --> 02:19:01.940
China was severely fragmented.

02:19:01.940 --> 02:19:05.210
One look at a map of all the divided militaries demonstrates

02:19:05.210 --> 02:19:08.360
the governmental disaster that had been brought on

02:19:08.360 --> 02:19:10.370
by the Republic's first president.

02:19:10.370 --> 02:19:12.770
The future held great uncertainty,

02:19:12.770 --> 02:19:15.050
though some men still held on to hope.

02:19:15.050 --> 02:19:19.340
One of those men was the arch revolutionary Sun Yat-sen.

02:19:19.340 --> 02:19:21.860
He established a new revolutionary government

02:19:21.860 --> 02:19:24.830
in the south of China with the aim of reestablishing

02:19:24.830 --> 02:19:28.190
a consolidated power under the Republic of China.

02:19:28.190 --> 02:19:31.310
His new movement was now called the Kuomintang

02:19:31.310 --> 02:19:33.290
or KMT for short

02:19:33.290 --> 02:19:36.860
and aimed to consolidate power under the Republic of China.

02:19:36.860 --> 02:19:40.070
Another major future political power was brewing in China

02:19:40.070 --> 02:19:41.870
during this period as well.

02:19:41.870 --> 02:19:45.260
The May Fourth Movement, a patriotic, intellectual,

02:19:45.260 --> 02:19:49.479
and political revolutionary movement that lasted from 1917

02:19:49.479 --> 02:19:54.380
to 1921 had led to an increase in Marxist ideologies

02:19:54.380 --> 02:19:57.290
and the creation of the Chinese Communist Party,

02:19:57.290 --> 02:19:59.690
or simply the CCP.

02:19:59.690 --> 02:20:03.440
Though these two parties formed an alliance in 1922

02:20:03.440 --> 02:20:06.020
with both sides aiming to end the regionalism

02:20:06.020 --> 02:20:07.310
plaguing the nation,

02:20:07.310 --> 02:20:09.440
they would go on to fight against each other

02:20:09.440 --> 02:20:11.270
just a small handful of years

02:20:11.270 --> 02:20:13.940
in the bloody Chinese civil war.

02:20:13.940 --> 02:20:18.470
After Sun Yat-sen's untimely death of cancer in 1925,

02:20:18.470 --> 02:20:21.860
a power vacuum was created within this new movement

02:20:21.860 --> 02:20:24.890
and every man for himself contest ensued

02:20:24.890 --> 02:20:26.570
to seize control occurred

02:20:26.570 --> 02:20:29.570
and resulted in general and rising political power

02:20:29.570 --> 02:20:32.240
to Chiang Kai-shek taking the reigns.

02:20:32.240 --> 02:20:35.390
The general aimed to unify the fragmented fractions

02:20:35.390 --> 02:20:38.480
of the warlord era and consolidate power

02:20:38.480 --> 02:20:41.540
and wanted to tame the rising Communist party as well,

02:20:41.540 --> 02:20:44.120
believing them to be a threat to the government's future

02:20:44.120 --> 02:20:47.450
because of their associations with peasant rebellions.

02:20:47.450 --> 02:20:51.230
After the KMT was successful in beating back the warlords

02:20:51.230 --> 02:20:54.080
and reclaiming major cities across China,

02:20:54.080 --> 02:20:57.680
the CCP no longer served an immediate purpose to them.

02:20:57.680 --> 02:21:01.550
Instead, they stood in the way of Chiang Kai-shek's KMT

02:21:01.550 --> 02:21:04.460
and consolidated unified China.

02:21:04.460 --> 02:21:07.010
After uncovering a plot to overthrow him,

02:21:07.010 --> 02:21:11.150
Kai-shek began violently suppressing communist organizers.

02:21:11.150 --> 02:21:14.690
A famous example of this was the Shanghai Massacre

02:21:14.690 --> 02:21:17.390
in which thousands of communists, leftists

02:21:17.390 --> 02:21:20.030
and Shanghai Labor Union militia members

02:21:20.030 --> 02:21:23.420
were purged in the name of securing China's future.

02:21:23.420 --> 02:21:26.480
When the struggling CCP was trying to plot a course

02:21:26.480 --> 02:21:29.060
of action in the aftermath of the massacre,

02:21:29.060 --> 02:21:32.840
leaders Li Lisan and Mao Zedong held differing opinions

02:21:32.840 --> 02:21:34.970
on the future of communism in China.

02:21:34.970 --> 02:21:38.690
Li advocated for staying put in metropolitan areas

02:21:38.690 --> 02:21:40.970
and refused the idea of retreat.

02:21:40.970 --> 02:21:44.000
While Mao felt that a focus on the rural peasantry

02:21:44.000 --> 02:21:47.390
was the true soul of communism and that they should regroup

02:21:47.390 --> 02:21:50.120
to establish themselves as a formidable force

02:21:50.120 --> 02:21:51.770
against the KMT.

02:21:51.770 --> 02:21:54.560
Mao's plan prevailed, and in the coming years,

02:21:54.560 --> 02:21:56.930
he was able to piece together his revolution

02:21:56.930 --> 02:21:58.850
in the remote regions of China

02:21:58.850 --> 02:22:03.320
where the far more powerful KMT did not have full control.

02:22:03.320 --> 02:22:06.920
This conflict, however, was not simply a Chinese problem.

02:22:06.920 --> 02:22:10.400
The USSR supported Li and Mao in this endeavor

02:22:10.400 --> 02:22:13.400
as they too were attempting to build a global empire

02:22:13.400 --> 02:22:15.020
of communist nations.

02:22:15.020 --> 02:22:17.900
It was at this time in the 1930s as well

02:22:17.900 --> 02:22:21.320
that the imperialist driven Japanese began moving

02:22:21.320 --> 02:22:24.830
into mainland China to expand their influence.

02:22:24.830 --> 02:22:27.680
The invasion of Manchuria in the northeast of China

02:22:27.680 --> 02:22:31.100
marked a new age of Japanese imperialism in China

02:22:31.100 --> 02:22:33.920
and would steadily swell until exploding

02:22:33.920 --> 02:22:37.700
into a full fledged official war a few years later.

02:22:37.700 --> 02:22:40.280
That war had not yet begun however,

02:22:40.280 --> 02:22:42.440
and the result of the invasion of Manchuria

02:22:42.440 --> 02:22:44.720
was that the nationalist KMT

02:22:44.720 --> 02:22:47.510
needed to divide their attention between the Civil War

02:22:47.510 --> 02:22:51.560
with the CCP as well as the now threatening Japan

02:22:51.560 --> 02:22:54.620
and temporarily cease their military campaign

02:22:54.620 --> 02:22:56.420
against the communists.

02:22:56.420 --> 02:22:58.910
They launched their fourth encirclement campaign

02:22:58.910 --> 02:23:02.900
to annihilate the remaining CCP members in 1932.

02:23:02.900 --> 02:23:05.900
Though the Red Army was able to tactically retreat

02:23:05.900 --> 02:23:09.020
and avoid extermination after the first few battles,

02:23:09.020 --> 02:23:12.110
Japan continued to push inward in the northeast,

02:23:12.110 --> 02:23:15.770
which stretched the KMT's manpower and resources thin,

02:23:15.770 --> 02:23:17.630
allowing the Guerrilla communists

02:23:17.630 --> 02:23:20.660
to gain ground against their vulnerable opponents.

02:23:20.660 --> 02:23:24.080
Mao was not ashamed of his numerous tactical retreats,

02:23:24.080 --> 02:23:25.847
but incredibly proud of his Red Army

02:23:25.847 --> 02:23:27.680
and their guerrilla tactics,

02:23:27.680 --> 02:23:31.040
stating that the guerrilla versus standing army dynamic

02:23:31.040 --> 02:23:35.000
was a necessary one between the oppressed and the oppressor.

02:23:35.000 --> 02:23:37.520
He recognized that they were an inferior force

02:23:37.520 --> 02:23:40.100
in terms of sheer strength and would need to adopt

02:23:40.100 --> 02:23:43.580
a hit and run mentality to fight against the KMT.

02:23:43.580 --> 02:23:46.400
He put a heavy emphasis on maintaining the good favor

02:23:46.400 --> 02:23:50.390
of the civilian population as well as such as necessary

02:23:50.390 --> 02:23:54.260
to grow in a revolution against powerful government forces

02:23:54.260 --> 02:23:56.270
such as the nationalists.

02:23:56.270 --> 02:24:00.050
In 1934, after signing a treaty with the Japanese

02:24:00.050 --> 02:24:02.690
that allowed for full focus on the communists,

02:24:02.690 --> 02:24:05.990
though relations with Germany were not ideal for China,

02:24:05.990 --> 02:24:09.020
given the European country's racial arrogance,

02:24:09.020 --> 02:24:11.150
they accepted the help of a Nazi general

02:24:11.150 --> 02:24:12.890
named Hans von Seeckt.

02:24:12.890 --> 02:24:15.380
Hans enacted massive encirclement

02:24:15.380 --> 02:24:18.500
and a scorched earth policy against the communists,

02:24:18.500 --> 02:24:21.380
a strategy that includes destroying everything

02:24:21.380 --> 02:24:23.540
that allows the enemy to wage war

02:24:23.540 --> 02:24:26.240
such as crops and other resources.

02:24:26.240 --> 02:24:29.240
He believed that this would draw the weakened CCP

02:24:29.240 --> 02:24:31.940
out into the open where they could be swiftly defeated

02:24:31.940 --> 02:24:35.690
without the ability to ambush or surprise the KMT.

02:24:35.690 --> 02:24:38.930
It worked, with the communist suffering major defeats

02:24:38.930 --> 02:24:41.570
at the hands of the strengthened nationalists

02:24:41.570 --> 02:24:44.120
who would put together their largest army yet

02:24:44.120 --> 02:24:45.440
for this operation.

02:24:45.440 --> 02:24:47.900
This spurred a major tactical retreat

02:24:47.900 --> 02:24:49.700
known as the Long March,

02:24:49.700 --> 02:24:52.850
which would cover 10,000 kilometers over the course

02:24:52.850 --> 02:24:56.990
of 13 months with the CCP's goal being to reestablish

02:24:56.990 --> 02:25:00.440
their base in northwestern China instead of the southeast.

02:25:00.440 --> 02:25:04.730
90,000 soldiers and 20,000 civilians began the trek

02:25:04.730 --> 02:25:09.730
in September of 1934 and were subjected to 15 major battles,

02:25:10.010 --> 02:25:13.340
constant skirmishes, starvation, disease,

02:25:13.340 --> 02:25:15.470
and harsh weather along the way.

02:25:15.470 --> 02:25:20.210
It was truly a brutal period with 90% of Mao's forces

02:25:20.210 --> 02:25:22.370
not living to see the end of the journey.

02:25:22.370 --> 02:25:26.000
This nonstop suffering did not phase the communist leader.

02:25:26.000 --> 02:25:30.890
However, in October, 1935, Mao and the remaining 10%

02:25:30.890 --> 02:25:34.730
of his company arrived in the northeast province of Shaanxi

02:25:34.730 --> 02:25:38.210
and united with local communist forces working out of there.

02:25:38.210 --> 02:25:41.540
More of the peasantry and neighboring areas were recruited

02:25:41.540 --> 02:25:44.210
as the CCP treated them exceedingly well

02:25:44.210 --> 02:25:48.440
and plans began to continue the war against the KMT.

02:25:48.440 --> 02:25:51.980
However, in 1937 hostilities ceased

02:25:51.980 --> 02:25:53.630
between the two parties.

02:25:53.630 --> 02:25:56.450
Japan was increasingly dangerous to the future

02:25:56.450 --> 02:25:57.920
of China's existence,

02:25:57.920 --> 02:26:02.690
forcing the KMT and the CCP to form a second united front

02:26:02.690 --> 02:26:04.070
against them.

02:26:04.070 --> 02:26:06.920
Chiang Kai-shek did not want to accept this piece,

02:26:06.920 --> 02:26:08.180
though his hand was forced

02:26:08.180 --> 02:26:10.580
after he was seized by his own generals

02:26:10.580 --> 02:26:12.170
who believed the Japanese threat

02:26:12.170 --> 02:26:14.513
to be larger than the Communist one.

02:26:15.477 --> 02:26:19.070
(suspenseful music)

02:26:19.070 --> 02:26:23.840
The second Sino-Japanese war began in July, 1937

02:26:23.840 --> 02:26:26.240
and would last until the end of World War II

02:26:26.240 --> 02:26:28.370
in September, 1945.

02:26:28.370 --> 02:26:31.160
It would be the sign of some of the most disturbing battles

02:26:31.160 --> 02:26:34.220
and massacres, not only in Chinese history,

02:26:34.220 --> 02:26:36.560
but in that of the entire world.

02:26:36.560 --> 02:26:39.710
The Japanese already had one foot ahead of the Chinese

02:26:39.710 --> 02:26:42.350
because of the favorable terms that had been outlined

02:26:42.350 --> 02:26:44.690
in their previous ceasefire agreement.

02:26:44.690 --> 02:26:46.370
They controlled regions of China

02:26:46.370 --> 02:26:49.220
that the KMT were not allowed to militarize in

02:26:49.220 --> 02:26:52.160
and already had troops stationed within her borders.

02:26:52.160 --> 02:26:56.540
After taking Beijing and Shanghai by November of 1937,

02:26:56.540 --> 02:26:58.010
the Japanese set their sights

02:26:58.010 --> 02:27:00.530
on the KMT's capital of Nanjing.

02:27:00.530 --> 02:27:04.850
This resulted in the slaughter of over 200,000 Chinese

02:27:04.850 --> 02:27:08.930
and a massacre widely known as the Rape of Nanjing.

02:27:08.930 --> 02:27:10.580
In December of the same year,

02:27:10.580 --> 02:27:12.470
Japanese troops had begun making their way

02:27:12.470 --> 02:27:13.790
to the capital city.

02:27:13.790 --> 02:27:16.220
By this time, Chiang Kai-shek had already pulled

02:27:16.220 --> 02:27:18.740
all official army members out of Nanjing

02:27:18.740 --> 02:27:21.830
as he did not wanna suffer a major loss of troops.

02:27:21.830 --> 02:27:23.900
This left the city utterly hopeless

02:27:23.900 --> 02:27:26.570
in the face of the imperial Japanese military

02:27:26.570 --> 02:27:30.140
defended only by mostly untrained auxiliary troops

02:27:30.140 --> 02:27:33.440
that served as support personnel to the KMT army.

02:27:33.440 --> 02:27:36.080
During the Japanese soldiers march to the city,

02:27:36.080 --> 02:27:38.180
the Nanjing safety zone had been prepared

02:27:38.180 --> 02:27:39.440
in the heart of the city.

02:27:39.440 --> 02:27:42.560
Many westerners, including missionaries and businessmen,

02:27:42.560 --> 02:27:44.570
were residing in the city at the time

02:27:44.570 --> 02:27:47.990
and set up a series of demilitarized refugee camps

02:27:47.990 --> 02:27:50.450
for the citizens that had not fled the city.

02:27:50.450 --> 02:27:55.370
This move would end up saving the lives of 250,000 people.

02:27:55.370 --> 02:27:57.890
On December 13th, the Japanese arrived

02:27:57.890 --> 02:28:00.410
and faced little military resistance.

02:28:00.410 --> 02:28:03.590
They began executing Chinese prisoners of war

02:28:03.590 --> 02:28:05.900
and started forming mass graves.

02:28:05.900 --> 02:28:07.430
Homes were ransacked,

02:28:07.430 --> 02:28:09.200
buildings were burnt and destroyed,

02:28:09.200 --> 02:28:11.720
and the soldiers began separating families

02:28:11.720 --> 02:28:13.550
of the terrified citizens.

02:28:13.550 --> 02:28:17.300
Some of the Japanese men engaged in kill contests,

02:28:17.300 --> 02:28:19.490
where they would race to see who could be the first

02:28:19.490 --> 02:28:23.030
to execute 100 victims using only a sword.

02:28:23.030 --> 02:28:25.550
Prisoners were used as target practice.

02:28:25.550 --> 02:28:28.580
Young children were promptly executed while their mothers

02:28:28.580 --> 02:28:31.970
viciously raped and then killed by Japanese troops.

02:28:31.970 --> 02:28:35.330
Unarmed boys were beheaded in indiscriminate slaughter,

02:28:35.330 --> 02:28:37.910
whenever spotted by the Japanese troops,

02:28:37.910 --> 02:28:41.390
young girls were dragged into the street to be abused.

02:28:41.390 --> 02:28:44.960
The Nanjing massacre is among the worst atrocities

02:28:44.960 --> 02:28:46.400
in human history

02:28:46.400 --> 02:28:49.790
and is an eternal stain on the history of East Asia.

02:28:49.790 --> 02:28:53.780
It is estimated that 200,000 civilians were massacred

02:28:53.780 --> 02:28:57.350
with 20,000 to 80,000.

02:28:57.350 --> 02:29:00.200
After the Japanese decimation of Nanjing,

02:29:00.200 --> 02:29:02.930
the de facto Chinese capital became Wuhan,

02:29:02.930 --> 02:29:06.680
which acted as the site for the aptly named Battle of Wuhan,

02:29:06.680 --> 02:29:09.590
which lasted for four months in 1938.

02:29:09.590 --> 02:29:12.590
Hundreds of thousands died as both sides suffered

02:29:12.590 --> 02:29:15.440
unimaginably high casualties.

02:29:15.440 --> 02:29:18.170
Though it resulted in another Japanese victory,

02:29:18.170 --> 02:29:20.810
the heavy losses weakened the imperial army

02:29:20.810 --> 02:29:23.990
who were also now struggling with military financing.

02:29:23.990 --> 02:29:26.210
When they pushed into communist army territory

02:29:26.210 --> 02:29:27.530
in the following period,

02:29:27.530 --> 02:29:30.890
a Japanese retreat was forced by guerrilla fighters.

02:29:30.890 --> 02:29:32.870
The tides of war were shifting

02:29:32.870 --> 02:29:36.050
with the Allied Chinese slowing down the imperial Japanese

02:29:36.050 --> 02:29:39.800
Army's advances until something of a stalemate was reached

02:29:39.800 --> 02:29:43.190
and major large pitched battles became less common.

02:29:43.190 --> 02:29:46.130
The guerrilla tactics had proved highly effective

02:29:46.130 --> 02:29:49.010
and allowed for the preservation of the Chinese military

02:29:49.010 --> 02:29:50.780
in the face of their invaders.

02:29:50.780 --> 02:29:53.420
They held out until the end of World War II

02:29:53.420 --> 02:29:56.480
and lived to see Japan's major defeat at the hands

02:29:56.480 --> 02:29:58.340
of the Allied United States,

02:29:58.340 --> 02:30:01.760
with the nuclear bombings of Hiroshima and Nagasaki.

02:30:01.760 --> 02:30:04.130
In September of 1945,

02:30:04.130 --> 02:30:07.040
the Japanese formerly surrendered in China.

02:30:07.040 --> 02:30:09.560
With the end of the war, China was recognized

02:30:09.560 --> 02:30:13.640
as one of the big four allies alongside the United Kingdom,

02:30:13.640 --> 02:30:16.520
the Soviet Union, and the United States,

02:30:16.520 --> 02:30:19.880
and regained all the territory that the Japanese had taken.

02:30:19.880 --> 02:30:23.180
The final days of World War II did not see the fighting stop

02:30:23.180 --> 02:30:26.000
in China, however, the Civil War resumed

02:30:26.000 --> 02:30:28.100
and a battle for the remaining resources

02:30:28.100 --> 02:30:30.560
and major metropolitan areas commenced

02:30:30.560 --> 02:30:33.500
between the KMT and the CCP.

02:30:33.500 --> 02:30:37.340
The United States tried to mediate the conflict, but failed.

02:30:37.340 --> 02:30:41.930
The resumed Civil War lasted from 1945 to 1949

02:30:41.930 --> 02:30:43.640
and resulted in Mao Zedong

02:30:43.640 --> 02:30:46.790
and his hardened Red Army taking control over China

02:30:46.790 --> 02:30:48.050
once and for all.

02:30:48.050 --> 02:30:51.200
Having been able to garner far more support than the KMT

02:30:51.200 --> 02:30:53.930
in rural areas, Zedong was able to capture

02:30:53.930 --> 02:30:56.030
the resource rich centers of the country

02:30:56.030 --> 02:30:59.000
using his People's Liberation Army,

02:30:59.000 --> 02:31:01.010
the armed wing of the CCP.

02:31:01.010 --> 02:31:03.500
It was truly a decisive victory

02:31:03.500 --> 02:31:05.060
with the strength of the two armies

02:31:05.060 --> 02:31:07.520
essentially being reversed from what they had been

02:31:07.520 --> 02:31:09.593
in the first part of the Civil War.

02:31:11.004 --> 02:31:13.587
(gentle music)

02:31:14.630 --> 02:31:17.120
The People's Republic of China was established

02:31:17.120 --> 02:31:21.110
by the CCP on October 1st, 1949.

02:31:21.110 --> 02:31:24.860
A 55-year-old Mao Zedong now leading the country

02:31:24.860 --> 02:31:28.340
was initially seeing very favorably by the people of China,

02:31:28.340 --> 02:31:30.980
as he had once again reunited China

02:31:30.980 --> 02:31:33.260
and seemed to be a man of the people.

02:31:33.260 --> 02:31:36.620
Mao was able to reduce class inequality in his first years

02:31:36.620 --> 02:31:39.320
in office by implementing major reforms

02:31:39.320 --> 02:31:42.080
that redistributed land amongst the peasantry.

02:31:42.080 --> 02:31:46.160
Over 1 million landlords were executed during this time,

02:31:46.160 --> 02:31:48.860
known as the land reform movement.

02:31:48.860 --> 02:31:52.190
As Mao desired to destroy the remaining fragments

02:31:52.190 --> 02:31:55.550
of futile and capitalist societies in China.

02:31:55.550 --> 02:31:57.710
He also desired the modernization

02:31:57.710 --> 02:31:59.720
and industrialization of China

02:31:59.720 --> 02:32:02.930
and attempted to do so in the 1958 social

02:32:02.930 --> 02:32:06.590
and economic campaign called The Great Leap Forward,

02:32:06.590 --> 02:32:09.770
which would result in the execution in famine related deaths

02:32:09.770 --> 02:32:14.570
of somewhere between 30 and 45 million Chinese citizens.

02:32:14.570 --> 02:32:17.060
The reforms focused on collectivization

02:32:17.060 --> 02:32:20.420
and communal farming was introduced as nobody was allowed

02:32:20.420 --> 02:32:22.190
to own private property.

02:32:22.190 --> 02:32:25.430
The monopolization of agriculture allowed for the government

02:32:25.430 --> 02:32:27.320
to cheaply acquire grain.

02:32:27.320 --> 02:32:30.380
During this time, backyard furnaces were implemented

02:32:30.380 --> 02:32:33.620
within each commune to encourage steel production.

02:32:33.620 --> 02:32:36.230
Though nobody was trained particularly well

02:32:36.230 --> 02:32:38.180
on how exactly to work with them,

02:32:38.180 --> 02:32:40.520
people were forced to hurl their possessions

02:32:40.520 --> 02:32:43.280
into the furnaces to increase steel production

02:32:43.280 --> 02:32:46.220
and larger factories began to pop up as well.

02:32:46.220 --> 02:32:48.830
Many were pulled from their initial jobs in schooling

02:32:48.830 --> 02:32:51.830
to work in these factories, but it was no use.

02:32:51.830 --> 02:32:55.250
At every avenue, the steel production was predictably

02:32:55.250 --> 02:32:59.480
an immense failure that produced consistently poor quality

02:32:59.480 --> 02:33:02.360
and oftentimes unusable results,

02:33:02.360 --> 02:33:04.850
and simply diverted important manpower

02:33:04.850 --> 02:33:07.760
and resources away from essential industries

02:33:07.760 --> 02:33:09.680
such as food production.

02:33:09.680 --> 02:33:13.280
By 1959, the Greek Chinese famine began

02:33:13.280 --> 02:33:15.620
as a result of these policy failures

02:33:15.620 --> 02:33:18.140
as well as natural weather disasters

02:33:18.140 --> 02:33:20.780
that ruined the green reserves of the communities.

02:33:20.780 --> 02:33:23.300
Reports of the consumption of household pets,

02:33:23.300 --> 02:33:26.750
and even cannibalism became increasingly common

02:33:26.750 --> 02:33:27.710
at this time.

02:33:27.710 --> 02:33:30.050
The famines caused by the Great Leap Forward

02:33:30.050 --> 02:33:33.530
had killed tens of millions of Chinese citizens

02:33:33.530 --> 02:33:36.470
forcing Mao's resignation as state chairman.

02:33:36.470 --> 02:33:38.870
He was succeeded by Liu Shaoqi.

02:33:38.870 --> 02:33:41.660
Though Mao had not truly given up his power

02:33:41.660 --> 02:33:45.770
in any real sense, it was merely a temporary retreat.

02:33:45.770 --> 02:33:49.610
In July of 1966, Mao took a symbolic dip

02:33:49.610 --> 02:33:52.310
in the Yangtze River to demonstrate his good health

02:33:52.310 --> 02:33:54.710
and capable mind following rumors

02:33:54.710 --> 02:33:57.260
that his old age had taken a toll on him.

02:33:57.260 --> 02:33:59.720
He became the state chairman once again

02:33:59.720 --> 02:34:02.750
and began his second period of reforms,

02:34:02.750 --> 02:34:04.760
the cultural revolution.

02:34:04.760 --> 02:34:07.970
The movement aimed to once again destroy all remnants

02:34:07.970 --> 02:34:10.850
of capitalist sentiment in Chinese society

02:34:10.850 --> 02:34:14.000
and secure Maoist power at the helm of China.

02:34:14.000 --> 02:34:16.430
It did so by launching a radical campaign

02:34:16.430 --> 02:34:19.400
against the bourgeois infiltrators,

02:34:19.400 --> 02:34:22.340
he perceived to be negatively affecting the country.

02:34:22.340 --> 02:34:25.460
Mao mobilized a student led youth organization

02:34:25.460 --> 02:34:27.290
named the Red Guards,

02:34:27.290 --> 02:34:31.190
encouraging them to put down any anti Maoist sentiment.

02:34:31.190 --> 02:34:34.460
The Red Guard soldiers worshiped Mao like a God

02:34:34.460 --> 02:34:36.410
and would do whatever was asked of them.

02:34:36.410 --> 02:34:40.100
This spurred the Red August, a series of massacres

02:34:40.100 --> 02:34:43.160
that would result in the deaths of 10,000 people.

02:34:43.160 --> 02:34:46.730
27 educators were murdered by their own students

02:34:46.730 --> 02:34:50.030
during this time for opposing the chairman's policies.

02:34:50.030 --> 02:34:51.800
While countless other intellectuals

02:34:51.800 --> 02:34:54.200
and elderly citizens were tortured,

02:34:54.200 --> 02:34:57.350
the police were banned from interfering with the violence.

02:34:57.350 --> 02:34:59.660
As Mao continued to encourage the slaughter

02:34:59.660 --> 02:35:01.670
and torture of those who opposed him,

02:35:01.670 --> 02:35:05.240
temples, scriptures and historical sites were destroyed

02:35:05.240 --> 02:35:09.290
by Red Guards in the name of producing a new reformed China.

02:35:09.290 --> 02:35:12.890
The country fell into anarchy when the revolutionaries began

02:35:12.890 --> 02:35:16.730
dividing up into factions, prompting Mao to restore order

02:35:16.730 --> 02:35:20.690
with the use of the official military in 1968.

02:35:20.690 --> 02:35:23.390
He turned on the Red Guards as they had served their purpose

02:35:23.390 --> 02:35:24.800
in destroying his enemies

02:35:24.800 --> 02:35:26.930
and banished many to the countryside

02:35:26.930 --> 02:35:29.600
where they would be less of a danger to society.

02:35:29.600 --> 02:35:32.150
By the time the cultural revolution had ended,

02:35:32.150 --> 02:35:36.380
somewhere between 500,000 to 2 million had perished.

02:35:36.380 --> 02:35:39.380
By the time Mao died in 1976,

02:35:39.380 --> 02:35:43.160
he had approximately 40 million to 80 million deaths

02:35:43.160 --> 02:35:46.760
of starvation, overwork, and mass execution

02:35:46.760 --> 02:35:48.230
attributed to his name.

02:35:48.230 --> 02:35:50.780
Mao was succeeded by Deng Xiaoping

02:35:50.780 --> 02:35:54.290
who would openly criticize Mao's policies in coming years

02:35:54.290 --> 02:35:57.050
and lean towards a slightly more open China

02:35:57.050 --> 02:35:58.970
with a market driven economy.

02:35:58.970 --> 02:36:02.060
China's trade and economy were greatly strengthened

02:36:02.060 --> 02:36:05.630
and the GDP would increase tenfold because of his reign.

02:36:05.630 --> 02:36:09.932
There were however, still turbulent times ahead.

02:36:09.932 --> 02:36:12.515
(gentle music)

02:36:14.480 --> 02:36:18.560
In the spring of 1989, there was a major call for political

02:36:18.560 --> 02:36:21.590
and economic reform of China's communist leadership

02:36:21.590 --> 02:36:23.510
among university students.

02:36:23.510 --> 02:36:25.070
There was an increasing sentiment

02:36:25.070 --> 02:36:27.140
that communism was on the decline

02:36:27.140 --> 02:36:29.750
and a tipping point was reached when Hu Yaobang,

02:36:29.750 --> 02:36:31.880
former chairman and general secretary

02:36:31.880 --> 02:36:33.350
of the Chinese Communist Party,

02:36:33.350 --> 02:36:38.350
died on April 15th, 1989 at the age of 73,

02:36:38.360 --> 02:36:40.790
who was well-liked by the population

02:36:40.790 --> 02:36:42.470
and was seen as a beacon of hope

02:36:42.470 --> 02:36:45.830
in a political landscape of corruption and nepotism.

02:36:45.830 --> 02:36:49.340
An enemy of many party elders who was an advocate

02:36:49.340 --> 02:36:52.100
for more liberal economic policies

02:36:52.100 --> 02:36:55.940
and less restrictions on free speech whose death turned him

02:36:55.940 --> 02:36:58.520
into something of an emblem for liberalization

02:36:58.520 --> 02:36:59.930
amongst the students.

02:36:59.930 --> 02:37:03.290
His funeral proceedings commenced on April 22nd,

02:37:03.290 --> 02:37:05.000
and public gatherings were arranged

02:37:05.000 --> 02:37:07.430
to honor him in numerous Chinese cities.

02:37:07.430 --> 02:37:10.370
These gatherings began to serve as demonstrations

02:37:10.370 --> 02:37:13.070
to protest the country's lack of democracy.

02:37:13.070 --> 02:37:16.640
The largest of these demonstrations was in Tiananmen Square

02:37:16.640 --> 02:37:19.760
in the heart of Beijing, and it only continued to grow

02:37:19.760 --> 02:37:21.980
after clashes with police spurred more

02:37:21.980 --> 02:37:25.190
and more angered students to join in protest.

02:37:25.190 --> 02:37:27.050
The students' desired dialogue

02:37:27.050 --> 02:37:29.780
with the government and drafted seven demands

02:37:29.780 --> 02:37:31.031
for the ruling class.

02:37:31.031 --> 02:37:35.030
(protesters chanting)

02:37:35.030 --> 02:37:37.070
The pleas were as follows.

02:37:37.070 --> 02:37:40.250
One, affirm Hu Yaobang's views on democracy

02:37:40.250 --> 02:37:41.840
and freedom as correct.

02:37:41.840 --> 02:37:45.410
Two, admit that the campaigns against spiritual pollution

02:37:45.410 --> 02:37:48.440
and bourgeois liberalization had been wrong.

02:37:48.440 --> 02:37:52.010
Three, publish information on the income of state leaders

02:37:52.010 --> 02:37:53.600
and their family members.

02:37:53.600 --> 02:37:56.420
Four, allow privately run newspapers

02:37:56.420 --> 02:37:58.250
and stop press censorship.

02:37:58.250 --> 02:38:00.860
Five, increased funding for education

02:38:00.860 --> 02:38:02.840
and raise intellectuals pay.

02:38:02.840 --> 02:38:06.710
Six, end restrictions on demonstrations in Beijing.

02:38:06.710 --> 02:38:09.080
Seven, provide objective coverage

02:38:09.080 --> 02:38:11.240
of students in official media.

02:38:11.240 --> 02:38:13.610
When the students attempted to bring their demands

02:38:13.610 --> 02:38:15.620
to a committee of the Communist Party,

02:38:15.620 --> 02:38:19.280
the police shut them down once again, though they continued

02:38:19.280 --> 02:38:20.840
to fight for their cause.

02:38:20.840 --> 02:38:23.660
Strikes started at the country's universities

02:38:23.660 --> 02:38:26.180
and the government began taking a harsher stance

02:38:26.180 --> 02:38:27.380
on the protests.

02:38:27.380 --> 02:38:29.900
Fearing anarchy, they accused the students

02:38:29.900 --> 02:38:31.670
of plotting civil unrest,

02:38:31.670 --> 02:38:34.517
which only led to greater anger on both sides.

02:38:34.517 --> 02:38:38.540
100,000 students and workers took to Tiananmen Square

02:38:38.540 --> 02:38:40.790
to protest following this decision,

02:38:40.790 --> 02:38:43.910
demanding that the government retract their declaration,

02:38:43.910 --> 02:38:46.070
many took to hunger striking,

02:38:46.070 --> 02:38:48.560
which garnered more support for their cause.

02:38:48.560 --> 02:38:50.510
Speeches from the government in the Square

02:38:50.510 --> 02:38:52.010
were unsuccessful.

02:38:52.010 --> 02:38:53.843
The students would not let up.

02:38:55.566 --> 02:38:58.910
- The students have certain requirements which must be met,

02:38:58.910 --> 02:39:01.280
otherwise they won't leave the Square.

02:39:01.280 --> 02:39:02.720
- [Narrator] After multiple debates

02:39:02.720 --> 02:39:05.210
and plenty of inner turmoil within the government

02:39:05.210 --> 02:39:09.170
on how to handle the situation, many officials were fired.

02:39:09.170 --> 02:39:13.250
In the last two weeks of May, Marshall Law was declared

02:39:13.250 --> 02:39:16.040
and the military was ordered into Beijing,

02:39:16.040 --> 02:39:18.980
but the troops were blocked by Beijing citizens

02:39:18.980 --> 02:39:21.860
who flooded the streets in massive droves.

02:39:21.860 --> 02:39:24.590
Some art students among the protestors built

02:39:24.590 --> 02:39:28.610
and erected a massive paper mache statue called the Goddess

02:39:28.610 --> 02:39:31.310
of Democracy, which became a symbol

02:39:31.310 --> 02:39:34.100
of their defiance against the Communist Party.

02:39:34.100 --> 02:39:37.130
Many western journalists were stationed in the Square,

02:39:37.130 --> 02:39:38.930
broadcasting the events to the rest

02:39:38.930 --> 02:39:41.510
of the world just like the government however,

02:39:41.510 --> 02:39:44.060
the students were becoming increasingly hectic

02:39:44.060 --> 02:39:46.040
and entered a state of disarray.

02:39:46.040 --> 02:39:48.350
The Square was incredibly overcrowded

02:39:48.350 --> 02:39:51.260
and the protesters lacked centralized leadership.

02:39:51.260 --> 02:39:53.900
Students began breaking up into factions

02:39:53.900 --> 02:39:56.750
and accusing each other of having ulterior motives

02:39:56.750 --> 02:39:59.840
such as becoming famous from the protests

02:39:59.840 --> 02:40:03.050
or even secretly conspiring with the government.

02:40:03.050 --> 02:40:05.900
It was a perfect storm of chaos.

02:40:05.900 --> 02:40:09.560
It was at this time that all hell broke loose.

02:40:09.560 --> 02:40:10.880
By the dawn of June,

02:40:10.880 --> 02:40:12.890
the government reached a breaking point,

02:40:12.890 --> 02:40:14.180
and on the third of the month,

02:40:14.180 --> 02:40:17.750
the People's Liberation Army was ordered into Beijing.

02:40:17.750 --> 02:40:20.450
The government issued an emergency broadcast

02:40:20.450 --> 02:40:23.780
demanding citizens to stay out of Tiananmen Square,

02:40:23.780 --> 02:40:26.090
but the protestors did not listen.

02:40:26.090 --> 02:40:28.700
Some students created their own broadcasts

02:40:28.700 --> 02:40:31.610
and called for the city's inhabitants to arm themselves

02:40:31.610 --> 02:40:34.550
and head to the Square to fight against the government.

02:40:34.550 --> 02:40:36.710
When the troops arrived in Beijing,

02:40:36.710 --> 02:40:39.320
protestors began lighting buses on fire

02:40:39.320 --> 02:40:41.180
to try to block the Army's path,

02:40:41.180 --> 02:40:44.810
prompting the troops to open fire with their assault rifles.

02:40:44.810 --> 02:40:47.990
Many were killed while others were ruthlessly beaten

02:40:47.990 --> 02:40:50.090
by gangs of troops in the streets.

02:40:50.090 --> 02:40:52.010
Some soldiers were caught by rock

02:40:52.010 --> 02:40:56.060
and Molotov cocktail wielding protestors and beaten to death

02:40:56.060 --> 02:40:58.520
after being dragged outside of their vehicles.

02:40:58.520 --> 02:41:00.230
The tanks marched forward

02:41:00.230 --> 02:41:02.300
crushing those who stood in their way.

02:41:02.300 --> 02:41:05.180
Because of the government's crackdown on any remembrance

02:41:05.180 --> 02:41:08.360
or recognition of the Tiananmen Square massacre,

02:41:08.360 --> 02:41:11.390
it is still unknown just how many were killed

02:41:11.390 --> 02:41:13.070
in the chaotic clashes.

02:41:13.070 --> 02:41:16.190
Journalists were prevented from reporting on the events,

02:41:16.190 --> 02:41:18.380
so little footage remains.

02:41:18.380 --> 02:41:20.840
Even though there is no official death toll,

02:41:20.840 --> 02:41:24.740
estimates range between several 100 to 10,000.

02:41:24.740 --> 02:41:26.360
By the morning of June 5th,

02:41:26.360 --> 02:41:29.990
the troops had seized complete control of Tiananmen Square

02:41:29.990 --> 02:41:32.660
and cleared the area of protestors.

02:41:32.660 --> 02:41:36.200
There was however, one infamous lone protestor

02:41:36.200 --> 02:41:40.400
known as Tank Man who continued his resistance that day.

02:41:40.400 --> 02:41:44.060
An American photographer named Jeff Widener captured images

02:41:44.060 --> 02:41:47.930
of a solitary, unarmed protestor confronting a line

02:41:47.930 --> 02:41:48.770
of tanks.

02:41:48.770 --> 02:41:51.710
A photograph of Tank Man got Widener nominated

02:41:51.710 --> 02:41:53.360
for a Pulitzer Prize,

02:41:53.360 --> 02:41:56.840
and the imagery has since been adopted globally as a symbol

02:41:56.840 --> 02:42:00.020
of resistance in the face of oppression and tyranny.

02:42:00.020 --> 02:42:02.570
Following the government's control of the Square,

02:42:02.570 --> 02:42:05.090
all governmental and state media employees

02:42:05.090 --> 02:42:08.480
who expressed sympathetic attitudes towards the students

02:42:08.480 --> 02:42:12.530
lost their jobs, with some being placed on house arrest.

02:42:12.530 --> 02:42:16.190
Some known protestors were executed after the fact,

02:42:16.190 --> 02:42:19.160
while others were handed long prison sentences.

02:42:19.160 --> 02:42:21.920
Being a democratic country that mostly sympathized

02:42:21.920 --> 02:42:24.320
with the anti-communist protests,

02:42:24.320 --> 02:42:26.660
the United States issued both diplomatic

02:42:26.660 --> 02:42:29.090
and economic sanctions on China

02:42:29.090 --> 02:42:31.460
and the Western world's opinion on the country

02:42:31.460 --> 02:42:32.990
greatly soured.

02:42:32.990 --> 02:42:36.410
The country's economic state was significantly weakened

02:42:36.410 --> 02:42:39.059
by the sudden lack of trade.

02:42:39.059 --> 02:42:41.476
(calm music)

02:42:42.830 --> 02:42:45.020
A period of great changes was occurring

02:42:45.020 --> 02:42:47.990
around the remaining communist world during this time,

02:42:47.990 --> 02:42:51.500
and in 1991, the Soviet Union collapsed,

02:42:51.500 --> 02:42:55.730
leaving China as the only major communist state on earth.

02:42:55.730 --> 02:42:57.740
Despite this global isolation

02:42:57.740 --> 02:42:59.660
as well as the fiscal hit taken

02:42:59.660 --> 02:43:01.790
following the Tiananmen incident,

02:43:01.790 --> 02:43:05.570
China was able to recover financially throughout the 1990s

02:43:05.570 --> 02:43:07.940
after sanctions were gradually lifted

02:43:07.940 --> 02:43:10.670
as a more mixed economy of capitalism

02:43:10.670 --> 02:43:13.220
and socialism began to take shape.

02:43:13.220 --> 02:43:15.740
Insular foreign policies were reversed,

02:43:15.740 --> 02:43:18.890
and the open for trade country continued operating

02:43:18.890 --> 02:43:21.350
under the mantra of the now retired

02:43:21.350 --> 02:43:26.120
Deng Xiopang's famed mantra, "To get rich is glorious."

02:43:26.120 --> 02:43:28.520
We are getting closer to the modern day,

02:43:28.520 --> 02:43:30.710
which brings us to the most important figure

02:43:30.710 --> 02:43:33.650
of contemporary China, Xi Jinping,

02:43:33.650 --> 02:43:38.650
but who exactly is Xi Jinping and where did he come from?

02:43:39.131 --> 02:43:41.881
(dramatic music)

02:43:43.010 --> 02:43:47.840
On the 15th of June, 1953, Xi Jinping was born in Beijing.

02:43:47.840 --> 02:43:51.770
His father, Xi Zhongxun was a former member of the Red Army

02:43:51.770 --> 02:43:54.470
and had been comrades in arms with Mao Zedong

02:43:54.470 --> 02:43:56.420
during the Chinese Civil War.

02:43:56.420 --> 02:43:58.370
He served as a high ranking official

02:43:58.370 --> 02:43:59.840
within the Communist Party,

02:43:59.840 --> 02:44:01.940
and though would eventually fall out of favor

02:44:01.940 --> 02:44:03.200
with the Chinese government

02:44:03.200 --> 02:44:05.450
after openly critiquing their handling

02:44:05.450 --> 02:44:07.760
of the Tiananmen Square protests,

02:44:07.760 --> 02:44:12.137
he was able to hold a position until his retirement in 1993.

02:44:12.137 --> 02:44:16.310
Xi Jinping's mother, Qi Xin was a like-minded communist

02:44:16.310 --> 02:44:17.660
who had worked with the government

02:44:17.660 --> 02:44:21.260
as a consultant in the Communist party state-run schools.

02:44:21.260 --> 02:44:24.260
After his graduation from Tsinghua University's

02:44:24.260 --> 02:44:26.930
chemical engineering program in Beijing,

02:44:26.930 --> 02:44:30.830
Jinping's political career began in 1972.

02:44:30.830 --> 02:44:33.950
He started out working as a secretary for Geng Biao,

02:44:33.950 --> 02:44:35.750
a senior official in the government,

02:44:35.750 --> 02:44:38.240
and a former subordinate of his father's.

02:44:38.240 --> 02:44:40.100
After three years under Geng,

02:44:40.100 --> 02:44:43.970
Xi began working as a deputy secretary for the CCP

02:44:43.970 --> 02:44:45.650
in the province of Hebei,

02:44:45.650 --> 02:44:49.400
a position that includes working with policy implementations

02:44:49.400 --> 02:44:51.260
and party organization.

02:44:51.260 --> 02:44:53.120
He did an exceptional job

02:44:53.120 --> 02:44:55.280
and continued to climb the governmental ladder

02:44:55.280 --> 02:44:57.200
throughout the 80s and 90s,

02:44:57.200 --> 02:45:01.340
marrying famed folk singer Peng Liyuan along the way.

02:45:01.340 --> 02:45:03.800
By 1999, he had achieved the role

02:45:03.800 --> 02:45:06.500
of the Fujian province's acting governor.

02:45:06.500 --> 02:45:09.710
This meant that he had boosted administrative control

02:45:09.710 --> 02:45:12.470
and a larger hand in infrastructure development.

02:45:12.470 --> 02:45:14.420
Though his career did not slow down

02:45:14.420 --> 02:45:16.070
with this major achievement.

02:45:16.070 --> 02:45:19.490
Eight years later, after another series of promotions,

02:45:19.490 --> 02:45:21.710
inner turmoil and controversy

02:45:21.710 --> 02:45:25.280
surrounding a major social security fund corruption scandal

02:45:25.280 --> 02:45:28.220
opened up many opportunities within the government,

02:45:28.220 --> 02:45:31.520
having successfully avoided any controversy himself

02:45:31.520 --> 02:45:33.950
Xi seized this chance to move on up.

02:45:33.950 --> 02:45:37.640
In October of 2007, the blooming politician was appointed

02:45:37.640 --> 02:45:40.370
to the nine man Politburo Standing Committee

02:45:40.370 --> 02:45:42.470
of the Chinese Communist Party.

02:45:42.470 --> 02:45:45.620
The committee consists of the government's top leadership,

02:45:45.620 --> 02:45:48.170
and when Xi was ranked above Li Keqiang,

02:45:48.170 --> 02:45:50.450
a fellow rising political star

02:45:50.450 --> 02:45:53.750
and contender for the succession of President Hu Jintao

02:45:53.750 --> 02:45:55.250
it became quite clear

02:45:55.250 --> 02:45:57.590
that he would be the nation's next leader.

02:45:57.590 --> 02:46:00.980
He was elected vice president in the spring of 2008

02:46:00.980 --> 02:46:03.470
and saw a number of major projects

02:46:03.470 --> 02:46:05.810
such as the Summer Olympics in Beijing,

02:46:05.810 --> 02:46:08.090
which took place later that same year.

02:46:08.090 --> 02:46:09.980
He also became the leading figure

02:46:09.980 --> 02:46:12.170
in the issue of affairs with Hong Kong.

02:46:12.170 --> 02:46:15.110
In later years, he would become locked into a rivalry

02:46:15.110 --> 02:46:18.950
with Bo Xilai, who was also seen as a top contender,

02:46:18.950 --> 02:46:21.470
but a major political scandal paved the way

02:46:21.470 --> 02:46:23.060
for Xi's leadership.

02:46:23.060 --> 02:46:27.020
The Wang Lijun Incident began when Neil Heywood,

02:46:27.020 --> 02:46:28.370
a British businessman,

02:46:28.370 --> 02:46:32.300
was found dead in his Chongqing hotel room in 2011.

02:46:32.300 --> 02:46:34.190
Heywood had business dealings with Bo

02:46:34.190 --> 02:46:37.400
and his spouse, Gu Xilai for over a decade.

02:46:37.400 --> 02:46:40.220
The death was initially ruled as an alcohol poisoning

02:46:40.220 --> 02:46:42.230
caused by excessive consumption.

02:46:42.230 --> 02:46:44.510
However, just a few short months later,

02:46:44.510 --> 02:46:48.080
the municipal police Chief Wang Lijan sought asylum

02:46:48.080 --> 02:46:50.360
at the United States Chinese consulate

02:46:50.360 --> 02:46:52.970
and claimed that Gu had poisoned Heywood,

02:46:52.970 --> 02:46:55.040
which was what truly killed the Brit

02:46:55.040 --> 02:46:57.350
rather than alcohol consumption.

02:46:57.350 --> 02:46:59.840
After a thorough murder investigation,

02:46:59.840 --> 02:47:02.090
the murderous truth was revealed

02:47:02.090 --> 02:47:04.640
as Gu had indeed decided to kill Neil

02:47:04.640 --> 02:47:07.220
during a mental breakdown over blackmail

02:47:07.220 --> 02:47:09.860
and demands of $22 million

02:47:09.860 --> 02:47:11.990
over a failed real estate venture.

02:47:11.990 --> 02:47:14.660
Gu was handed a suspended death sentence,

02:47:14.660 --> 02:47:17.090
though it was eventually commuted to a life sentence

02:47:17.090 --> 02:47:20.660
in late 2015, while Li Keqiang's political career

02:47:20.660 --> 02:47:22.400
was utterly decimated

02:47:22.400 --> 02:47:26.480
and he was purged of his role in the CCP as a result of him

02:47:26.480 --> 02:47:28.610
and his second wife's misconduct.

02:47:28.610 --> 02:47:30.140
This scandal paved the way

02:47:30.140 --> 02:47:33.410
for Xi Jinping's unopposed rise to power,

02:47:33.410 --> 02:47:37.130
so its effects on the modern world cannot be understated.

02:47:37.130 --> 02:47:40.820
On March 14th, 2013, Xi was elected president

02:47:40.820 --> 02:47:42.980
by the National People's Congress

02:47:42.980 --> 02:47:45.290
and quickly enacted a series of measures

02:47:45.290 --> 02:47:49.100
to fortify the Communist party's grip on Chinese society.

02:47:49.100 --> 02:47:51.440
Anti-corruption campaigns were launched

02:47:51.440 --> 02:47:55.610
to weed out political rivals, and his power was centralized.

02:47:55.610 --> 02:47:57.950
A campaign for ideological control

02:47:57.950 --> 02:48:00.710
was also set in motion after his election.

02:48:00.710 --> 02:48:03.440
Internet and media censorship were heightened

02:48:03.440 --> 02:48:06.350
to ensure no content deemed as oppositional

02:48:06.350 --> 02:48:09.980
to the CCPs ideals could be consumed in China

02:48:09.980 --> 02:48:13.190
and surveillance on civilians greatly increased.

02:48:13.190 --> 02:48:17.150
China possesses 700 million surveillance cameras,

02:48:17.150 --> 02:48:20.210
roughly one for every two citizens.

02:48:20.210 --> 02:48:23.210
Furthermore, the social credit system was introduced

02:48:23.210 --> 02:48:25.760
as a means of keeping the population in check.

02:48:25.760 --> 02:48:28.760
The social credit score essentially rates the country's

02:48:28.760 --> 02:48:32.510
individual citizens on how well they are performing in life

02:48:32.510 --> 02:48:35.840
and how aligned they are with the CCPs ideals,

02:48:35.840 --> 02:48:38.180
financial standing, criminal history,

02:48:38.180 --> 02:48:42.350
and other such factors all affect one's social credit score.

02:48:42.350 --> 02:48:46.820
By 2018, presidential term limits were completely abolished.

02:48:46.820 --> 02:48:50.270
Xi was recently awarded his third, five year term,

02:48:50.270 --> 02:48:54.440
and with such tightly consolidated power, he's now on track

02:48:54.440 --> 02:48:56.810
to remain in power for the rest of his life,

02:48:56.810 --> 02:48:59.543
or at least as long as he desires.

02:49:00.468 --> 02:49:03.051
(gentle music)

02:49:04.310 --> 02:49:07.400
Under Xi Jinping's stern authoritarian leadership,

02:49:07.400 --> 02:49:09.080
China has maintained its role

02:49:09.080 --> 02:49:11.870
as an unstoppable economic force.

02:49:11.870 --> 02:49:15.200
They continue to industrialize at a rapid pace

02:49:15.200 --> 02:49:17.990
and lead the world in the manufacturing sector.

02:49:17.990 --> 02:49:22.130
The population has now soared to 1.4 billion,

02:49:22.130 --> 02:49:26.030
surpassed only marginally in 2023 by India,

02:49:26.030 --> 02:49:29.780
and the influence of the country only continues to grow.

02:49:29.780 --> 02:49:31.430
Tensions are currently rising

02:49:31.430 --> 02:49:34.760
with Xi Jinping's potential aims to invade Taiwan

02:49:34.760 --> 02:49:38.390
and the tightening of his governmental power over Hong Kong.

02:49:38.390 --> 02:49:42.020
Many African countries that China is heavily invested in

02:49:42.020 --> 02:49:45.080
are feeling an increase in Chinese intervention as well

02:49:45.080 --> 02:49:49.550
in a process that many are labeling as Neocolonialist.

02:49:49.550 --> 02:49:53.360
Many Westerners fear the diplomatic and global implications

02:49:53.360 --> 02:49:55.220
of this aim for expansion.

02:49:55.220 --> 02:49:57.740
As the looming threat of the Chinese military

02:49:57.740 --> 02:50:00.200
becomes more threatening by the day,

02:50:00.200 --> 02:50:03.530
they have flourished into the world's second most powerful

02:50:03.530 --> 02:50:06.140
army behind just the United States

02:50:06.140 --> 02:50:09.110
and possessed the largest navy on earth.

02:50:09.110 --> 02:50:12.440
Mandarin Chinese, spoken by nearly a billion people

02:50:12.440 --> 02:50:16.160
worldwide is often called the language of the future

02:50:16.160 --> 02:50:19.970
as China continues to solidify its place as a key player

02:50:19.970 --> 02:50:22.550
in the new era of globalization.

02:50:22.550 --> 02:50:26.450
However, nobody truly knows what the next great nation

02:50:26.450 --> 02:50:29.810
of tomorrow will be or what the future will hold.

02:50:29.810 --> 02:50:33.200
There is only one certainty about the fascinating region,

02:50:33.200 --> 02:50:35.540
the stories that make up the rich history

02:50:35.540 --> 02:50:40.130
of earth's longest continuous civilization, China

02:50:40.130 --> 02:50:43.223
will be told for generations to come.

